Title Headline: 28 Skincare Products For Anyone Who Doesn't Even Know Where To Start
Short Description Sub Headline: As Troy and Gabriella sang, 🎵I feel in my heart / the start of something new 🎵
Content Body: Shopping | | Beauty | 28 Skincare Products For Anyone Who Doesn't Even Know Where To Start | As Troy and Gabriella sang, 🎵I feel in my heart / the start of something new 🎵 | Posted on March 27, 2020, 18:00 GMT | March 27, 2020, 18:00 GMT | Sarah HanBuzzFeed Staff | GlossierPromising review: "I was a skeptic when it came to Glossier products all around, but I am so in love with this face wash. It makes my face feel clean without all the fake stuff that the 'lathered' face washes give you, and it is so gentle on my face! I suffered forever from hormonal breakouts (from birth control and PCOS) and this face wash calmed down all of that during ALL times of the month (if you catch my drift). Because of my lash extensions (gotta stay oil free), this cleanser is my end-all-be-all of face cleansers. I highly recommend it to everyone I meet!!!" —LizGet it from Glossier for $9+ (available in two sizes). And for any ~waterproof makeup formulas~, start with their Milky Oil. | Soko GlamThey're already not very noticeable (for daytime wear), but now that you're stuck at home all day, it's even easier to stick 'em on and treat your acne at first sight! Promising review: "I’ve tried so many products, including products prescribed by dermatologists, and none of them work as fast as the acne pimple master patch. My pimples are resolved quickly. —Anamaria W.Get a pack of 24 from Soko Glam for $5. Also available in Clear Fit and AC Collection (slightly larger, oval-shaped patches infused with soothing centella asiatica extract) versions. | @fleshbeauty / Via instagram.com, @fleshbeauty / Via instagram.comAgain, even if you're inside all day, you still need to wear SPF — sun rays can still penetrate your skin through windows!! This SPF has definitely stolen my heart. In my past sunscreen reviews, it's no surprise that I love chemical formulas and my skin handles them very well — but as always, do a patch test first if you're not sure! This SPF contains 10% homosalate, 5% octisalate, and 3% avobenzone — note that there's no oxybenzone or octinoxate, which has been in the news re: ocean preservation and the Hawaii ban. It's also super hydrating (hence the "serum" part), thanks to ingredients like glycerin, which attracts water to your skin. Don't fret about the white-ish color 'cause it instantly applies clear on skin. My skin doesn't feel tacky afterwards, but it definitely grips onto makeup super well. Get it from Flesh Beauty for $32. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Sephora, Sarah Han / BuzzFeedI actually prefer this over the cult-fave Color Correcting Treatment (see below), mostly texture-wise since it's lighter. I find that this gel cream also blurs any redness I have without feeling heavy, sticky, or taking a long time to absorb. I get redness around my nose and sometimes scattered on my cheeks, so this is a quick fix — and since it's a lot lighter than the treatment and hydrating enough for my skin type, I've been applying it day *and* night.Promising review: "I haven't really found something that calms redness but also doesn't make me break out from being too heavy, and then I got a sample of this with an order and was pretty happy with it. My skin was super soft, stayed clear, and looked slightly less red. Then, I went on vacation to New Hampshire. I spent four and a half hours hiking in 20 degree windy weather with snow and ice blowing in my face. My skin was bright red and stung from windburn. I put some of this on after I showered, and then a little more before I went to bed. After the first time I put it on my face, it no longer stung, and by morning, my skin wasn't red at all. Normally I would be red for a few days and then peeling afterwards. I am definitely going to purchase a full size of this, and I think it will be really helpful for the New England winter and beyond." —cayjayGet it from Sephora for $48. | Sarah Han / BuzzFeed / Via buzzfeed.comHow does it work its magic? Papaya and pineapple enzymes help loosen dead skin cells in preparation for removal, and then soft plant-based fibers act like ~micro-lint rollers~ to capture and roll away dirt and dry, flaky skin.Promising review: "Let me tell you! I've tried EVERYTHING, including Proactive and Rodan & Fields, and nothing has helped my skin in the way that this (and the cleansing collection) have! My skin is combination that reacts to EVERYTHING, but after two days of using this, my redness, peeling, and oily patches were GONE! I can't get over how much I love this! I actually enjoy taking care of my skin now because I can see almost immediately and feel how much of a difference this has made!" —AnonymousGet it from Target for $10.99 or Bliss for $12.99.Read my full review of the Bliss Jelly Glow Peel (#7) for more info! | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Sarah HanIt doesn't contain your average ingredients either, but rather proven nourishing and brightening ingredients like saccharomyces ferment filtrate, bamboo water, algae extract, licorice root extract, centella asiatica leaf water — and absolutely no alcohol, parabens, or artificial fragrance.Promising review: "This essence is brilliant. The mist is so fine and it's so quick to use in the morning when I'm in a rush. Leaves my face feeling fresh and hydrated, and I feel like my skin has been producing way less oil than it usually does." —Alice B.Get it from Soko Glam for $24.P.S. This product was created as a result of the Acwell pH balancing toner's popularity/effectiveness, which is obviously great as well if you'd like to pair the two! | GlossierPromising review: "I am 47 and have some age spots/discoloration, as well as splotchiness and some monthly hormonal acne. This stuff is fantastic! From the first use I noticed a difference in my skin. My pores were tighter, my face was smoother, and makeup went on better. You do have to wear an SPF because of the exfoliation, but I wear one every day anyway. After a month of use, my skin is brighter, the discoloration has lightened, and even my hormonal acne decreased. If anyone has used the expensive and hard to find Recherche Biologique 1970 toner, Glossier solution works a lot like that, without the hefty price tag. I recommend this to anyone looking to achieve brighter, clearer, and healthier skin!" —KStern119Get it from Glossier for $24.Check out our full writeup (and reviews!) on Glossier Solution for more deets! | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: Dear Toilet Paper Hoarders: This Viral TikTok Proves That Stocking Up Makes No Sense
Short Description Sub Headline: If a person uses 20 sheets of toilet paper per poo, they would have to poop 182 times a day to use up four Costco-sized packs of TP.
Content Body: Health | Dear Toilet Paper Hoarders: This Viral TikTok Proves That Stocking Up Makes No Sense | If a person uses 20 sheets of toilet paper per poo, they would have to poop 182 times a day to use up four Costco-sized packs of TP. | Posted on March 24, 2020, 18:38 GMT | March 24, 2020, 18:38 GMT | Krista TorresBuzzFeed Staff | Farrah PennBuzzFeed Staff Writer | Melanie Korach@melanie_korach | Melanie Korach | @melanie_korach | I went to the grocery store tonight and still no toilet paper, no paper towels & no Kleenex. Title Headline: Wey, no sé cómo "Los Simpson" hicieron estas 10 predicciones tan precisas del futuro pero estoy asustado
Short Description Sub Headline: De verdad son MUY extrañas.
Content Body: Wey, no sé cómo "Los Simpson" hicieron estas 10 predicciones tan precisas del futuro pero estoy asustado | De verdad son MUY extrañas. | publicado March 25, 2020, 20:02 GMT | March 25, 2020, 20:02 GMT | Jacob Trobe{"user_id": 9099919}Community Contributor | 20th Century Fox, Drew Angerer / Getty ImagesEste episodio, "Bart al futuro", se transmitió por primera vez en el 2000, 16 años antes de que Trump fuera electo. | 20th Century Fox, Tim Robberts / Getty ImagesEl episodio "Lisa y los deportes" se transmitió por primera vez en 1994 y presentó un dispositivo llamado Apple Newton PDA. El logotipo parece una imitación de un dispositivo Apple, pero esto fue 13 años antes del lanzamiento del primer iPhone. Cuando un personaje escribe "Golpear a Martin" el Apple Newton PDA lo autocorrige como "Comer a Martha". La cosa es que el autocorrector se presentó por primera vez en el 2005 en la vida real. Los Simpson lo presentaron 11 años antes de que sucediera. | 20th Century Fox, Tim Robberts / Getty ImagesEn 1995, Los Simpson presentaron un híbrido de teléfono y reloj en un episodio titulado "La boda de Lisa", 20 años antes del lanzamiento del Apple Watch. | 20th Century Fox, ZyngaEn el episodio "Bart en la feria" de 1998, en Los Simpson se hizo una broma sobre niños jugando en un simulador de trabajo de campo. En ese momento, la idea parecía totalmente risible. Sin embargo, en 2009, 11 años después del estreno del episodio, la gente de todo el mundo estaba obsesionada con un juego llamado FarmVille en el que podías arar, plantar y cosechar cultivos y árboles. | 20th Century Fox, IPREn el especial de Halloween, "La casita del horror XIX", una máquina para votar amañada cambia los votos de Homero por Barack Obama por votos para John McCain varias veces. El episodio se estrenó en 2008 y cuatro años después, en 2012, una máquina electrónica para votar en Filadelfia seleccionaba a Mitt Romney incluso cuando los votantes intentaban elegir a Obama. | 20th Century Fox, FoxUna versión simpsonizada de Lady Gaga actuó en el pueblo de Springfield colgando en el aire en el episodio de 2012, "Lisa y Lady Gaga". Cinco años después, en 2017, el espectáculo de medio tiempo del Super Bowl mostró a Gaga bajando desde lo alto del estadio con un cable. ¿Gaga se inspiró en eso o simplemente Los Simpson lo sabían? | 20th Century Fox, HBOEn el episodio de 2017, "Los Siervson", las payasadas de Homero llevan a que un dragón incinere un pueblo completo. En 2019, dos años después de que ese episodio de Los Simpson saliera al aire, en Game of Thrones (temporada 8, episodio 5) Daenerys y su dragón mataron a miles de personas inocentes con el fuego. | 20th Century Fox, 20th Century Fox/DisneyEn el episodio de 1998, "Cuando se anhela una estrella", un letrero enfrente del estudio de 20th Century Fox revela que es una división de Walt Disney Co lo que no era verdad... en ese momento. En 2017, 19 años después, Disney compró 21st Century Fox. | 20th Century Fox, ABCEn el episodio de 1993, "$pringfield próspero, o el problema del juego", dos magos que actúan en un casino son atacados por un tigre blanco. En 2003, 10 años después de que se transmitió el episodio, Siegfried y Roy fueron atacados por uno de sus tigres blancos.

Title Headline: 23 YA Books We Recommend That Are Specifically Tailored To Your Hogwarts House
Short Description Sub Headline: Consider this the shopping list that comes with every Hogwarts letter.
Content Body: 23 YA Books We Recommend That Are Specifically Tailored To Your Hogwarts House | Consider this the shopping list that comes with every Hogwarts letter. | Posted on March 29, 2020, 00:46 GMT | March 29, 2020, 00:46 GMT | Rachel StrolleBuzzFeed Contributor | Katherine Tegen Books, Via lylaleebooks.comRelease date: Jun. 16, 2020What it's about: Skye Shin has just made it into an internationally televised competition looking for the next K-pop star. Her spectacular voice earns her a spot in the singing portion of the competition, and despite what her mother has told her — that fat girls shouldn't dance, that they shouldn't draw attention to themselves — her incredible moves get her into the dance portion. But her mother isn't the only one whose fat-phobic standards Skye will have to overcome on her quest to become the world's first plus-sized K-pop star. Hufflepuffs will swoon hard over this book, and if you're thinking it's odd that a competition book is being sorted into the house that represents "loyalty," it's because no matter what, Skye always stays true to herself. Get it from Amazon for $17.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Scholastic, Lens of LakhaniRelease date: Oct. 15, 2019What it's about: Nathaniel Fremont, the son of the settlement's tyrannical Commissioner, is determined to earn his father's respect. His plan? Capturing the Technician, who has been supplying black market medical technology to the sick and injured. What Nathaniel doesn't know is that the Technician is Anna Thatcher, a girl with an illegal clockwork heart. And as she attempts to evade capture, an assassin arrives to learn the Commissioner's secrets...at any cost. Slytherins will love this queer steampunk sci-fantasy as much as Draco Malfoy loves namedropping his father. Get it from Amazon for $14.26, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Salaam Reads, Azalia SuhaimiRelease date: Feb. 5, 2019What it's about: Melati Ahmad, a Malaysian 16-year-old, believes there is a djinn inside her. Unless she adheres to a ritual of counting and tapping, she's threatened with images of her mother's death. And in May of 1969, the worst case scenario arrives. Racial tensions in Kuala Lumpur boil over into riots between the Chinese and the Malays, and Melati and her mother are separated. Desperate to track down her mom, Melati can only rely on the strength and courage inside of herself (and a wee bit of help from a Chinese boy named Vincent) to reunite. Gryffindors will be eager to throw this book into the hands of everyone they know — after they cry a little bit. Get it from Amazon for $10.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Sourcebooks Fire, Via linseymiller.comRelease date: Feb. 4, 2020What it's about: Emilie des Marais is a noble lady who would prefer scalpels to embroidery needles. Anette Boucher wants to be trained in magic and gets the offer of a lifetime from a noble...to switch places. Annette attends finishing school as a noble lady to learn the art of divination, and Emelie enrolls to be a physician's assistant. The two must work together, however, when their nation instigates a war — a war based on lies. Ravenclaws will enjoy this magical story featuring two girls who literally go to great lengths to get the schooling they want. Get it from Amazon for $13.34, Barnes and Noble for $16.72, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Little, Brown, Levy Moroshan, Chris ReynoldsRelease date: Jul. 7, 2020What it's about: The last thing Iris (a secret witch) expects on her first day of school is to be taken in by a trio of other witches. Their coven includes soft-spoken Greta, musical Ridley, and fiery Binx...but they aren't the only coven in town. Since junior high, they've had a rivalry with The Triad, a group who uses their spells to punish their exes and break up happy couples for fun. But when someone's anti-witch ideology turns deadly, the two covens may need to band together. Gryffinclaws will love this one — their Ravenclaw side will love the mystery and their Gryffindor side will relate to having friends you'd walk through fire for.Get it from Amazon for $17.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Little, Brown, London ShahRelease date: Oct. 29, 2019What it's about: In the last days of the twenty-first century, London is living underwater. When Leyla McQueen, a 16-year-old submersible racer, gets the chance to participate in the annual marathon, she knows it's her opportunity to save her father, who was arrested on false charges. But during the race, something unexpected occurs, leaving Leyla to defy a corrupt government determined to keep its secrets. Ravenclaws will adore watching optimistic Leyla use logic and determination to work her way through a series of impossible choices.Get it from Amazon for $8.99, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Crown Books, York WilsonRelease date: Jan. 21, 2020What it's about: Ever since phoenix horses were gifted to the Ashlords by their gods, they've raced them. These races evolved into a multi-day event, where elite riders fight to be crowned champion. Not only do the competitors need to be good at riding, they must be skilled at controlling the horses that are made of ash and alchemy. For every sunset, the horses burst into flame and rise from the ashes at sunrise. Racers must also find ways to keep their horses safe, for while murdering a rival's horse is outlawed, other forms of sabotage are not. Fiery Gryffindors will fall headfirst for this series starter as they follow the races through the eyes of a champion's daughter, a scholarship entrant, and a revolutionary's son. Get it from Amazon for $13.99, Barnes and Noble for $16.79, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Katherine Tegen, Via writeinbk.comRelease date: May 21, 2019What it's about: Brooklyn, 1998. After Steph is murdered, his friends Quadir and Jarrell come up with a plan to promote Steph's music. With the help of Steph's sister Jasmine, they create a demo and a new rap persona: the Architect. When that demo catches the ear of a music label rep, they must not only prove Steph's talent but also confront the truth about what really happened to Steph. Slytherins will devour this sublime piece of historical fiction and immediately reach for Jackson's other novels.Get it from Amazon for $12.77, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Razorbill, Via jenniferciacopelli.comRelease date: Feb. 18, 2020What it's about: A year ago, Audrey Lee was recovering from a spine surgery that could have paralyzed her. Now, she's on the United States' gymnastics team with her best friend, Emma, and getting ready for the Olympics. But when horrifying news emerges about one of their coaches, the team faces a new reality...one where they aren't all on the same side. Hufflepuffs will love the friendship between Audrey and Emma and will certainly cry at a few choice moments throughout the book. Get it from Amazon for $15.52, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Viking, Sue GrubmanRelease date: Apr. 21, 2020What it's about: Fitz Holton and Juniper Ramirez meet in Boston, on their first college tour, and they could not have more opposite ideas of the future. Fitz wants to stay close to home, maintaining the ability to care for his single mother as her early-onset Alzheimer's starts stealing her my memory. Juniper cannot wait to leave the zero privacy home that is crowded with five siblings. Fitz is on the college tour because his mother wants him to go, but Juniper planned hers herself against the wishes of her family. Slytherclaws will want to hold tight to the two leads as they meander towards one of their first adulting decisions. Get it from Amazon for $17.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Little, Brown, Via ronnidavis.comRelease date: Nov. 12, 2020What it's about: Last summer, Devon fell in love with a boy named Ashton, only to have him break her heart at the end of the summer. Since then, she's put the pieces back together, but that plan veers off course when Ashton shows up on the first day of senior year. Davis masterfully wraps up a stunning love story and a carefully crafted portrayal of mental illness in a Gryffinpuff package. Get it from Amazon for $17.99, Barnes and Noble for $17.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Simon & Schuster, Carter HasegawaRelease date: Jul. 30, 2019What it's about: Maren is on her way to steal a dragon and rescue her girlfriend. She would have been perfectly happy with a quiet life, but after the Aurati (prophetic agents of the emperor) abducted Kaia, Maren was forced to hatch a plan. To succeed, she must become an apprentice to the mysterious dragon trainer of the emperor, but she's unprepared for the dangerous secrets she uncovers. Time is running out, and Gryffindors will love every heart-pounding second. Get it from Amazon for $9.49, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Skyscape, Via victorialeewrites.comRelease date: Mar. 1, 2019What it's about: Noam Álvaro wakes up in a hospital bed with technopathic abilities, the only survivor of the viral magic that killed his family. He is quickly thrust into the attention of the minister of defense, who offers to teach him the science behind his magic. Noam has spent his life fighting for the rights of refugees fleeing magical outbreaks the nation of Carolinia, so he accepts the ministers offer. After all, he plans to use anything he learns to work against the government. Slytherins will devour Noam's story along with the recently released sequel, The Electric Heir, and then busy themselves reading the Webtoon adaptation. Get it from Amazon for $6.79, Barnes and Noble for $8.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Balzer + Bray, Via abdaddy.comRelease date: Jun. 4, 2019What it's about: For 3 teens in 1989, New York City, the world is changing. Reza, an Iranian boy, just moved to the city with his mother, and while Reza knows he is gay, all he knows of gay life are the media's images of men dying of AIDS. Judy is a plus-size aspiring fashion designer who has never dreamed of finding romance...until she and Reza start dating. Judy's best friend, Art, is the only out and proud teen at their school, who rebels against his conservative parents by documenting the AIDS crisis through photography. Hufflepuffs will tense as Art and Reza grow closer, as you desperately hope none of the wonderful characters get their hearts broken. Get it from Amazon for $8.29, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Margaret K. McElderry, Alice StallcupRelease date: Jun. 4, 2019What it's about: For as long as she has lived, Elisabeth has known one thing: all sorcerers are evil. She dreams of becoming a warden, charged with protecting the kingdom from the power of grimoires — tools of sorcery that rattle beneath chains and transform into beasts of ink and leather if provoked. When the most dangerous grimoire in the library is released during an act of sabotage, she must turn to a sorcerer, Nathaniel Thorn, and his mysterious demonic servant for help. If you are a Ravenclaw who grew up knowing that no gift would ever live up to the Beast gifting Belle the library, this is the book for you. Get it from Amazon for $11.59, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Simon Pulse, Sabreen LakhaniRelease date: Jan. 2, 2018What it's about: Twins Adina and Tovah are about to take a genetic test for Huntington's, the rare degenerative disease that has slowly been turning their Israeli mother into a stranger. Viola prodigy Adina wants to succeed as a soloist and hopes to convince her music teacher that he wants her in the way she wants him. Tovah dreams of becoming a surgeon and awaits an acceptance letter from Johns Hopkins. And when the test results arrive, one twin tests negative. The other tests positive. If you love ambition and emotion, you'll love this Slytherpuff book. Get it from Amazon for $7.99, Barnes and Noble for $11.69, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | HarperTeen, Kerem HanciRelease date: Feb. 18, 2020In case you haven't yet read book one, The Final Six: After erratic climate change renders Earth too dangerous, 24 teens are drafted into the International Space Training Camp in order to determine which six of them will be scouting a new planet. Among the 24 are Leo, an Italian championship swimmer who lost his family, and Naomi, an Iranian-American science genius who is suspicious of the ISTC. What it's about: As a part of the Final Six, Naomi is headed into space, away from Leo and on towards Europa. She is determined to find out if there is alien life there and to discover what happened to the last group of astronauts who attempted their mission. Leo is on Earth, working with a renegade scientist to warn Naomi and the others of what awaits on Europa. Ravenpuffs will crave the reunion of Naomi and Leo and the resolution to the mysteries of what truly lies beyond Earth. Get it from Amazon for $14.19, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Wednesday Books, Traci J BrooksRelease date: Jan. 21, 2020What it's about: Big League Burger just stole a grilled cheese recipe that belonged to Jack's grandmother. While he's always been a bit of a class clown and isn't super sure about his future within his family's deli, he knows he must defend the honor of the legendary grilled cheese...one tweet at a time. On the other side of the Big League Burger's Twitter account is Pepper — swim team captain, perfectionist, annoyed by Jack IRL. As the businesses end up in a viral Twitter war, neither Pepper nor Jack knows that the other is behind the rival account. And in real life, they're falling for each other on an anonymous chat app. Perhaps you are wondering, "Well, it seems like this book is pretty Slytherin, what with the manipulation of social media!" Might I remind you that the characters names are Pepper and Jack and the main conflict centers grilled cheese? 100% Hufflepuff. Get it from Amazon for $13.49, Barnes and Noble for $16.19, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Little, Brown, Becky ForsayethRelease date: Mar. 3, 2020What it's about: Dayna Walsh is focused on ascending and finally becoming a witch. Better to focus on that than on the fact that she was outed as bisexual in her conservative Irish town and is now attempting to cope with somatic OCD. Her focus is interrupted by the arrival of another coven, one that supposedly has a history with black magic, and with them comes Meiner King, the bewitchingly frustrating granddaughter of their coven leader. When a witch turns up murdered with the symbols of an infamous serial killer who was never caught, Dayna and Meiner find themselves at the center of a web of witches and gods. It takes a whole lot of cunning to catch a killer, and Slytherins will delight in the chase. Get it from Amazon for $15.36, Barnes and Noble for $18.76, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Knopf, Louisa WellsRelease date: Oct. 29, 2019What it's about: Simone Garcia-Hampton is at a new school, making sure that the fact that she was born HIV-positive stays under wraps. Starting over seems to be working out for her — making new friends, student directing Rent, and falling for a sweet boy named Miles — until she receives an anonymous note in her locker. If she doesn't break things off with Miles by Thanksgiving, everyone will know her secret. Though her instinct is to protect the information at all cost, she begins to wonder if the only way to rise above is to face the haters head on... Garrett's debut is full of brave choices, honest conversations, and an authenticity that only someone who wrote it while still a teenager could provide. Get it from Amazon for $14.31, Barnes and Noble for $17.09, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Tor Teen, Sasha LedneyRelease date: Feb. 5, 2019What it's about: Brynn Hilder has been recruited by Vale Hall, an elite academy that will provide her a welcome escape from her mom's loser boyfriend. But Vale is not a normal school — students are recruited based on their activities outside of class, such as Brynn's time spent conning rich North Shore kids out of their allowances. The school's mission is to rid the city of corrupt officials, a mission Brynn initially is on board with, but that's before she discovers the headmaster has his own secrets...secrets he'll protect at any cost. Though many of the characters within are certainly Slytherins, it's Ravenclaws who will appreciate piecing together the puzzle that Simmons gives to her readers.Get it from Amazon for $10.99, Barnes and Noble for $10.99, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | Putnam, Via goodreads.comRelease date: May 24, 2016What it's about: Mercy Wong lives in Chinatown in 1906, San Fransisco, and she needs a break. Her best bet is an education at St. Clare's School for Girls — a school she'll have to bribe her way into, since it is off-limits to all but the wealthiest white girls. But getting in was the easy part, since April 18th brings with it a historic earthquake that destroys the school and Mercy's home. As martial law is enacted in the city, Mercy can't sit by while so many are suffering. Slytherdors with an equal dose of cunning and moxie will relate deeply to Mercy and will find a new favorite historical fiction in this book. Get it from Amazon for $7.89, Barnes and Noble for $9.89, or from a local bookstore through Indiebound here. | The Parliament House, Daniel McCookRelease date: Jun. 25, 2019What it's about: In a world full of superheroes, one girl will do whatever it takes...to not get killed. Meg lives in Lunar City, where the near-daily battles between superhumans has led her to adopt a "background citizen" existence. But her entire strategy falls to pieces when she stumbles across the dead body of one of the supers, and his girlfriend coerces her into tracking down who killed him. Non-magical folks will find a kindred spirit in Meg and will be especially delighted by the fact that there is a rat whose name is Trashface. Get it from Amazon for $14.99 or from Barnes and Noble for $17.60.

Title Headline: 17 Easy Cocktails To Make Social Distancing Just A Little Bit More Fun
Short Description Sub Headline: It's not drinking alone. It's social distancing.
Content Body: Food | 17 Easy Cocktails To Make Social Distancing Just A Little Bit More Fun | It's not drinking alone. It's social distancing. | Posted on March 23, 2020, 19:00 GMT | March 23, 2020, 19:00 GMT | Hannah LoewentheilBuzzFeed Staff | Bev Cooks / Via bevcooks.comMade with just five ingredients, a sweet and zesty classic mojito will almost transport you to Havana. Start with muddled mint and sugar, then add fresh lime juice, rum, and a splash of club soda. Get the recipe for classic mojito here. | Sweet Phi / Via sweetphi.comAnother five-ingredient creation, the old fashioned cocktail gets a seasonal twist with the help of hard or soft apple cider and sliced apples for garnish. Get the recipe for apple cider old fashioned cocktail here. | Fork in The Kitchen / Via forkinthekitchen.com, Fork In The Kitchen / Via forkinthekitchen.comFast forward to summertime with this light and fresh sangria, made with rosé, sugar or simple syrup, lemon, strawberry, and mint. You can get creative though and use whatever fruits and herbs are in your kitchen. Get the recipe for strawberry mint sangria here. | Blossom To Stem / Via blossomtostem.netDon't be intimidated by the idea of using egg white in a cocktail. It's actually so simple, and it turns your everyday drink into something that looks and tastes incredibly fancy. Get the recipe for Aperol sour cocktail here. | Cookie and Kate / Via cookieandkate.comThis cocktail might sound intricate and involved, but all you need is bourbon, lemon juice, maple syrup, and a pinch of cinnamon. Get the recipe for cinnamon maple whiskey sour here. | I Am A Food Blog / Via iamafoodblog.comThe classic negroni gets a makeover: Instead of bitter Campari, this version is made with sweet elderflower liqueur. Get the recipe for St. Germain negroni here. | The Sweetest Occasion / Via thesweetestoccasion.comUsing fruit jam in a cocktail recipe is simply genius if you ask us. With just peach jam, fresh peaches, iced tea, and whiskey, you can make a restaurant-quality cocktail at home. Get the recipe for peach whiskey smash cocktail here. | Drinking Hobby / Via drinkinghobby.comThis recipe calls for raspberry syrup, but don't worry if you don't have that. Muddled raspberries and classic simple syrup or agave will do the trick. Get the recipe for clover club cocktail here. | Gimme Some Oven / Via gimmesomeoven.comThe status of the world is basically spring break for everyone so if you're looking for a little something to get your morning going, we've got you covered. Get the recipe for tequila sunrise mimosas here. | Set The Table Blog / Via setthetableblog.comThis sophisticated drink comes together with gin, lemon juice, honey, and egg white. Throw everything into a cocktail shaker and strain into a coupe. Get the recipe for bee's knees cocktail here. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: こりゃ太るけどウマイ。セブンに「フライドポテトのいいとこ取り」が売ってた。
Short Description Sub Headline: セブンで発見したスナック菓子「クリスピーポテト」が最高でした。なんと、見た目が「ギザギザしたフライドポテト」と瓜二つなんです。カリッカリの食感と、バターの風味が罪深い…。セブンさん、美味しいもの作りすぎです。
Content Body: こりゃ太るけどウマイ。セブンに「フライドポテトのいいとこ取り」が売ってた。 | セブンで発見したスナック菓子「クリスピーポテト」が最高でした。なんと、見た目が「ギザギザしたフライドポテト」と瓜二つなんです。カリッカリの食感と、バターの風味が罪深い…。セブンさん、美味しいもの作りすぎです。 | March 29, 2020, 07:00 GMT | March 29, 2020, 07:00 GMT | Tomoya Kosugi小杉 知也 BuzzFeed LIFE Intern, Japan | | | ひるちゃん@hirucham830 | ひるちゃん | @hirucham830 | セブンとカルビーの共同開発のクリスピーポテトほんと美味しすぎて今日4袋ずつ買ってきた😂笑量少ないのにお値段ちょっと高めだけど本当美味しい。田舎のセブンには売ってないけどベニマルに売ってる。 | 返信 | リツイート | お気に入り | びーぷ🎮5/5コミケ4日目 西H33b@BeepboyTokyo | びーぷ🎮5/5コミケ4日目 西H33b | @BeepboyTokyo | おやつテロ承知で書きます。セブンのクリスピーポテト🍟子供の頃に食べた冷凍フライドポストの「ひと皿に1〜2個だけある　油を吸ってカリカリになってる　レアなやつ」だけが袋に入っている状態‼️子供の頃の夢がひとつ叶いました✨ありがとうカルビーありがとう7&I🙇‍♂️ | 返信 | リツイート | お気に入り | こると@koruto_ | こると | @koruto_ | セブンのクリスピーポテトのガーリックバター味がアホみたいにうまい。麻薬 | 返信 | リツイート | お気に入り

Title Headline: 16 Self-Isolating Tips For Parents That've Worked For My Kids So Far
Short Description Sub Headline: Self-isolating + parenting = a lot!
Content Body: Parents | 16 Self-Isolating Tips For Parents That've Worked For My Kids So Far | Self-isolating + parenting = a lot! | Posted on March 25, 2020, 16:15 GMT | March 25, 2020, 16:15 GMT | Mike SpohrBuzzFeed Staff | | | Universal, Warner Bros.My wife and I are ‘80s kids, so we've used self-isolating as an opportunity to show Annie and James some of the classics from childhood. So far we’ve watched the Back to the Future trilogy, The Goonies, Groundhog Day, and Ghostbusters. Seeing the kids enjoy these movies as much as we did as kids has been a blast.The best part of these movie nights, though — from a self-isolating perspective — is that it A) gives the kids something to look forward to all day, B) creates a bit of scheduled normalcy, and C) is family time when we can cuddle and focus on each other.

This stay spray made it through an extremely hot and muggy outdoor wedding, as well a rushed/stressful surprise 18th birthday party/grad party combo. My friend and I were both literally dripping with sweat and yet our makeup looked like we both just applied it. Before I used the spray, my makeup would have been running. Once I used the spray, it stayed looking perfect for 10+ hours." —Rachel L.Price: $17.50+ (originally $25) | TartePromising review: "There's nothing that compares to Tarte's Shape Tape Foundation. Title Headline: Boris Johnson Has Tested Positive For The Coronavirus
Short Description Sub Headline: Health secretary Matt Hancock has also tested positive and chief medical officer Chris Whitty is self-isolating after experiencing symptoms.
Content Body: Boris Johnson Has Tested Positive For The Coronavirus | Health secretary Matt Hancock has also tested positive and chief medical officer Chris Whitty is self-isolating after experiencing symptoms. | Posted on March 27, 2020, 11:17 GMT | March 27, 2020, 11:17 GMT | Alex WickhamPolitical Editor | | Boris Johnson #StayHomeSaveLives@BorisJohnson | Boris Johnson #StayHomeSaveLives | @BorisJohnson | Over the last 24 hours I have developed mild symptoms and tested positive for coronavirus.I am now self-isolating, but I will continue to lead the government’s response via video-conference as we fight this virus.Together we will beat this. #StayHomeSaveLives | Reply | Retweet | Favorite

Title Headline: Survivors Of The AIDS Crisis Are Revealing How We Can Get Through The Coronavirus Pandemic
Short Description Sub Headline: “I had a boyfriend die in front of me. You either go under or you get stronger.” Across two continents and three countries, survivors of the AIDS crisis reveal how to cope now.
Content Body: Survivors Of The AIDS Crisis Are Revealing How We Can Get Through The Coronavirus Pandemic | “I had a boyfriend die in front of me. You either go under or you get stronger.” Across two continents and three countries, survivors of the AIDS crisis reveal how to cope now. | Posted on March 21, 2020, 10:59 GMT | March 21, 2020, 10:59 GMT | Patrick StrudwickBuzzFeed UK LGBT Editor | | Sharon Bosely, Sharon BosleySharon Bosely | Alan SpinkLeft: Alan Spink (left) with his late partner, John, (right) in 1993. Right: Guy-Bray today. | Simon WatneyLeft: Simon Watney in the 1980s. Right: Watney today with his partner, Glyn.

Title Headline: 18 Tweets That Perfectly Encapsulate What Your Forties Are Like
Short Description Sub Headline: Vacuums become a lot more exciting.
Content Body: 18 Tweets That Perfectly Encapsulate What Your Forties Are Like | Vacuums become a lot more exciting. | Posted on March 22, 2020, 20:15 GMT | March 22, 2020, 20:15 GMT | Shelby HeinrichBuzzFeed Staff | Chad Read@squirrel74wkgn | Chad Read | @squirrel74wkgn | This kid working at Footlocker doesn’t seem to understand that I’m in my forties and need a pair of white tennis shoes that’ll last me the next 25 years. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Dumb Beezie@dumbbeezie | Dumb Beezie | @dumbbeezie | Your 20s are for partying with people, your 30s are for actually getting to know them and your 40s are for trying to avoid them altogether | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Bethenny Frankel@Bethenny | Bethenny Frankel | @Bethenny | In your 20s, you wear no makeup, in your 30s you wear some, in your 40s you paint on your face. What happens in 50s? Spackle? | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Sooz@CruisinSoozan | Sooz | @CruisinSoozan | I’ve now entered the floral tunic portion of my forties. Your thoughts and prayers would be appreciated during this loud time. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Jacqueline Bouvier@jackiembouvier | Jacqueline Bouvier | @jackiembouvier | Sex in your 20s: Constant.Sex in your 30s: Occasional.Sex in your 40s: A Unicorn. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Eric Nelson@literaryeric | Eric Nelson | @literaryeric | In your 20s: Boy, am I tired.In your 30s: I can’t believe how tired I am.In your 40s: Now I understand why old people don’t care if they die. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Jawbreaker@sixfootcandy | Jawbreaker | @sixfootcandy | Welcome to your 40s. A new cordless vacuum will excite you now. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | mark@TheCatWhisprer | mark | @TheCatWhisprer | [shopping for clothes]in my 20s: i want to look goodin my 30s: i want to be sensiblein my 40s: i don’t want to feel any fabric pressing into my body anywhere | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Ken Jennings@KenJennings | Ken Jennings | @KenJennings | HOBBIESin my 20s: hiking, paintingin my 30s: board games, travelin my 40s: singing the wrong numbers in the lyrics to "Seasons of Love" from Rent to infuriate my daughter | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | RM@dorsalstream | RM | @dorsalstream | Your 20s: I will strive for goodness and peace in this troubled world.Your 40s: Every single chair is terrible. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Lady Lawya@Parkerlawyer | Lady Lawya | @Parkerlawyer | Your teens: I’ll just sleep on the floor.Your 20s: I’ll just sleep on the futon.Your 30s: I’ll just sleep on the couch.Your 40s: Is this tempurpedic? I can only sleep on tempurpedic. Preferably sleep number 37. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Nonchalant Charlotte@jellybnbonanza | Nonchalant Charlotte | @jellybnbonanza | Being in your 40s means date night includes standing in line at Walgreens for your annual flu shot. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | WineMummy@WineMummy | WineMummy | @WineMummy | The best thing about dating in your 40s:..........Not one fucking thing. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Chucklehouse@Chucklehouse1 | Chucklehouse | @Chucklehouse1 | Dating in your teens: Can't wait to get home so I can fart.Married in your 40s: I don't even care if I shit my pants right now. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | 🌴Sardonic Tart🌴@SardonicTart | 🌴Sardonic Tart🌴 | @SardonicTart | Me in my 20s: I'm not ready to have kids yet.Me in my 40s: I wish I had my kids when I was a teenager. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Stephen_With_A_Ph@with_a_ph23 | Stephen_With_A_Ph | @with_a_ph23 | Hangovers in your 20s: I’d better drink a Bloody Mary.Hangovers in your 30s: I’d better sleep in.Hangovers in your 40s: I’d better make funeral arrangements. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Divergent Mama@Divergentmama | Divergent Mama | @Divergentmama | Welcome to your 40s - you now think every car has its brights on. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Evel@FeverFlave | Evel | @FeverFlave | Welcome to your 40s. You are no longer the target audience for anything cool. | Reply | Retweet | Favorite

Content Body: Shopping | 16 Things To Do Now That You Can't Watch Your Favorite Sports | Please, I just need to see a ball (any ball) score a point, goal, or run. | Posted on March 24, 2020, 20:01 GMT | March 24, 2020, 20:01 GMT | John MihalyBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | | | Sony, XboxAs always, a new Major League Baseball season brings with it new video games (even when that season is postponed). Play out that entire162 game schedule with either MLB The Show 20 for PS4 ($59.99) or RBI Baseball 20 for Xbox ($29.99). | WalmartSince anything more than two-on-two is considered a gathering (and a really bad idea) you're going to have to take your game inside. Play some one-on-none with the Pro Mini Basketball Hoop ($24.99) and take a break from WFH to work on that long-distance jumper. Title Headline: 27 Things To Have If You Wanna Look, Smell, And Feel Like A Grownup
Short Description Sub Headline: 🎶 "Man. I feel like a grownup." —You, remixing Shania Twain after snagging these goodies.
Content Body: Shopping | 27 Things To Have If You Wanna Look, Smell, And Feel Like A Grownup | 🎶 "Man. I feel like a grownup." —You, remixing Shania Twain after snagging these goodies. | Posted on March 15, 2020, 02:00 GMT | March 15, 2020, 02:00 GMT | Marquaysa BattleBuzzFeed Staff | | | | amazon.comPromising review: "I initially bought this to clean red wine out of fabrics that cannot be cleaned but did so with trepidation because I've tried other products that have only made things worse. Anyway, I didn't have to wait long to test out Wine Away's effectiveness as the first red wine spill happened a couple of weeks later on my wife's brand new, super expensive runner which we weren't supposed to be drinking anywhere near and, of course, is brilliant white. At this point, I had already given up all hope of covering up my tracks but figured I might as well try Wine Away as my last-ditch 'maybe I won't have to sleep on the couch' effort. To my amazement, upon spraying Wine Away on the stain, it immediately cleared up and left no residue or dullness behind. Honestly, I even called my wife in, told her what happened, and had her search for where the stain was and she couldn't find it. Simply amazing stuff. I am now a believer in Wine Away and have used it on not only wine spills but also pet stains on various fabrics and it's always stepped up to the challenge." —DerekGet it from Amazon for $6.67. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "These little guys work perfectly for dermaplaning! I used one the other night after I washed and applied toner to my face. It’s been a couple of days and my skin still feels baby soft. I didn’t have any sort of reaction or anything to the exfoliation which was nice because I have severe cystic acne. My makeup goes on so smoothly and I finally have that glowing look I’ve been trying to get! I will definitely be buying these again." —Hannah JeanGet the set of three from Amazon for $4.99+ (available in a three-pack and nine-pack). | NordstromNew boots, who dis?Promising review: "I literally wear them everywhere I go. It’s like, what was I doing before I owned these???? I wear socks with them and I honestly find them so comfortable. I’m ordering in more colors because they’re just so perfect." —YGC!1Get them from Nordstrom for $59.95 (available in sizes 6-10; five colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Loved it, wish had more boob support too but it could have been much worse! It was tight enough to give some support, quality material, and covered in all the right places. Very satisfied!! Much better quality and fit than more expensive suits that I've bought at popular brick and mortar retail stores!!" —KatieGet it from Amazon for $16.99+ (available in sizes S–1X and four colors). | Amazon, amazon.comThe spikes will feed each plant for up to two months. Promising review: "I have several houseplants that had stopped flowering so I put a few of these spikes in the pot. There are directions on the back of package for quantity and approximately a month after using these spikes, my peace lily had three flowers on it! My African violets plants all got several blooms on them! This worked wonders for my plants that don't flower also. I noticed that my ivy and cactus plants started growing faster and they became more green and healthy-looking. I am very happy with this product and I will buy it again." —ElizabethGet it from Amazon for $2.24 (available in a pack of 48). | AmazonAside from these bowls being gorg, they're also airtight, and dishwasher- and microwave-safe so you can tote your food without fear of it spilling. Peep what BuzzFeed writer Rachel Dunkel thinks of these bowls:"I use my Porter Bowl basically every time I bring my lunch to work. The lid vacuum seals tightly, and I've never had a problem with leaks. It's both microwavable and dishwasher-safe which is obviously a huge win in my book. And it just feels nice to eat lunch out of a real piece of dishware, rather than flimsy plastic. I have the ceramic version and haven't had any problems with scratching. It's rubber coated, so it's easy to travel with and doesn't slide around. I would personally like more as gifts, please!"Get them from Amazon for $25+ (available in ceramic or plastic and in 10 colors). | AmazonPromising review: "I got the pink chair. It is exactly like the site images. It is so comfortable and looks expensive! I was looking into buying a similar chair from a retail store that is three times more expensive but this one is such a great value and high quality." —M. ZacariasGet it from Amazon for $99.99 or two for $189.99 (available in six colors). | elf, BuzzFeed / Marquaysa BattleAlso: The brand is cruelty-free! Yay!Get it from e.l.f. for $8 (available in two color combos). | amazon.com, amazon.comIt'll also remove lint and dander. Plus, it'll be easy to clean since the roller traps the particles in a compartment that you can open up and dump out. The reusability makes it pretty ideal and you won't have to worry about running out of stickies as you would with a traditional lint roller. Promising review: "I have searched and searched for a pet hair remover for my furniture that actually works — this is it. It removes all the hair quickly and fully and self cleans. It is so much easier than the disposable rollers — not to mention cheaper and more environmentally friendly. I have ditched those altogether. I’m buying two more for other rooms in my house. Amazing success!!!" —Sophia P.Get it from Amazon for $24.95. | Olive and JunePromising review: "I love doing my own manicures but had to stop due to issues with mobility in my hands and fingers making it too difficult to hold onto the brushes. This little Poppy lets me get a good grip. So I can do my mains the exact way I like them!" —Melissa D.Get it from Olive and June for $16 (available in white or pink) | Amazon, amazon.comOne reviewer used the desk pad as a mat for a makeup vanity which is SUPER smart since it can prevent beauty products from staining lighter surfaces.Promising review: "This is a super simple but elegant addition to my desk. I purchased the pink one and it contrasts nicely with my dark espresso wooden desk. The mouse moves easy and steady on the surface and has made it much easier to write on my desk. Since the desk is wooden, it's collected small imperfections over the years, making writing on the desk sometimes difficult. I would definitely recommend for new or old desks. New to prevent nicks and dents, and for the old ones to cover them up. 🙂" —DeleahGet it from Amazon for $13.99+ (available in three sizes and nine colors). | amazon.comPromising review: "I rarely ever leave reviews, but THIS is amazing!! I have naturally frizzy hair that is also wavy and curly. I have a lot of breakage around the crown and this stuff sleeks it back but it doesn’t make it look greasy or crunchy! I suggest taking the mascara wand and wiping off the excess on the tube before applying so you don’t apply too much. When I apply too much all you have to do is let it dry and then scratch your fingernails from front to back to break it up and it still creates a sleek look without any crunchiness. I love this stuff so much I need to get another for my car on those days that my mom hair is looking terrible." —AdrianaGet it from Amazon for $7.98. | AmazonPromising review: "This chair is dazzling to the eyes. It goes well in my upscale office space. It's also fairly comfortable and more than I expected for the price. I love it!" —Best realtor everGet it from Novogratz on Amazon for $119.12 (available with free shipping). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Marquaysa Battle / BuzzFeed, Myro / Via mymyro.comPick your case. Pick your scent. Then, select your plan based on whether you want a one-time purchase or regular refill plan. Myro deodorants are cruelty-free but there's so much more to it than that. They're also aluminum-, paraben-, phthalate- and talc-free. Plus, they don't use baking soda, artificial colors, or synthetic fragrances which are known to be skin irritants. Tbh, I wasn't looking for environmentally friendly deodorant although I swear I love Mother Earth. My go-to fragrance-free deodorant was discontinued so I just desperately needed one that wouldn't irritate my sensitive underarm skin and would keep me smelling fresh. All the other natural deodorants I tried DEFINITELY DID NOT KEEP ME FRESH 🙅🏿‍♀️. I had to re-up several times throughout the day just to avoid a sweaty smell which wasn't my norm and made me feel self-conscious. Finally, I stumbled upon the Myro deodorant and figured I'd just try it since I tried everything else (Native, Tom's, Almay, you name it). I was skeptical because it smelled so good and my severely sensitive skin typically doesn't play nice with scents. I guess since the product is truly natural, that's why it didn't irritate me. Fair warning: I peeped that the deodorant has low ratings on like two sites but it appears that the Myro brand listened to the people, as its website notes that it's upgraded the formula. I've been using it for about three weeks. I apply it once daily and don't have to break my schedule to re-up, haven't had any itchy patches develop under my arms, and FINALLY get to enjoy a great scented product again, which I haven't been able to do in years. BTW, the scent I have is the Chill Wave which smells like cucumber, jasmine, and spearmint 👃🏾❤️.Get the actual deodorant from Myro for $10 (available in seven scents) and the case for FREE (refill for $10 (available in seven colors). Personalize your case for $6 more. | GlossierPromising review: "I didn’t know how much I needed this product. I could never achieve the brow look I wanted until I got my first boy brow. It’s super easy to use and gives brows a groomed but natural look." —Ella M.Get it from Glossier for $16 (available in four shades including clear). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "OK, so I'm really digging this trend as of right now so I decided to get these because boutiques are selling them for $30 and these are $8. So, like, no brainer, am I right?? I love them. I feel confident that they aren't going to break every time I put them in as the pearls are woven together. I've worn them a couple of times now and love them. It's the easiest way to cover up the desperate need to wash your hair or make it look like you've actually tried." —Taylor GreenGet them from Amazon for $5.99 (available in a pack of four). | amazon.comThe barrel is designed to protect your fingers from getting burned so you enjoy an ouchless curling sesh. It also has an auto-shutoff feature and even a feature that pauses the iron if you put too much hair into the chamber to curl at once. Promising review: "Love it!! I have fine textured hair — very straight hair. I have trouble not only curling it, but keeping it curled. For example, the other day I left rollers in my hair for 45 minutes and got a minor wave that fell out in 10 minutes. This tool is easy and fast to use, adds shine, and the curl stays." —AlexandriaGet it from Amazon for $74.99+ (available in three colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I wear an 8 but ordered a half-size down because of suggestions from other customers. The 7.5 I ordered fits lovely! They are nice and snug and comfortable on my flat feet! I ordered three different pairs." —Alexis BecksGet them from Amazon for $28.84+ (available in sizes 5.5-11 and 70!!! color/style combinations).

Title Headline: 30 Subscription Boxes That Are So Fun, You Just May Forget You’re Stuck Inside
Short Description Sub Headline: If you're bored and stuck inside, boy do I have a subscription box (or two) for you.
Content Body: Shopping | 30 Subscription Boxes That Are So Fun, You Just May Forget You’re Stuck Inside | If you're bored and stuck inside, boy do I have a subscription box (or two) for you. | Posted on March 27, 2020, 14:00 GMT | March 27, 2020, 14:00 GMT | Harper HendricksonBuzzFeed Staff | | Book Of The Month, Book of the MonthWhat you get: BOTM searches through hundreds of new releases each month and picks out the top five new reads for you to choose from! You can also skip months if you're still working on your latest read. Promising review: "WOW! I absolutely love Book of The Month Club! Discounted best sellers with the option to skip some months? Count me in! Thanks to BOTM I have encountered some wonderful novels from new authors that I will be sure to add to my collection forever." ⁠—Chellie R.Get it from Book of The Month club starting at $9.99/month. | | CratejoyWhat you get: You'll get a box of pre-measured, vacuum-sealed, gourmet, handcrafted ingredients to create your own gourmet cookies just like you'd find at the bakery, plus cookie-themed gifts and surprises!Promising review: "OH MY GOSH! What a fantastic box. We got this for our son's 20th birthday and they worked with me to get it here earlier than their normal shipping schedule to allow us to give it to him on time. They even included a gift note AND our birthday note to him beautifully written and decorated. This box is packed full of fun/themed items on top of the tasty recipe and all the dry ingredients needed to make it. They even sent the wearable appropriately sized for a guy, which was AMAZING! I am so glad I chose this bakery box!!! And, most importantly, our son LOVED it. Thank you so much for this awesome box, Fresh Baked Cookie Company." —Michele D.Get it from Cratejoy for $20/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: Each month you'll receive a box packed with three to five pieces of quality apparatus, plus bonus tricks online, unique tricks and routines, info on the history of magic and magicians, and secret links to performance and tutorial videos presented by world-renowned magicians!Promising review: "These boxes of magic are carefully considered and thought out. The packaging is beautiful. The magic is stunning (so much so that I have used some of the pieces in my professional act) and the creativity is overflowing. These boxes are for kids. These boxes are for adults. The magic is STRONG. The ideas are brilliant. I just love, love, love these boxes! They are perfect as a gift for someone that is interested in magic or for the pro that wants to have a shot of creativity injected into their arsenal of magic." —Jonathan L. Get it from Cratejoy for $32.08/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: This box includes a live succulent friend (or two depending on your size subscription!), cute planters, the right potting mix, hand-illustrated care info, and everything else you need to be a successful plant parent each month!Promising review: "We gave this as a gift to my mother-in-law and I am just blown away by the quality of this subscription. The attention to detail is amazing. It's a terrific value for the dollar. I am a regular subscriber on Cratejoy and this subscription is as good as it gets! Thank you!" —Dana W.Get it from Cratejoy for $17.41/month+. | CratejoyWhat you get: You'll get high-quality training gear, lifting accessories, work out apparel, recovery aids (massage tools and hydration supplements), high-protein snacks, and everything else you'll need to crush your next workout! Promising review: "Purchasing this box for my fiancé was a great idea. Not only are the shirts super soft and comfy, and the snacks are also delicious. The products are awesome — the shaker bottle was an instant hit and is really easy to clean. The Doc Spartan combat-ready ointment smells great, the wod welder odor crusher really works! Honestly, every item that has arrived at our doorstep has been a huge hit, makes a great present." —Madison G.Get it from Cratejoy for $33/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: A new fearless female role model each month, a 20-page Girls Can activity book featuring a woman's story, games, experiments, and more; two to three hands-on activities per box, and creative play props. Promising review: "I can't begin to tell you the quality of the items in this box. They teach us historical events, geography, math, science experiments, and ways to encourage our girls to achieve by boosting their confidence through knowledge. You need a whole month to dive into all the materials they included in the workbook. My granddaughters were inspired to create and learn and so was I, I will be a long term Girls Can Crate subscriber." —LynnGet it from Cratejoy for $18.50+/month (available in three sizes). | CrateJoyWhat you get: You'll receive a monthly box filled with things like arts and crafts supplies, a growing project with seeds, cooking activities, stickers, veggie-themed toys, and more!Promising review: "We love veggie buds! My son looks forward to their monthly box in the mail. There are games, recipes, crafts, seeds to plant, and more! We love the books that come with it too. Content Body: Music | BTS Are Releasing "Learn Korean With BTS" Videos To Help Fans Study And 7 Other Pieces Of K-Pop News You Should Know | Plus a bunch of new music to help you cope with the state of the world. | Posted on March 27, 2020, 18:16 GMT | March 27, 2020, 18:16 GMT | Sarah HanBuzzFeed Staff | Emlyn TravisBuzzFeed Staff | Chung Sung-jun / Getty Images, Hannah Foslien / Getty ImagesA star-studded lineup of celebs will be playing games and performing live, including Joe Jonas, Lauv, Charlie Puth, Jordin Sparks, and Aly Raisman.Viewers can donate during the stream or create a "supporting campaign" on Twitch's donation page, or you can also co-stream the Stream Aid on your own Twitch channel. All proceeds will go to the COVID-19 Solidarity Response Fund for WHO, and this stream kicks off a whole week's worth of fundraising opportunities on Twitch. Stay tuned, literally! And if you can donate (while watching your faves perform), please do! 💸 | | Big Hit EntertainmentThe videos feature clips of BTS saying frequently used expressions, like their introductions or "How have you been?", so you'll be talking as eloquently as RM in no time at all. That's how this works, right? You can watch the first three episodes of "Learn Korean with BTS" on Weverse (you can make an account for free!) right now, and stay tuned for the rest! P.S. According to a press release, Professor Heo Yong (Department of Korean Education at Hankuk University of Foreign Studies) and researchers at the Korea Language Contents Institute (KOLCI) all helped in developing this easy-to-follow ~curriculum~. Time to study up!And! Title Headline: 25 Things That'll Make Working From Home Suck A Whole Lot Less
Short Description Sub Headline: Coffee machines, indoor gardens, meditation headbands, and more!
Content Body: Shopping | 25 Things That'll Make Working From Home Suck A Whole Lot Less | Coffee machines, indoor gardens, meditation headbands, and more! | Posted on March 16, 2020, 16:45 GMT | March 16, 2020, 16:45 GMT | Victoria KuglinBuzzFeed Staff | | | | Amazon / Via amazon.caWith these, you can listen to your tunes for more than 30 hours on a single charge. And with a handy control knob, you can adjust the volume, skip tracks, and even take calls on the go.Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $91.03+ (available in nine colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caSetup is super easy, so you can go from unboxing to listening in minutes. It has built-in voice control, and works with Alexa, or you can also use the Sonos app or Apple Airplay to go completely hands-free. It can even pair with other speakers for a richer, more immersive sound. Get it on Amazon Canada for $247.77+ (available in two colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caEucalyptus is naturally antiseptic and antibacterial, and can be used to help with a number of sinus and respiratory conditions. It also makes a great yoga mat spray!Get it on Amazon Canada for $14.99+ (available in ten scents). | Amazon / Via amazon.caThe headband also connects to the Muse app, so tracking meditations and brain activity is super easy. Over time, you'll be able to see when your brain is tired, angry, or frustrated, and when you're feeling relaxed, happy, and content, and it'll be a lot easier to navigate your way back to a happier state!Get it on Amazon Canada for $237.36+ (available in two colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caThese 100% cotton joggers look great with a cropped sweater, and can take you from couch to coffee meeting in less time than it takes to say, "They're machine washable, too?"Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $24.23+ (available in five colours and in sizes S-3XL). | @everlasting_comfort / Via instagram.com, @everlasting_comfort / Via instagram.comUse it in your home office to help with things like sciatica, tailbone pain, and posture correction. Or take it with you to the next sporting event, camping trip, or picnic! With over 1,000 five-star reviews, this is one purchase you'll be comfortable with.Get it on Amazon Canada for $39.95. | @levoitlifestyle / Via instagram.com, @levoitlifestyle / Via instagram.comIt also has three fan speeds, so you know it's strong enough to address even the nastiest air conditions. It's also available in a compact size.Get it on Amazon Canada for $101.99 (available in two colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caTouch anywhere on the base to activate the lamp, adjust brightness, or cycle through the colours. You can also get a mini version here!Get it on Amazon Canada for $37.99. | @discovervibes / Via instagram.com, @discovervibes / Via instagram.comUnlike traditional earplugs, these ones still allow you to hear certain frequencies (like a ringing phone), so you won't be totally isolated. They're also great for parents of newborns, or for those with noise sensitivity. Each set comes with three interchangeable tips (small, medium, and large), so you know you'll get a perfect fit. Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $37.95. | Amazon / Via amazon.caThey can't guarantee that you'll get paid overtime, but the spring hinges and funky colours make them ultra comfortable and hella cute.Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $19.99+ (available in ten colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caIts sleek, tablet-like design is unobtrusive and versatile enough to pair with any decor style. Reviewers love its sunshine-y brightness that's powerful enough to deliver a hefty dose of vitamin D.Get it on Amazon Canada for $59.95. | Amazon / Via amazon.caThey're tough, versatile, and can be combined for bigger jobs. *Cut to me wrapping everything in my house in these*Get a multi-coloured pack of 50 on Amazon Canada for $11.89 (also available in black). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: Twitterで大絶賛も納得の味。サバを70%使用した“おさかなチップス”が感動の美味しさでした！
Short Description Sub Headline: ファミマで発見した「あじげん サバチ」に感動しました。サバを70%も使用したチップスで、臭みやえぐみが一切ないんです。鼻に抜ける香りはまるで「塩焼きサバ」のよう。
Content Body: Twitterで大絶賛も納得の味。サバを70%使用した“おさかなチップス”が感動の美味しさでした！ | ファミマで発見した「あじげん サバチ」に感動しました。サバを70%も使用したチップスで、臭みやえぐみが一切ないんです。鼻に抜ける香りはまるで「塩焼きサバ」のよう。 | March 25, 2020, 10:31 GMT | March 25, 2020, 10:31 GMT | Tomoya Kosugi小杉 知也 BuzzFeed LIFE Intern, Japan | | | ルーク@STARDY@Stardy_luke | ルーク@STARDY | @Stardy_luke | まじでこの世の全てのサバ好きに教えてあげたいんだが、ファミマには全ての人間を虜にする禁断のサバチがある。これうま味調味料無使用にも関わらず超絶美味しいので全国のサバ好き、サバを愛する者たち、サバを憎む者たち、あとげんげんに伝われ！ | 返信 | リツイート | お気に入り | ことりビスケット@koguma_tourism | ことりビスケット | @koguma_tourism | ふっと初めて買ったこのおやつ。｢サバチ(さばチップス)｣めちゃめちゃ美味しくて思わず叫んだ！うっまーーい！！！油っぽくなくさっぱりしてて。お酒のおつまみにもきっといいと思います🍺香川県で作ってるみたい。いやぁ～びっくりした。帰りにもう一袋買って帰ろう。いや、あと3袋…買うかも | 返信 | リツイート | お気に入り | おすぎ@81_anko | おすぎ | @81_anko | サバチ美味しくって感動してるやめられないとまらないヽ(ﾟ∀｡)ﾉ | 返信 | リツイート | お気に入り

Title Headline: 21 Incredibly Useful Gadgets Under $50
Short Description Sub Headline: Want to feel old? The Spy Kids now source their gadgets from my posts.
Content Body: Shopping | | Under $50 | 21 Incredibly Useful Gadgets Under $50 | Want to feel old? The Spy Kids now source their gadgets from my posts. | Posted on March 19, 2020, 10:00 GMT | March 19, 2020, 10:00 GMT | Colin GorensteinBuzzFeed Staff | | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Natalie Brown / BuzzFeedPromising reviews: "Holy crap I love this thing. It’s freakin' awesome. Best $13 I ever spent, and my grout is white again. Even around the toilet...where the man I married can’t figure out how to pee. I used this thing as soon as I got it from my mailbox...and wow. I love it. You’re stupid not to buy it. I’m buying another one for my mom. I’d buy you one if I could. Just get it." —Rebecca LynnGet it from Amazon for $15.99. | | Amazon, amazon.comThe kit includes the whitening light, mouth guard, and two gel syringes with enough product for 20 whitening sessions. You can also get gel refills to keep your pearly whites pearly for good!Promising review: "I won’t lie, I didn’t notice a huge difference after the first use, BUT my teeth were noticeably whiter after the third use and have continued to get whiter with every use since then. This is the only whitening product that has worked for me, and I will definitely continue to use it." —TomGet it from Amazon for $47.95. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF amazon.com, amazon.comYou charge up the wand with a USB, put your brush in the wand, and choose one of three different speeds to spin it clean in a pretty little glass bowl. One reviewer suggested picking up a second glass bowl from a dollar store to use for rinsing after you clean — seems like a smart idea to me. Promising review: "When I use liquid foundation and get the brushes REALLY dirty, I have to scrub them down before I wash them, but the machine gets them cleaner than I could after. The most important thing is that it DRIES them ASAP. I don't mind washing my brushes (but still, who wants to?), but I don't want damp or even wet brushes that I can't use — this solves that problem! The speed variability makes it so all my brushes are perfect! Never blown out. All of my brushes worked in this, even the ones that I thought would not — the ones that have diamond-shaped or flat-shaped handles or ones where the brush head is oddly shaped or asymmetrical. Keeping your brushes clean means having cleaner skin and more sanitary cosmetics." —LGet it from Amazon for $49.99. | AmazonPromising review: "These work amazingly well. I was surprised that you can charge and use them at the same time. I use them on planes to listen to the in-flight entertainment with my AirPods. I also use them to listen to music on my laptop with my AirPods. They work really well. Now, I don't have to carry my wired earbuds with me when I travel anymore. They really work as advertised. I have not had any issues with them since I started using them." —RPLGet it from Amazon for $39.99+ (available in three options).
