Title Headline: 36 Beauty Products You'll Probably Pat Yourself On The Back For Buying
Short Description Sub Headline: I support your decision to treat yourself to yet another lipstick you probably don't need but deserve.
Content Body: Shopping | | Beauty | 36 Beauty Products You'll Probably Pat Yourself On The Back For Buying | I support your decision to treat yourself to yet another lipstick you probably don't need but deserve. | Posted on March 15, 2020, 12:01 GMT | March 15, 2020, 12:01 GMT | Heather BragaBuzzFeed Staff | | elfcosmetics / Via instagram.com, elfcosmetics / Via instagram.comThis concealer is made with a highly pigmented formula that still dries matte, feels lightweight, and won't settle into fine lines or creases.Get it from e.l.f. Cosmetics for $6 (available in 26 shades). | | amazon.comPromising review: "I rarely ever leave reviews, but THIS is amazing!! I have naturally frizzy hair that is also wavy and curly. I have a lot of breakage around the crown and this stuff sleeks it back but it doesn’t make it look greasy or crunchy! I suggest taking the mascara wand and wiping off the excess on the tube before applying so you don’t apply too much. When I apply too much all you have to do is let it dry and then scratch you’re fingernails from front to back to break it up and it still creates a sleek look without any crunchiness. I love this stuff so much I need to get another for my car on those days that my mom hair is looking terrible." —AdrianaGet it from Amazon for $7.99. | Amazon, amazon.comAvarelle's pimple patches are formulated with tea tree oil and calendula, which is said to heal and shrink zits overnight. A single pack comes with 40 patches in a variety of sizes to fit any pimple you've got.Promising review: "I’ve tried so many brands of pimple spots, and these are hands-down the best on the market. I’m a performer at Walt Disney World, and a clear complexion is required. Last night, I put these on a few acne problems (a small cyst, a whitehead, and a pimple I shouldn’t have picked and has been a bump for about three weeks now.) I just woke up and am writing this review in disbelief. THEY'RE FLAT! Gone! All of them! I could cry I’m so happy. The packaging is also ideal, because it allows you to conveniently and easily peel the stickers off without stretching them out or folding them back on themselves. Do yourself and your complexion a huge favor! Have these on hand for a stubborn zit when you really need help. Make sure you apply them to completely clean and dry skin." —CaitlynGet it from Amazon for $8.50. | GlossierMy coworker AnaMaria Glavan is passionate about this product. Here's what she had to say:"Believe the hype: this magic bottle is proof that not all heroes wear capes. The creamy formula, which comes in blond, black, clear, and brown (which is what I used!), goes on smoothly and doesn’t require a lot of product to do the job. I used the wand to brush baby hairs in the beginning/middle of my brow upwards, and then brushed the longer, toddler-like hairs at the end of my eyebrows, sideways. And one coat was more than enough! Boy Brow does what exactly what the Glossier brand claims to do; it gives me a filled-in eyebrow that doesn’t look filled in. The finish looks natural, which is exactly what I wanted — my facial caterpillars have never looked better."Get it from Glossier for $16 (available in four shades). | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I absolutely LOVE this mascara. I have very sensitive eyes and am highly devoted to my trusted brands. When a friend suggested this mascara I was curious, as she loved it. For the price point and how good it looked on her eyes, I thought why not. Holy moly. I'm in love. It makes my lashes longer, — looks like I'm natural but better — and has a thinner formula so it looks like I have a billion gorgeous lashes, and looks the same all day long. I cannot recommend this enough. It doesn't rub during the day and give me that black eye look. It's wonderful. Must buy." —Katherine OchsmanGet it from Amazon for $12.95. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "My hair is very thin and curly. The ends are damaged from heat and color, causing my hair to look even more unruly. I do oil treatments once a week and only wash my hair two to three times a week but NOTHING has made my hair feel like this product does. There is an immediate difference as soon as this product touches my hair. It leaves my hair feeling so silky, even after I rinse it out and dry my hair." —Maegan W.Get it from Amazon for $12.95. | TartePromising review: "Best concealer till time!! Just love the consistency. Can be worn without powder to give a more dewy look! Love the travel size. Medium to high coverage! Would definitely recommend!" —Mehwish K.Get it from Tarte for $10 (available in 30 shades). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "These masks are amazing!!! Having 'ice pick' scars left over from acne I was told that I'd have to pay for expensive laser therapy because the body can't produce enough collagen to heal deep scars. I've been using these masks for two months and I've seen SIGNIFICANT reduction in my scars. They are almost completely gone!" —ShaunRead our full review of the Dermal Korea collagen sheet masks!Get them from Amazon for $9.99. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "I was lucky enough to have clear skin in high school so I never understood how awful acne really is. When I was about 21-22 years old, I switched to a birth control implant, and that thing wreaked havoc on my entire life. I suddenly had horrible cystic acne. Not only did it make me self conscious and uncomfortable, but it was actually so painful — laying on my pillow hurt my face! To top it all off, my skin was also dry, and irritated. I tried every skincare line on the market for about two to three years, with no, or very little, results. Finally, I found La Roche-Posay's skincare products. Within four days, the inflammation decreased, the redness was fading, and my skin felt less dry. By two weeks, my skin was practically clear! I have been using this product for about four to five years now, and I haven't had a single outbreak, EXCEPT for the time I wanted to try a different product to save money. Huge mistake, one I will not make again." —LadyHawkeGet it from Amazon for $14.99. | Thrive CausemeticsFor every product purchased Thrive Causemetics donates to help a woman *thrive*.Promising review: "This is honestly the best product. I use it on my eyes and lips and cheeks and it literally doesn't budge as eyeshadow. By the end of a 14-hour day it's still bright and beautiful. I mean it LASTS. I haven't found an eyeshadow that isn't gone by the end of the day or smudge. And it gives a beautiful glow to cheeks. WORTH IT!!" —Marcella C.Get it from Thrive Causemetics for $36 (available in four shades). | Kylie CosmeticsEven as a 27 year old, I own more than my fair share of Kylie Cosmetics. I'm talkin' lip kits and palettes for DAYS. Why you ask? Because Kylie Jenner makes a damn good product. Her packaging is among my favorite across all beauty brands and I love that she continues to reinvent the bottles, brushes, and boxes!Promising review: "This is my favorite gloss! I buy several high-end brands and this high gloss takes the cake! It even has the scent of cake! I’ve put it on and it keeps my lips hydrated all day! It’s not sticky like other brands tend to be. This was my first Kylie Cosmetics purchase and I’m extremely satisfied. I’m over 40 and thought, 'Is this even going to look good on me?' The answer is YES." —DebbieGet it from Kylie Cosmetics for $16. | Olive and JuneI've been doing my own nails for a long, long time. It always seemed smarter to me to spend money on a bottle of polish I can keep instead of a manicure that only lasts a week. It's a skill that took a while to work on but, luckily, for at-home manicurists like myself The Poppy has made doing my nails a lot less challenging. It pops right onto any bottle of nail polish (not just Olive and June colors) and provides you with a stronger grip and a more accurate swipe.Get it from Olive and June or Target for $16. | Amazon, amazon.comI have one of these babies and it really is wonderful. Not only does it make me feel like I'm really getting in there while I'm washing my hair, but it also recreates that feeling you get when your hairdresser massages your head while washing it. Ugh, so good.Promising review: "Love this product! About five days before I received it I dyed my hair at home. As some of you may know who do the same, it’s difficult to get the hair dye out of your scalp. I scrubbed my hair for days with my fingers and it seemed like everything was gone because the water ran clear. When I received the product I was excited so I am immediately jumped in the shower to use it. To my surprise a ton of hair dye that was stuck on my head came off. Not only that, but my scalp feels breathable and clean. Definitely not greasy 24 hours later like regular shampooing would do for me. I would recommend this product." —Lisa AgroGet it from Amazon for $7.98+ (available in three colors). | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I have never felt more compelled to write a product review before. This stuff is INCREDIBLE. I have tried almost everything to improve my skin. I continue to get acne in my mid-30s and literally everything else I've tried has not worked, including prescription topical cream and oral medication. This has saved my skin! I have had very few breakouts, and if anything pops up, this takes care of it quickly! My skin feels moisturized and looks smoother and healthier overall. This is truly one of the best purchases I've ever made. I'm thankful I stumbled upon this serum!" —J.C. DentonGet it from Amazon for $14.95. | oliveandjune / Via instagram.com, Olive & JuneI recently tried Olive and June's nail polish and was quite impressed. It went on very smoothly and didn't chip even after a week! I love how these colors will brighten up my nails for spring and summer (the mint is already calling my name!). This brand is also proudly 7-free, which means it doesn't contain harmful chemicals that most polishes do.Get it from Olive & June for $56. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "These eye masks are absolutely amazing! I have hereditary dark circles under my eyes, as well as slight bags from being a mother of four. Eye creams do absolutely nothing for me, and I gave these a try just on a whim, not really expecting much. But they really work! The results aren't permanent, but I put these on for about an hour in the evening while I relax and watch TV, and my under-eyes are much lighter and less puffy. I absolutely love these eye masks, and I will never be without them again." —Kate JohnsonGet a pack of 12 pairs from Amazon for $23.50. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer / BuzzFeedPromising review: "This hot air brush has made the biggest difference in my usually flat, frizzy hair! I now have more body and shine than I have had in years! I highly recommend this product. It is lightweight and easy to use. My hair holds a style longer and it is so much easier than trying to blow dry my hair while also using a round brush trying to style it. I wish I would’ve discovered this hot air brush years ago! Love it!" —LRead our full review of the John Freida Hot Brush for more info!Get it from Amazon for $39.99+ (available in 1 and 1.5-inch versions). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "A must have in my makeup case! I have used plastic lash combs, metal ones, and flat ones, all of which just didn’t get the job done. I always went back to a safety pin, WHICH I DO NOT ADVISE! This comb is metal and arched, which is much easier to use, and the teeth glide through lashes easily. NOTE: If your mascara is dry and clumped, ANY COMB COULD POTENTIALLY PULL OUT LASHES. JUST NO. DO NOT DO IT. I put on mascara, and while it’s still wet, I glide the comb through the base and go up. It’s that simple. I was concerned about cleaning it with alcohol, but I asked customer service and was told it was safe." —ASConnerGet it from Amazon for $7.99. | Loops Beauty / Via instagram.com, Loops BeautyI recently gave this mask a go and was super impressed. Usually sheet masks slip and slide off of my face and I have to recline in an awkward position for 10 minutes — but no this one from Loops! It stays in place and includes great ingredients (pumpkin extract, white flower, and baobab oil) that left my face feeling super soft and hydrated. Oh, and the packaging is super cute.Get a five-pack from Loops Beauty for $30. | Glossier, Sarah Han / BuzzFeedMy colleague Sarah Han (as well as MANY other BuzzFeeders) is a big fan of this product. This is what she had to say:"I wasn't a blush person until I met Cloud Paint. Any other attempts at wearing blush always looked super unnatural and accented redness on my face that would, as you might guess, populate in the cheek areas. It was always too much or too little, no in between. Little did I know I needed to say goodbye to powder blushes and let ~gel-cream~ blush into my life. The gel-cream formula just blends so seamlessly, like no other blush I've ever used, and it's a piece of cake to use. It doesn't make pores look more apparent and just gliiiiides over your skin for a dewy-looking flush. And if I have too many glasses of wine, I can blame any flush on the blush."Get it from Glossier for $18 (available in six shades). | instagram.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I am lazy and hate doing my makeup, especially after a morning workout on a weekday. I wanted something I could throw in my bag and smear around my eyes in a couple of seconds, and to just add a little color without the fussiness. This fits the bill perfectly. It gives my eyes a little definition, but isn't super noticeable. The slight shimmer also makes me look awake on days where I'm dragging. It is not intensely shiny, though, which is important to me — I'm not a disco ball! It just reflects light and looks luminescent, not glittery. Because this is so easy to use, non-irritating, and is the exact color I was looking for, I expect that I will keep ordering it as long as it's available." —RachelGet it from Amazon for $4.50+ (available in 23 shades). | lovebeautyandplanet / Via instagram.com, AmazonI'm a sucker for anything made by Love, Beauty and Planet, so you can imagine how thrilled I was to try out this body scrub in my shower. This product is infused with organic coconut oil and Bulgarian roses. It smells AMAZING and leaves my body feeling like velvet — definitely a luxurious add-on for any shower experience. Then I'll top off the whole experience by covering myself in the equally-lovely lotion. Can't beat it!Get them from Amazon for $14.31. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 16 Tips que harán el auto aislamiento con tus hijos mucho más divertido
Short Description Sub Headline: Porque sabemos que puede ser abrumador.
Content Body: 16 Tips que harán el auto aislamiento con tus hijos mucho más divertido | Porque sabemos que puede ser abrumador. | publicado March 27, 2020, 18:26 GMT | March 27, 2020, 18:26 GMT | Mike SpohrBuzzFeed Staff | | | Universal, Warner Bros.Mi esposa y yo fuimos niños en los 80, así que aprovechamos el autoaislamiento para mostrarle a Annie y James algunos de los clásicos de nuestra infancia. Hasta ahora hemos visto películas como la trilogía de Volver al futuro, Los Goonies, Hechizo del tiempo y Los cazafantasmas. Ver a los niños disfrutar de estas películas tanto como nosotros cuando éramos niños ha sido increíble.Pero lo mejor de estas noches de cine, desde el punto de vista del autoaislamiento, es que A) hace que los niños tengan algo que esperar todo el día, B) crea un poco de normalidad programada y C) es un gran momento familiar en el que podemos acurrucarnos y centrarnos en nosotros.

Title Headline: 22 Veces que Hollywood te mintió sobre el cabello
Short Description Sub Headline: Por cosas como estas es que la gente va a las estéticas con el cabello negro y espera tenerlo morado en una hora.
Content Body: 22 Veces que Hollywood te mintió sobre el cabello | Por cosas como estas es que la gente va a las estéticas con el cabello negro y espera tenerlo morado en una hora. | publicado March 27, 2020, 16:31 GMT | March 27, 2020, 16:31 GMT | Hannah MarderBuzzFeed Staff | | | | The WB"En Gilmore Girls, cuando Rory decolora el cabello de Lane. Primero que nada, el decolorante es una especie de ESPUMA (¿¡¿qué?!?) con el que Rory pinta la cabeza de Lane sin separarla ni saturarla. Eso hubiera resultado en manchas anaranjadas desiguales a lo largo del cabello. En segundo lugar, Lane termina con un rubio suficientemente claro como para cubrirlo con un morado BRILLANTE. Esto no sería posible. En la vida real necesitaría MÚLTIPLES sesiones de aclarado para lograrlo, dado que ella tenía un cabello naturalmente negro".—frontbutt69 | Universal PicturesCuando el cabello de un personaje es de un color extraordinario, como azul o rojo cereza, y nunca se destiñe, ni le salen raíces extrañas con el tiempo.—rebeccam4e04c2006 | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Presiona acá para ver el GIFPresiona acá para ver el GIF | Mar. 09, 2020, at 17:45 PM

Title Headline: プリンづくし…！ファミマの“プリンパフェ”に幸せが詰まってました！
Short Description Sub Headline: ファミリーマート（FamilyMart）の「窯出しプリンのパフェ」が最強すぎました…！プリンの下にプリンがあるほどプリン尽くし！！プリンはトロトロ濃厚、ちょっぴり苦味のあるカラメルゼリーも美味しくて、ぺろっと食べられちゃいますよ！

Title Headline: 24 Vegan Baking Ideas For Anyone Who's Been Stress-Baking Lately
Short Description Sub Headline: Ideas from dairy-free donuts to classic chocolate chip cookies.
Content Body: Food | 24 Vegan Baking Ideas For Anyone Who's Been Stress-Baking Lately | Ideas from dairy-free donuts to classic chocolate chip cookies. | Posted on March 21, 2020, 15:46 GMT | March 21, 2020, 15:46 GMT | Whitney JeffersonBuzzFeed Staff | | Domestic Gothess / Via domesticgothess.comEveryone needs an ooey, gooey, melt-in-your-mouth chocolate chip recipe up their sleeve, and this one will deliver exactly that. | The Loopy Whisk / Via theloopywhisk.comIn times of stress, we could all use a little chocolate cake to calm our nerves. Luckily, this recipe is perfect for beginner bakers and fancy chefs alike. | Nora Cooks / Via noracooks.comThis recipe is a vegan spin on classic raspberry bars and is the perfect mix of sweet and savory. | Chocolate Covered Katie / Via chocolatecoveredkatie.comEspecially handy right now, this recipe for vegan lemon bread can be made with whatever flour you have on hand. | The Loopy Whisk / Via theloopywhisk.comThis chocolate babka recipe looks like an artistic masterpiece but is actually fairly simple to make. | Chocolate Covered Katie / Via chocolatecoveredkatie.comWhat's more comforting in the morning than cinnamon rolls all drenched in sugary icing? Try this recipe and find out. | The Big Man's World / Via thebigmansworld.com, Via thebigmansworld.comYes, you can make vegan donuts at home! This tasty recipe can also be modified to be keto and paleo, too. | Ela Vegan / elavegan.comThese brownies are vegan, gluten-free, and made with ease in a food processor. And to those of you who haven't baked with zucchini before, know that you won't taste any actual zucchini or "weird" flavors in the end result. | Short Girl Tall Order / Via shortgirltallorder.comNo baking list would be complete without a recipe for cupcakes. These are particularly fancy with their Earl Grey batter and blueberry whipped frosting! | Nora Cooks / Via noracooks.comWhat's better than s'mores? With this recipe, you can eat vegan cookie bars any day of the week. | Baker by Nature / Via bakerbynature.comIf you're anything like Larry David on Curb Your Enthusiasm, the hardness of your scone is a very important and personal preference. Learn how to make your own with this recipe. | Wee Little Vegans / Via weelittlevegans.comFrench toast is always a fun breakfast, but baking it into French toast cups is kinda next level, no? Just grab some syrup and go to town! | Lucy & Lentils / Via lucyandlentils.co.ukThis recipe for salted caramel shortbread combines dates, gluten-free flour, chocolate, and sugar for layers of goodness. | Strength and Sunshine / Via strengthandsunshine.comThis vegan coffee cake recipe is free of refined sugar and will please everyone at the breakfast table. | Okonomi Kitchen / Via okonomikitchen.comIf it's cake you're after, this recipe for banana snack cake is both easy to make and delicious. | Chocolate Covered Katie / Via chocolatecoveredkatie.comBaking classic sugar cookies is a great way to spend time at home. Use this recipe to make them vegan and get creative with any cookie cutters you have in your house. | Katarina Cermelj / Via theloopywhisk.comThis recipe for vegan banana bread has chocolate chips in it, so you know it'll be a crowd-pleaser. | Eat With Clarity / Via eatwithclarity.comThese soft, pumpkiny cookies have just the right amount of sweetness with icing and might feel a little reminiscent of fall. | The Simple Veganista / Via simple-veganista.comYes, with this recipe, you can make thumbprint cookies vegan and gluten-free using almond flour. | Livin' La Vegan Life / Via livinlaveganlife.com, Livin' La Vida Vegan Life / Via livinlaveganlife.comThe recipe for this delicious-looking marbleized cake is easier to do than you'd imagine just by looking at it. | Love From The Oven / Via lovefromtheoven.comIf you love to make pumpkin bread, try this veganized recipe — I dare you to taste a difference. | The Hidden Veggies / Via thehiddenveggies.comSpeaking of morning staples, this muffin recipe is something you can make ahead of time and then eat the muffins all week!

Title Headline: 23 Low-Effort Products To Help You Become More Productive Without Even Realising
Short Description Sub Headline: Get productive the easy way.
Content Body: Shopping | 23 Low-Effort Products To Help You Become More Productive Without Even Realising | Get productive the easy way. | Posted on March 18, 2020, 17:00 GMT | March 18, 2020, 17:00 GMT | Amy GloverBuzzFeed Staff | | | | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukThe best time to wipe down your shower is immediately after you've finished using it, when the steam has loosened all the dirt and your soap spills haven't hardened yet. That's why the suction cups on these cloths are so genius! You'll always have one to hand after your shower, and the material is designed to clean and polish glass and chrome without leaving any streaks behind.Price: £7.45 for two. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukThey distribute pressure really evenly over your surfaces, helping to clean and polish them without leaving streaks behind. Just run one of these bad boys over your mirrors or door handles and it'll leave them gleaming (trust me, you won't be able to stop using these once you start because the results are super fast and incredibly satisfying). Price: £6.99 for 10.

Title Headline: Pinguine durften in einem Aquarium herumwandern, nachdem es für Menschen geschlossen wurde
Short Description Sub Headline: Wenigstens Wellington, Edward und Annie haben ihren Spaß.
Content Body: Pinguine durften in einem Aquarium herumwandern, nachdem es für Menschen geschlossen wurde | Wenigstens Wellington, Edward und Annie haben ihren Spaß. | Gepostet am March 17, 2020, 14:00 GMT | March 17, 2020, 14:00 GMT | Pablo ValdiviaBuzzFeed Staff | | Shedd Aquarium@shedd_aquarium | Shedd Aquarium | @shedd_aquarium | Penguins in the Amazon?! 🐧🌴Some of the penguins went on a field trip to meet other animals at Shedd. Wellington seemed most interested in the fishes in Amazon Rising! The black-barred silver dollars also seemed interested in their unusual visitor. | Antworten | Retweet | Faven | | Shedd Aquarium@shedd_aquarium | Shedd Aquarium | @shedd_aquarium | The adventure continues! 🐧🐧This morning, Edward and Annie explored Shedd’s rotunda. They are a bonded pair of rockhopper penguins, which means they are together for nesting season. Springtime is nesting season for penguins at Shedd, and this year is no different! (1/3) 👇 | Antworten | Retweet | Faven | Shedd Aquarium@shedd_aquarium | Shedd Aquarium | @shedd_aquarium | Penguins like Edward and Annie will begin to build their nests next week. Join us digitally for nesting coverage! In the meantime, we will be sharing lots of different animal updates (and yes, Wellington will return!) 🐧👀 (2/3) | Antworten | Retweet | Faven | Shedd Aquarium@shedd_aquarium | Shedd Aquarium | @shedd_aquarium | While this may be a strange time for us, these days feel normal for animals at Shedd. Our caregivers are constantly providing new experiences for the animals to explore and express their natural behaviors with. Let us know what penguin activities you would like to see! (3/3) | Antworten | Retweet | Faven

Title Headline: 9 formas de parar de tocar o rosto
Short Description Sub Headline: O CDC recomenda que as pessoas evitem tocar os olhos, o nariz e a boca para prevenir a disseminação de germes. Mas isso é mais difícil do que parece!
Content Body: 9 formas de parar de tocar o rosto | O CDC recomenda que as pessoas evitem tocar os olhos, o nariz e a boca para prevenir a disseminação de germes. Mas isso é mais difícil do que parece! | publicado March 20, 2020, 19:29 GMT | March 20, 2020, 19:29 GMT | Emma LordBuzzFeed Staff | Clique para ver o GIFClique para ver o GIF | Clique para ver o GIFClique para ver o GIF | Para deixar claro, o objetivo do lenço ou cachecol é treinar a si mesmo para perceber quando você está tocando o rosto, não para impedir a propagação de germes. Uma das partes do rosto que mais tocamos é a boca, e um lenço ou cachecol que a encubra parcialmente servirá como um sinal de que algo está diferente e talvez lembre você de que não deve tocar o rosto. Se você está procurando um lenço bandana leve e casual que possa usar, aqui tem ofertas na faixa de R$69 e R$20E sim — tecnicamente, as máscaras médicas são um jeito de fazer isso. Mas o CDC recomenda que apenas as pessoas que estão doentes ou que cuidam de doentes usem máscaras no momento e, no ritmo em que as máscaras estão se esgotando, é mais importante que essas pessoas tenham acesso a elas do que o restante da população. | Até que você consiga se treinar para não tocar o rosto, experimente um lembrete tátil que alertará sua consciência para o gesto inconsciente. Uma forma de fazer isso é usando luvas; se você trabalha num escritório, experimente um par de luvas finas e sem dedos (estas para artrite por R$38,55 na Amazon são perfeitas e podem te ajudar a evitar dor) para que ainda possa usar o computador com facilidade, mas perceba o tecido em seu rosto se tocar nele. Se você é mais de comer as peles dos cantos das unhas, experimente uma combinação de lembrete tátil e visual ao colar pedacinhos de fita adesiva colorida nas pontas dos dedos. Você ainda vai conseguir digitar, mas com certeza sentirá a textura estranha se tocar o rosto e, com sorte, notará a cor neon brilhante antes mesmo de chegar a esse ponto. (Este conjunto de fitas adesivas coloridas por R$6,11 na Amazon, deve funcionar.) | super fantástico meu perfil mágico 𓆙@marav1lhosa | super fantástico meu perfil mágico 𓆙 | @marav1lhosa | Nois tá assim o dia todo tentando não tocar no rosto | Responder | Retwittear | Favorito

Title Headline: Boris Johnson Has Ordered Britain's Pubs, Bars, And Restaurants To Close
Short Description Sub Headline: The government has been forced to introduce tougher measures to protect citizens from the coronavirus. A scheme described as "unprecedented in scope and scale" in the history of the UK will help pay people's wages.
Content Body: Boris Johnson Has Ordered Britain's Pubs, Bars, And Restaurants To Close | The government has been forced to introduce tougher measures to protect citizens from the coronavirus. A scheme described as "unprecedented in scope and scale" in the history of the UK will help pay people's wages. | Originally posted onMarch 20, 2020, 17:11 GMT | March 20, 2020, 17:11 GMT | Updated onMarch 20, 2020, 17:49 GMT | March 20, 2020, 17:49 GMT | Hannah Al-OthmanBuzzFeed News Reporter | |

Title Headline: 「うまぁ！」「ほんのりさくら味」カルディの“春プリン”が今年も出たよー！！このプルップル感、マジ最高だわ…
Short Description Sub Headline: KALDI（カルディ）から期間限定で「さくらミルクプリン」が発売中です。これは大人気カルディの「パンダ杏仁豆腐」シリーズの期間限定バージョン。さくらの爽やかな風味がして、春を感じさせる味わいに仕上がっています！
Content Body: 「うまぁ！」「ほんのりさくら味」カルディの“春プリン”が今年も出たよー！！このプルップル感、マジ最高だわ… | KALDI（カルディ）から期間限定で「さくらミルクプリン」が発売中です。これは大人気カルディの「パンダ杏仁豆腐」シリーズの期間限定バージョン。さくらの爽やかな風味がして、春を感じさせる味わいに仕上がっています！ | March 22, 2020, 06:25 GMT | March 22, 2020, 06:25 GMT | Aina Maruyama丸山 愛菜 BuzzFeed Staff, Japan | | | | こま@guri_kuroneko | こま | @guri_kuroneko | さくらミルクプリンうまぁ！カルディのパンダのパッケージのやつ！うまぁ！ | 返信 | リツイート | お気に入り

Title Headline: It's Been 15 Years Since "The Suite Life Of Zack & Cody" Premiered, So Here's What The Cast Looks Like Now
Short Description Sub Headline: Their lives are pretty ~sweet~.
Content Body: Celebrity | It's Been 15 Years Since "The Suite Life Of Zack & Cody" Premiered, So Here's What The Cast Looks Like Now | Their lives are pretty ~sweet~. | Posted on March 19, 2020, 17:46 GMT | March 19, 2020, 17:46 GMT | Lauren GarafanoBuzzFeed Staff | Disney Channel, Frazer Harrison / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What he's up to now: Currently, Cole stars as Jughead Jones on The CW's Riverdale. Last year, he played Will Newman in the movie Five Feet Apart, and later this year he will be producing and starring in a fictional podcast called Borrasca. | Disney Channel, Theo Wargo / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What he's up to now: Since Suite Life, Dylan has continued acting and has appeared in movies like Dismissed and Carte Blanche. He's also got a few movies coming up, including Banana Split, Tyger Tyger, Turandot, and After We Collided. Dylan's also the cofounder of a meadery called All-Wise Meadery. | Disney Channel, Phillip Faraone / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What she's up to now: Ashley has continued acting and recently starred on Netflix's Merry Happy Whatever, and she's currently starring on Carol's Second Act. Last year, Ashley also released her third studio album, Symptoms. | Disney Channel, David Livingston / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What she's up to now: Brenda also kept acting after Suite Life. Recently, she's been in a bunch of shows and movies, like Dollface, Secret Obsession, Amphibia, Changeland, and Station 19. | Disney Channel, Phill Lewis / cameo.comFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode: "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What he's up to now: Phill has taken a break from acting, but he's started directing! He's directed episodes of Young & Hungry, Melissa & Joey, 2 Broke Girls, Indebted, and One Day At A Time. He's currently on Cameo too! | Disney Channel, @kimrhodes4reals / instagram.comFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What she's up to now: Kim continued acting in movies and TV. Aside from her role on Suite Life, she's also known for playing Sheriff Jody Mills on Supernatural. | Disney Channel, @adrianrmante / instagram.comFirst episode (2005): "Hotel Hangout" (Season 1, Episode 1)Last episode (2008): "A Tale of Two Houses" (Season 3, Episode 15)What he's up to now: Since Suite Life, Adrian has appeared in Magnum P.I., Twice the Dream, The Haunt, Hawaii Five-0, and NCIS: Los Angeles. He also got married in 2018 and has two kids! | Disney Channel, Matt Winkelmeyer / Getty ImagesFirst episode (2005): "The Prince & The Plunger" (Season 1, Episode 6)Last episode (2008): "Mr. Tipton Comes to Visit" (Season 3, Episode 22)What he's up to now: Brian continued acting and has since been in movies like LBJ and Green Book. He currently has recurring roles in The Loud House and Young Sheldon, and has guest starred on shows like I'm Sorry, The Thundermans, and Longmire.

Title Headline: 19 Subscription Boxes That People Actually Swear By
Short Description Sub Headline: Subscriptions for gardeners, teachers, pet parents, bakers, board game enthusiasts, and way more.
Content Body: Shopping | 19 Subscription Boxes That People Actually Swear By | Subscriptions for gardeners, teachers, pet parents, bakers, board game enthusiasts, and way more. | Posted on March 23, 2020, 14:11 GMT | March 23, 2020, 14:11 GMT | Harper HendricksonBuzzFeed Staff | | | | CratejoyWhat you get: You'll unpack four to six full-size, themed items for you and your pup. There will be toys and all-natural treats in every box for your pup, and all sorts of things for you — home decor items, healthy snacks, aromatherapy oils, tea, jewelry, books, bath and beauty products, crystals, and more!Promising review: "Fantastic Box! My puppy spent hours playing with the unicorn toys and loved the treats. I adored the necklace and candle and the blessing was so sweet. I am totally in love with this box and it's so reasonably priced! The items are very high quality. It was like present after present that my pup and I opened together. Loved it. Great job!" —Andrea H.Get it from Cratejoy for $39.95/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: You'll receive all the pre-measured ingredients you need to make baking easy, quick, and fun! You'll also receive step-by-step instructions and video tutorials, and a new baking tool in every box. Each variety of treat makes up to 12-20 servings. Promising review: "My wife bought these boxes and I decided to try to make one on my own when she wasn’t home. It’s very rare that I bake, but the directions were easy to follow and she was really surprised by how good I did. Maple pecan mini cakes came out great! And, the box made more mini cakes than it said it was going to. Update: Tried the Chai Tea Latte cupcakes and they came out perfect too. Our favorite of all the boxes we have tried so far." —Anthony M.Get it from Cratejoy for $30.99/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: Your kiddos will get a fun and engaging box that combines SELL (Social-Emotional Learning and Literacy) with monthly secret missions! These hands-on missions include projects, comic books, and stories of real heroes. This box promotes a mindfulness mindset and helps kids build skills like resilience, courage, and empathy.Promising review: "BRILLANT! I had high expectations when I purchased this as Christmas gifts for my two nieces (ages 5 and 6) and nephew (6). I wanted to give them something different. The lessons are deliberate and packaged as fun they can identify with. Who wouldn’t want to be their own superhero? The kids (three different families) constantly send me videos of their projects and their parents all tell me it is the one gift they have been going back to after all the Christmas excitement has settled. The boxes are fun and unique. I love the learning that it's given the kids. As they’ve told me, 'Superheroes have feelings too!' This is a perfect product for modern times and will be my 'go-to' gift from here on out." —Celeste C. Get it from Cratejoy for $29.58/month. | CratejoyWhat you get: You'll receive eco-conscious products to help reduce your carbon footprint, and information about global environmental problems such as plastic pollution, deforestation, ocean dead zones, and pollinator die-off. You'll also receive postcards, stamps, addresses, and talking points so you can inform family, friends, and neighbors about the issues affecting our world via snail mail. Promising review: "I got my first box last month. It's amazing! It had produce bags, really cool bamboo straws, pens and pencils and everything I need to send postcards about causes I care about. I love that I can do this with my family and teach them that change is possible and that it starts in our own home. I had all the neighborhood kids come over and write postcards. Not only did they participate, but they learned about the effects of having plastic in our national parks. This crate is fun and makes me feel good about myself." —Amber W.Get it from Cratejoy at $20/month. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 26 Filme, die so verstörend sind, dass du sie eventuell nicht zu Ende gucken kannst
Short Description Sub Headline: Vielleicht solltest du dir diese Filme besser nicht ansehen, wenn du alleine zu Hause bist...
Content Body: 26 Filme, die so verstörend sind, dass du sie eventuell nicht zu Ende gucken kannst | Vielleicht solltest du dir diese Filme besser nicht ansehen, wenn du alleine zu Hause bist... | Gepostet am March 30, 2020, 18:01 GMT | March 30, 2020, 18:01 GMT | Spencer AlthouseBuzzFeed Staff | A24Worum es geht: „Ein Ehepaar reist nach Schweden, um das sagenumwobene Mittsommerfest eines abgelegenen Dorfes zu besuchen. Was zunächst wie ein idyllischer Rückzugsort wirkt, entwickelt sich schnell zu einem immer heftigeren und bizarreren Wettstreit im Rahmen eines heidnischen Kultes.“Warum du dir den anschauen solltest: „Ich habe ihn vor etwa einer Woche gesehen und er spukt mir immer noch im Kopf herum. Die Folterszenen waren starker Tobak und an manchen Stellen musste ich die Lautstärke runterdrehen und die Augen schließen.“—genevievemnm | | El Deseo S.A.Worum es geht: „Ein brillanter plastischer Chirurg, der von den Tragödien der Vergangenheit geplagt wird, erschafft eine Art synthetische Haut, die jeder Art von Schäden widersteht. Sein Versuchskaninchen ist eine geheimnisvolle und launische Frau, die den Schlüssel zu seiner Besessenheit in sich trägt.“Warum du dir den anschauen solltest: „Es ist ein spanischer Film mit Antonio Banderas. Ich habe ihn vor fünf Jahren gesehen und denke immer noch oft darüber nach, weil er mich so geschockt hat.“—kayliel2 | Warner Bros.Worum es geht: „Die Bewohner des Urlaubsortes Seal Island werden von einer Hundemeute terrorisiert – es handelt sich um zurückgelassene Haustiere von früheren Urlaubern.“Warum du dir den anschauen solltest: „Dieser Film hat mich fast 30 Jahre lang begleitet. Die Jump Scares haben mich damals geschockt und sie schocken mich auch heute noch. Der Film kann wirklich Ängste auslösen.“—beaverhousen469

Title Headline: 35 Heavy-Duty Cleaning Products To Help You Tackle The Toughest Messes In Your Home
Short Description Sub Headline: They never even stood a chance.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 35 Heavy-Duty Cleaning Products To Help You Tackle The Toughest Messes In Your Home | They never even stood a chance. | Posted on March 18, 2020, 14:00 GMT | March 18, 2020, 14:00 GMT | Melanie AmanBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.comPromising review: "I have very hard water that leaves hard water buildup and nasty stains. It’s embarrassing to have guests over because the toilets are so gross! I have tried so many products and cleaning solutions — from natural essential oils to harsh chemicals so strong I was lightheaded for the rest of the day. Well, I tried out this pumice stone after reading about it in a BuzzFeed article, and honestly the hype is real! It does take some elbow grease, but the after picture is from only 20 minutes of scrubbing, light enough that I didn’t break a sweat! The stone does get used up, but I think this one should last me a couple years at least. So if you have embarrassing toilets, try this!" —Stephanie RayGet it from Amazon for $8.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "This stuff is amazing! After over 10 years of the grout not being cleaned, and a botched repair job, the bathroom floor in this house looked horrendous. Two pens covered the entire bathroom floor, with plenty left over in the second pen, even with applying two to three layers (which you will definitely need as the paint is a bit thin and also absorbs into the grout). Super easy to apply, works exactly like a regular paint marker. Be sure to press the pen tip on a separate (thick) cloth to activate it before actually using on the grout so you don't end up with a huge mess on the tile when the paint floods out at first. If you see the first side of the tip is getting frayed, just pull it out and turn it around to the other side." —regalleGet it from Amazon for $8.99+ (available in two sizes and three colors). | | amazon.comPromising review: "I recently moved into a home with hard water and the dishwasher needed cleaning. One cycle with this cleaner and it looks perfect! I will continue to use this product once a month as recommended. :-)" —MorgysMomGet a three-pack from Amazon for $19.99. | amazon.comIt's safe for unwaxed, non-oiled, polyurethane-finished wood flooring. Just spray it on wood and wipe with a mop or Swiffer.Promising review: "I moved into an apartment with absolutely disgusting wood floors. Whenever I would walk on it my feet would turn black. I used this product as well as a rag and a cleaning brush. It worked very well and now I’m not scared or grossed-out walking on my floors! The pictures are 'before' and 'afters' from cleaning." —fwkGet it from Amazon for $7.97. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "After running eufy for nearly two months now, I can confidently say I absolutely LOVE it! It is amazing on my hardwood floors. It picks up sooo much fine dust brought in by my two German Shepards! They shed year-round! And it’s super effective with pet hair! Wow! I use Eufy once a day for a little more than hour, emptying and cleaning the brushes out about three to four times during use. It seriously has been life-changing, keeping my floors cleaner than sweeping! Great purchase and I would highly recommend!!" —Jacqueline MGet it from Amazon for $159.99 (originally $229; also available in white). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I had the previous Hoover carpet cleaner and it worked well, but I always dreaded using it because it was time consuming to wash, rinse, and dry. This Smartwash is incredible and so easy to use. I love that it does the wash when you push and the rinse/dry when you pull back. I finished in half the time!!!! I love that I can just use it as if it’s a regular vacuum and it does all the hard work for me! I can’t say enough good things!!!!" —John and MeganGet it from Amazon for $198 (originally $249.99). | amazon.comThis portable carpet cleaner will spray, brush, and suction up any stain, no adult supervision needed. It also comes with a hose and tool attachment if you'd prefer a more hands-on cleaning session.Promising review: "I have an older pug and he has always been good, but I knew one day this machine would be brought out. I had it nine months before my first use. He got sick one week, and I literally used the machine about 12 times in a week. All I can say is Bissell knocked it our of the park with this. It’s amazing. It cleans so well. It is the simplest machine I have ever used that does so much. It is well designed. Quick set up. And clean up. It does all the work for you. And it does a fantastic job. I love it. Worth every penny. I’ll never be without one. If you are on the fence, buy it. I can’t believe how good this machine works. And the design is flawless. The tanks are so easy to fill. And clean for storage. And if it can clean 100% of what we had this week. It can clean anything!!! Like it never even happened. Thank you Bissell!!!" —DavidGet it from Amazon for $149 (originally $179.99). | amazon.comPromising review: "Throw away your other bathroom descalers and shower cleaners and use this. I get mineral spots on the glass wall and mineral buildup on the shower head causing the shower to spray water to the sides, and a quick soak in this product clears the shower head of minerals, cleans the glass completely, and leaves your shower looking brand new." —R. EnglishGet it from Amazon for $19.38. | amazon.comPromising review: "Holy crap!! Are you skeptical when it comes to buying stuff online? ME TOO! That's why I figured all of these rave reviews were a crock of crap. I've seriously bought every kind of vacuum out there, including the Roomba, which is about as intelligent as a cotton swab. But I have four cats and a golden retriever, so I was getting desperate! I believe the saying is… a picture is worth a thousand words. Check mine out (above)! Of note — the 'before' picture was taken of my dog's bed AFTER it went through the washer and dryer. Look at all of that left-behind hair!!! And the 'after' picture was taken after only THREE MINUTES spent vacuuming her bed. I. Am. SOLD! BTW, I've NEVER taken the time to review a product before, just FYI." —Luka ChanGet it on Amazon for $30.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "Our tub/shower has a grippy bottom, and scum and dirt cakes on it so easily. The only way I've been able to get it off before was literally scraping it inch by inch. I've spent hours and all it ever got was somewhat clean — never enough for me to want to take a real bath in it. This stuff is expensive but with the good reviews I decided to try it. It works amazingly!! I sprayed it on (it came with a great spray nozzle and a lid) and left it for about 15 to 20 minutes. Then I took a brush with hard plastic bristles (I believe a soft brush would have even worked) and with less than 20 minutes of scrubbing the entire tub and walls it was cleaner than when we moved in. The grime and scum almost like melted off. It smells pleasant. It's not crazy-strong smelling, but in an enclosed space I still felt the need to wear a mask while cleaning." —Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $18.88. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Amazon, amazon.comIt comes with the brush spinner, charging station, eight rubber collars that securely connect the makeup brush to the spinner, a glass bowl, and a splash guard ring. Promising review: "I use my makeup brushes daily, and they get filthy. I've used other cleaners and this product wins hands down. The wand and the cleaner itself takes all the hard work and does it for you, not to mention the the brushes dry in seconds. This is the cleanest my brushes have ever been. Highly recommend." —ValerieGet it from Amazon for $49.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comThere's also a built-in squeegee for wiping up liquids or for cleaning glass. Plus, the handle extends from 36 to 60 inches so it can reach practically any mess.Promising review: "I bought this broom based on the tons of great reviews and I am not disappointed. I love this broom! It is lightweight but sturdy. I have used it on tile floors and carpet and it does a great job of getting the pet hair, lint, and dirt. I like this so much better than our traditional push broom. It is very easy to clean after use just using my hand, unlike our old broom. It also has a telescoping handle so that you can adjust it to whatever height you need. There is also a squeegee for doing the house windows and the car windows. I highly recommend it." —Joyce VGet it from Amazon for $14.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "I'll let my pictures (above) speak to how amazing this works. I had a stained mattress that I'd been covering with a mattress pad for years. As I was preparing for a move, I decided to give OxiClean a try and see if it could remove the stains that had been there for well over SEVEN YEARS. I honestly don't even know what caused the stains, but OxiClean removed them. I took before, during, and after pictures (after pictures show the outline of water because I took them immediately after rinsing. I honestly can't believe the results. I wish I'd done this sooner!" —Little GreekGet it from Amazon for $12.98. | amazon.comPromising review: "When we bought our home, there was no water softener and years of iron buildup. We tried so many things on our shower. Nothing worked. We were convinced we’d be stuck until we renovated the bathroom. The Iron Out worked wonders. I still can’t believe it. We had to let it sit for about an hour. It then dissolved and wiped right off. Definitely use in a ventilated area if possible." —M. GilardiGet it from Amazon for $3.80+ (available in two versions). | amazon.comPromising review: "Where has this been all my crazy cat-loving life? Sticky rollers work fine for clothes, but this is the only product that has ever COMPLETELY removed all the cat hair from my bed. I have a long-haired 20-pound tabby and if you run your hands up his back a few times and fling the hair everywhere, it looks like it's snowing — he never stops shedding no matter what I do. After using the ChomChom, I can put on a black dress and roll around on my bed and not get a single hair on me. It's absolutely amazing. Everyone is getting one for Christmas, even if they don't have a pet. I don't care, it's THAT good." —StephanieGet it from Amazon for $24.95. | amazon.comPromising review: "Something I didn't believe until I tried it. So easy to follow directions, written on Angry Mama. Was disappointed when I opened the microwave to see the filth still on it. Was wishing it would magically taken care of itself. But all it took was a quick swipe with a paper towel and GONE. Loosened everything, which is half the process. My microwave was sooooo white once cleaned!! Would buy as gifts." —max's mumGet it from Amazon for $9.58. | amazon.comWe recommend picking up some reusable cleaning gloves before you begin your disinfecting. If you want to save yourself from getting down on your hands and knees to scrub, one reviewer suggested using a broom so you can both stand *and* clean a larger surface area.Promising review: "We’re on a well so we have very hard water. Recently the water got super rusty and left horrible stains in the shower that would not come out. This was the only thing that worked and it worked GREAT! I just used a damp sponge to scrub it in and all of the rust stains came out. For the lighter spots it took maybe one swipe to clean which was incredible. For the super dark spots it took a little elbow grease but it got it out. I am absolutely amazed and will always use this from now on. I highly recommend it for tough-to-clean hard water stains." —Amanda A. Get it from Amazon for $8.28.Read our review of Bar Keepers Friend and how one writer used it to deep clean her new apartment. | amazon.comPromising review: "Our poor older pup started having some incontinence issues and had several accidents in the house. I was really frustrated until I found these. They work amazingly well. They're small, so if the area was larger I had to use two or three, but they pulled up stains and saved the house from being smelly. I even used one on an older stain (that I'm pretty sure wasn't pet related) and it came up after leaving it on for about 24 hours. I make sure to keep a supply of these in the house at all times now." —MCGet a pack of 20 from Amazon for $24.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "I’ve been trying to switch all my cleaning products over to biodegradable or biocompatible, but I still expect them to work. I bought this because my shower stall doors are supposed to be transparent but were actually a mess of fog, hard water deposits, and other foul substances. Nothing I used cleaned the doors at all. I tried this and scrubbed my doors twice with it. Not only did it actually clean my doors but it lacks gross fumes and smells quite pleasant." —A. Via Get it from Amazon for $12.95. | amazon.comPromising review: "Be sure to use hot water; even though it won't foam as much it seems to do a lot better job. The first time I used these on a Contigo travel mug I used room-temp water, and it just came out OK. For the next travel mug, I used boiling water and the results were terrific. It looks new again. Then I used two cubes (and boiling water) in a large old pressure cooker that had become brown inside from years of making vegetable soups, and I'm amazed how clean it came out. That pressure cooker stain persisted throughout dozens of scrubbing sessions and dishwasher runs, so I figured the Bottle Bright wouldn't help either but it did." —MisterPlowGet 12 tablets from Amazon for $8. | amazon.comPromising review: "My shower floor is a bumpy, plastic material that has been a thorn in my side for a couple of years. I have used bleach, chlorine, tile cleaners, Soft Scrub, and Clorox bathroom spray (which usually cleans everything). I have even soaked cloths in bleach and let them sit on the area to see if that would work. None of them have removed the stains. I only had about 10 minutes before having to leave for work, so I only cleaned half so I could see the difference. It was amazing! I sprayed it on, let it sit for about five minutes (not sure if I needed to do that, but figured if bleach wouldn't clean it that nothing would), then used my usual cleaning brush. I didn't even have to scrub....just minimal circular motions and viola! The stains are gone! I couldn't be more pleased. The stains were there for over two years and with only five minutes of sitting and less than a minute of scrubbing, it looks like a new shower again. There are a couple of small areas that probably need a little more brushing, but like I said, I literally spent less than a minute with the brush. I highly recommend this product. And, no, I am not getting paid anything to say this. I very rarely review products unless I believe in them and this one is a keeper!" —MakadamiaGet it from Amazon for $5.51. | amazon.comPromising review: "I let my tub get extra dirty on purpose because I knew this brush set was coming. In five minutes my tub was sparkling clean. This item is no joke. The flat brushes are awesome for big surfaces and the cone brush hits the hard to reach corners. I liked them so much I bought a set for my mom." —Jason B.Get it from Amazon for $14.95+ (available in soft, medium, stiff, and ultra stiff bristles). | amazon.comPromising review: "This stuff is seriously amazing! I am relentless about cleaning my tub because I use it so often and always get grossed out if I don’t. Before I purchased this, I used the typical homemade recipe of bleach and powdered dishwashing soap. I’d have to run two or three cycles to get it crystal clear. One cycle with this stuff, 15 minutes, and the results are amazing! The first photo (above) is with my tub running with the solution. Then I drained it (second photo) and wiped it down with a sponge. When I refilled the tub up, and reran the jets, I kid you not the water was CRYSTAL CLEAR! See for yourself in the last photo! I’m so impressed!" —ChelseaGet it from Amazon for $16.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "This stuff is incredible. My rental apartment has a white glass cooktop and it gets nasty even if you use very clean pots and pans on it. Before I found this stuff, I thought that for sure I would lose a big chunk of my security deposit, but I have yet to encounter a stain that this stuff cannot remove. Sometimes it takes a couple of tries alternating between the paste and the razor scraper, but even the most stubborn burned-on, carbonized food bits always come off." —MaxGet it from Amazon for $11.03. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "First, let me say I never clean my oven because hate it so much! It had years of baked-on drippings on the bottom and the usual brown crud that forms on the sides and shelves. After reading reviews, I decided to give it a try. It works wonders! My oven looks great and it was so easy. Follow the directions and all the bad stuff just wipes away! I've even used it on other stubborn stains on baking pans. Highly recommended!!" —E. NyquistGet it from Amazon for $6.44. | amazon.comPromising review: "Totally impressed! The unassuming generic packaging and label left me a bit skeptical but this stuff is almost as exciting as the wine I spilled! This cabernet stain sat on my ivory faux fur blanket for over a month before I tried this product. Completely gone in one try! Get this. Seriously. You won’t be disappointed." —PersianTessGet it from Amazon for $6.67. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 17 Tips & Products The BuzzFeed Shopping Team Swears By For Working From Home

Content Body: Shopping | 17 Tips & Products The BuzzFeed Shopping Team Swears By For Working From Home | From our couch to yours. | Posted on March 25, 2020, 18:01 GMT | March 25, 2020, 18:01 GMT | Maitland QuitmeyerBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | | | BuzzFeed / Heather Braga, Nordstrom"I do not work in PJs. Or if you have a 'good' set of PJs (like the stuff you wear on a group trip where other ppl see your PJs) slip into those. I'm never going to wear jeans while WFH but I'll put on clean pajama pants at least." —Elizabeth Lilly"I've had trouble with the 'dress as if you're going to work' advice (I wanna be comfy) so I tweaked it to be 'dress in a way you would never ever leave the house.' It motivates me to actually change clothes (I get to plan out a very weird outfit) and it'll be fun to see how out of control my outfits get by the end of the week. Today is head-to-toe buffalo check." —Bek O'Connell"I’m doing a Disney T-shirt challenge. Title Headline: 23 Stress-Reducing Things For Your Workspace To Help You Calm Down A Little
Short Description Sub Headline: Whether your current workspace is a desk, a couch, a bed, or a kitchen table, you're gonna want these.
Content Body: Shopping | 23 Stress-Reducing Things For Your Workspace To Help You Calm Down A Little | Whether your current workspace is a desk, a couch, a bed, or a kitchen table, you're gonna want these. | Posted on March 26, 2020, 14:00 GMT | March 26, 2020, 14:00 GMT | Katy HermanBuzzFeed Staff | Chronicle Books, Sarah Han/BuzzFeedGet it from Barnes & Noble for $15.72, Chronicle Books for $16.95, or from Bookshop (to support local booksellers) for $15.59. | | | HomesickGet the Grandma's Kitchen candle (with notes of apple and butter) for $29.95 and the Beach Cottage candle (with notes of bergamot and sandalwood) for $29.95, both from Homesick. | Knock KnockPromising review: "I use these daily to lift my mood and remind myself that I'm a badass!" —SyniGet a deck of 50 from Knock Knock for $14. | PrincetonPieces/Etsy, EmbellishMyWorld/EtsyGet the chonky hamster pen from PrincetonPieces on Etsy for $2.99 (available in four colors) and the narwhal pen from EmbellishMyWorld on Etsy for $2.25 (available in four colors). | Urban OutfittersPromising review: "I use these in my dorm since I have no control over the heater, and they really help in a pinch when my feet are cold as I'm writing essays." —odetteb Get them from Urban Outfitters for $35 (available in three colors). | Best BuyPromising review: "I spend A LOT of time at my desk so I decided I need to find the way to do some exercise. I found it. This product is very quiet — my coworkers sitting next to me don't even notice or hear a thing when I start pedaling. Easy and quick to assemble — it took me less than 30 minutes. Well-packaged out of the box and sturdy pedal straps. LCD monitor is removable and can be extended to be placed on top of a desk for display." —LityGet it from Best Buy for $139.99. | REIPromising review: "Although designed primarily for feet and hands, it can be used for arms, calves, neck, and even the quads, hamstrings, and hips. It really helped loosen all the tension and knots." —Golf nut in NoviGet it from REI for $24.95. | Pusheen ShopThe pages tear out easily, so you can turn your masterpieces into adorable workspace decor!Get it from Pusheen Shop for $7.80 or Barnes & Noble for $7.99. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | The Paper StoreGet the lemur or the avocado from The Paper Store for $19.99. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 27 Things That Are Both Incredibly Stylish And Wildly Practical
Short Description Sub Headline: Because you shouldn't have to sacrifice style for utility!
Content Body: Shopping | 27 Things That Are Both Incredibly Stylish And Wildly Practical | Because you shouldn't have to sacrifice style for utility! | Posted on March 17, 2020, 18:41 GMT | March 17, 2020, 18:41 GMT | Victoria KuglinBuzzFeed Staff | | | Amazon / Via amazon.ca, @zinganything / Via instagram.comReviewers say it's strong, durable, and doesn't leak.Get it on Amazon Canada for $20.67+ (available in four colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caIt also has handy handles for easy mobility, so go ahead and move it around wherever you need it. Get it on Amazon Canada for $105. | Amazon / Via amazon.ca, Victoria Kuglin / Via BuzzFeedI've used it on freezing airplanes, as an extra layer during chilly fall mornings, or as a full-on scarf come winter. It rolls up pretty small, so tucking it into my purse or carry-on is easy!Get it on Amazon Canada for $99.99+ (available in ten colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caPlus, the bangles double as hair tie holders! Say goodbye to those annoying and painful wrist creases (#bless).Get the set on Amazon Canada for $25.99 (also available individually, or in sets of two). | Amazon / Via amazon.caReviewers say they've used it for everything from organizing their desk, to storing their kids' art supplies, and they say it can withstand just about everything they throw at it. Get it on Amazon Canada for $26.24+ (available in two sizes). | Amazon / Via amazon.caI'm very moto-vated to get one of these for myself!Get it on Amazon Canada for $157.99+ (available in eight colours, and in sizes XS-L). | Amazon / Via amazon.caIt's made of soft, natural materials, so you won't have to worry about any kids accidentally bonking their noggins on sharp edges. It arrives folded, but don't stress — fill it with some blankets or pillows, and it'll plump up in no time.Get it on Amazon Canada for $27.99+ (available in three styles). | Amazon / Via amazon.caYou can also layer this with long-sleeve tops, turtlenecks, or T-shirts during the rest of the year.Get it on Amazon Canada for $22.99+ (available in ten prints, and in sizes S-3XL). | Amazon / Via amazon.caReviewers love that unlike some wire strainers, this one actually contains the tea leaves and keeps them from spilling out. Plus, it's easy to clean!Get it on Amazon Canada for $18. | Amazon / Via amazon.caIf you're looking for a more tailored fit, you can find a great option here.Get it on Amazon Canada for $29.99+ (available in four colours, and in sizes S-XL). | @oxo / Via instagram.com, @oxo / Via instagram.comThe carafe also comes with a cork seal to keep the concentrate fresh after brewing.Get it on Amazon Canada for $37.32. | Amazon / Via amazon.caReviewers have been pleasantly surprised by these, saying the quality and comfort rivals higher-end eyewear. Get a pair on Amazon Canada for $30 (available in three colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caThey also have neat little crumb-catching edges and non-slip feet to prevent your food prep from turning your kitchen into a disaster zone. Title Headline: 45 Clever Little Ways To Store Almost Everything In Your Home
Short Description Sub Headline: Imagine a world where you open a drawer or cabinet and everything doesn't fall out.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 45 Clever Little Ways To Store Almost Everything In Your Home | Imagine a world where you open a drawer or cabinet and everything doesn't fall out. | Posted on January 24, 2020, 13:00 GMT | January 24, 2020, 13:00 GMT | Elena GarciaBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Wow! I can find my socks, hose, bras, and scarves again! Great organizers! It helps clear clutter and makes putting together great outfits so much easier! So glad I got them! I hope to order more! Also, no more solo socks!" —H.j.Get a set of four from Amazon for $12.97+ (available in seven colors). | | AmazonPromising review: "It was always a pain to reach down the side of my bed to reach my chargers, not to mention the wad of cables I’d have to sift through just to charge my phone. I finally searched for a solution and came across these. They’re great! They’re really easy to stick on and they stay in place. I haven’t had an issue of them falling off. Whenever I need to charge a device they’re right next to me, easy to reach and untangled. I definitely recommend!" —Nelis PerezGet a pack of six from Amazon for $6.97. | amazon.comPromising review: "I love the crap out of this thing! I have so many camis that I use as undershirts for work and they were always being folded up and crammed into a drawer, taking up way too much space. After putting away half of my shirts on this two-pack, I knew I needed to buy another pack! It's so easy to take the shirts on and off without messing around with any of the others. This organizer is perfect for my needs in freeing up a drawer and taking up little space in my closet." —TessaGet a two-pack from Amazon for $9.99+. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Exactly as advertised! I've got mine on the counter, with the feet on it, but I'm considering taking them off and sliding it in the cupboard. Right now the novelty and organizational prettiness of it has me smitten. I'd say it's pretty much exactly worth the price, and this was the best price everywhere I looked, even including places where I could have used a 20% coupon." —Gigi Marie Get it from Amazon for $9.99+ (available in black, red and white). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "These come with their hangers and will add considerable storage. I put one on the inside of our pantry door and the second on the back of the door going from laundry room to garage. I initially was interested in getting one for the pantry, but the second was a nice bonus and it makes a great place to hold cleaning supplies. Well-made, excellent price." —KimberleeGet a two-pack from Amazon for $12.97. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "Sturdy! The weight limit says 30 lbs., but I'm 99% sure I'm over that and the bar is still straight as a board. I recommend measuring the distance from your main closet bar, the average length of the clothes, and seeing if the remaining length leaves enough room for the second row to hang without touching the floor (unless you don't mind it)." —M. GeeGet it from Amazon for $22.04. | AmazonPop them right out when you need to clean them!Promising review: "This is one of my favorite things I've ever purchased from Amazon! The fact that they are so customizable allows you to cut them for any drawer size! I think this will be my go-to gift for all of my friends who love cooking as much as I do! Freeing up cabinet space and having something that can easily be rinsed off in the sink makes this a for-sure buy!" —momononoGet a pack of six on Amazon for $15.99. | AmazonPromising review: "THESE ARE SO MUCH BIGGER AND NICER IN PERSON!! Really, they are so great! I love them! And yes, I am a grown-up but I thought they would make storing stuff at my office more fun and they stack easily. I WAS RIGHT!! SO MUCH FUN AND REALLY HANDY! Whether you buy them for your kids or you buy them for yourself, they are GREAT for storage and stack just like giant Legos and are SO WORTH THE MONEY!!" —Sean T. FlynnGet them from Amazon for $10.49+ (available in small, medium, and large sizes and in a variety of colors). | AmazonPromising review: "It is so great to have a high-quality knife set. The pieces have a very nice weight to them. The various knives make easy work when cutting/slicing both uncooked and meats, seafood, bread, tomatoes, onions — heck, everything I've cut thus far has been a breeze. Also, the knife block continually sharpens the pieces. Literally the best set I've owned. Love them." —MeSharonnaGet a 15-piece set from Amazon for $112.99. | AmazonPromising review (for the over-the-door organizer): "Oh my goodness, I should've gotten something like this long ago. Everything is available at a glance and it's all organized. I don't have to take everything out of my cupboard just to find the one I'm looking for. And it doesn't take up tons of space in my coat closet. I can do a quick inventory of what I'm running out of. It's also a great place to keep a pair of scissors and tape high up out of the reach of my toddlers." —daiseyworldGet the organizer from Amazon for $8.14 and the over-the-door organizer for $13.32. There's also a really great gift bag organizer if that's more your jam. | AmazonPromising review: "Love these sooo much I bought three! I use them to hold rice, homemade breadcrumbs, and coconut flour. The caps make a nice airtight lid and they're very convenient to use, always right where you need them to be. The sizing on the bin itself is a little tall, so I store these lying down in my cabinets, otherwise, they don't fit. If you are looking for something to store your grains/powders/crumbs/seeds/cereal/whatever in, these bins are AWESOME." —ChrisGet it from Amazon for $12.95. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I love it!! I wanted to do a huge apartment cleanse and finally get everything organized and orderly. My apartment's shelving and cabinets are awkward but this product does the trick and allows me to utilize the dead space underneath my sink. Now I don't have to sift around when I need something, I can see where it is! One of the shelves did have a minor dent when it arrived, but I don't really care since it's an under-the-sink shelving unit. It has not comprised the quality or function of this product." —XtinaGet it from Amazon for $19.87+ (available in three finishes). | AmazonPromising review: "It actually fits my size 13 shoes! Not a fan of the color but when something this useful comes along for me, who cares? I mean, it is behind the closet door. I recommend this for anyone who has large feet and is looking for an over-the-door shoe organizer." —C. CurateGet it from Amazon for $24.95 (available in two colors). | marthastewart.com, AmazonGet the storage container from Amazon for $11.99+ (available in four colors). | AmazonPromising review: "They have been working wonderfully. Having lots of vegetables chopped up and easily accessible without opening several containers has really sped up our morning lunch preparation time." —Magen R.Get a set of two from Amazon for $29.65+. | AmazonPromising review: "Just purchased my second set of these — they are perfect! I use them to protect my good frying pans, my Dutch ovens, nice glass bowls — anything where stacking is needed for space but I was worried about scratching. I love the neutral color, but with a cute, all-over pattern, and the size is great for deep bowls to protect the sides or large pans. Plus they are definitely the most cost-effective ones out there. I plan to buy more and also use as an add-on gift when giving cookware." —Sno-cone loverGet a set of six from Amazon for $9.69+ (available in six sizes). | AmazonPromising review: "This is the product I didn’t know always needed. The little map is so cute and both my 1-year-old and 4-year-old enjoy playing. The best part is when they’re done I just pull the drawstring and clean up is over. It makes moving the play space and cleaning up so easy. I wish I found this before. Highly recommend." —AnonymousGet it from Amazon for $39.99. | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "The perfect thing for all the remotes! Attractive, sturdy, plus well-made and stylish. Just ordered two more." —DPGet it from Amazon for $10.99. | AmazonGet it from Amazon for $125+ (available in black and brown). | amazon.comGet it from Amazon for $18.69+ (available in three sizes and in black, white, and green). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 52 Valentine's Day Gifts For When You're Totally In Love, But Broke
Short Description Sub Headline: I hate how much I love Valentine's Day.
Content Body: Shopping | | Gift Ideas | Under $50 | 52 Valentine's Day Gifts For When You're Totally In Love, But Broke | I hate how much I love Valentine's Day. | Posted on January 31, 2020, 01:01 GMT | January 31, 2020, 01:01 GMT | Mallory MowerBuzzFeed Staff | | | AmazonThe box includes 100 unique conversation starters ranging from basic and lighthearted to more serious situations. With questions like, "What was your proudest moment from the last 12 months?" and "What's one dream that you've tucked away for the moment?" you're sure to find something you and your S.O. can really connect with. Promising review: "This game, if we should call it a game, is so wonderful. We opened the box and just randomly started choosing out cards. Some of the cards were quick and straightforward, while other were more thought provoking. We got some good laughs out of this and it was truly a refreshing change compared to our previous casual conversations. I see this can being very useful for couples who want to get to know each other but also for couples like us, who are so busy in our day-to-day with the work and kids. It gave us something different to talk about outside the typical operational 'how was your day' type of conversations." —OritGet it from Amazon for $18.95. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This adventure book is really cute. I bought this because my boyfriend and I just moved into our first apartment together! It's a very exciting time for us and this adventure book was the perfect start to our new adventure. The brown pages are big enough to fit a good amount on each page. There are no plastic protectors. It is more like a scrapbook than a photo album. I love it. It looks just like the one from Up. Well worth it!" —Sara PepasGet it from Amazon for $13.69. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This was a birthday gift for my boyfriend and he loved it. I love most how you can hang it up or you can leave it as a regular picture frame. It’s a great, sentimental gift." —Jalonda StokesGet it from Amazon for $24.99. | Amazon, amazon.comThis set includes everything you need to make miniature hamburgers, sushi, doughnuts, and bento (including teeny, tiny utensils!). Promising review: "I love these. They're fun for kids and adults to make." —KristinaGet them from Amazon for $22.99. | Tiny Portrait ProjectGet it from Tiny Portrait Project on Etsy for $15+ (available with up to ten people). | AmazonPromising review: "This was a gift for my stepfather and he loves it! He loves recording the different beers he’s tasted, and this guide is simple but great with descriptions of flavors and tasting notes." —Deanna Wegman Get it from Amazon for $8.10. | AmazonGet six of the produce pairs for $10.99 and the six candy pair pack for $14.99, both from Amazon. | AmazonPromising review: "I got these as a gift for a family member that is a wine aficionado, partly for a laugh but also for the great concept. When she opened them, I did get a huge laugh and she was amazed at the concept. I also received confirmation from her that they work wonders and truly provide an airtight seal." —ThomasGet a set of six from Amazon for $16.97. | AmazonPromising review: "This was a little bit of a gag gift for some friends but they absolutely adore it. I receive messages all the time from the husband saying how much he loves it and that it's relaxing and helps calm him down after his high stress job. The images are hilarious and true." —Marina F.Get it from Amazon for $8.99. | instagram.com / Via @chuaochocolatier, Via @chuaochocolatierThere's also potato chip chocolate, spicy chocolate, honeycomb chocolate, and croissant-inspired chocolate. Promising review: "This is just what was needed to lighten up my fiancé's Wednesday. She loved every flavor, glass of wine in hand! It came shipped in a cool package with ice packs – I live in southern Nevada where it's triple digits outside, so I was expecting to have to put the chocolates in the fridge. But nope, they came cold and dry! The best ordering experience." —Nick AvelliGet a set of eight from Amazon for $16.95. | AmazonPromising review: "This is a great chill date night activity. We do a page every date night and we're still going after two years. :) It gives us something to look forward to doing together and starts up great conversations." —Allie MorenoGet it from Amazon for $9.35. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I got this toy 10 months ago for my dog and it is still going strong! It's filled with a lot of questions and places to put pictures and is all organized from beginning to end of the pregnancy. She has spent hours working in it and it's being treated almost as a personal journal, which we'll one day show our children. You can't beat that price.
