Title Headline: 48 Practical Things To Buy That'll Help You Feel More Like A Grown-Up
Short Description Sub Headline: See, Mom? I'm Tom Hanks in Sleepless In Seattle, not Tom Hanks in Big.
Content Body: Shopping | 48 Practical Things To Buy That'll Help You Feel More Like A Grown-Up | See, Mom? I'm Tom Hanks in Sleepless In Seattle, not Tom Hanks in Big. | Posted on January 22, 2020, 14:01 GMT | January 22, 2020, 14:01 GMT | Heather BragaBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Heather Braga / BuzzFeed, AmazonI'm obsessed with candles, so it was a no-brainer for my husband to gift me this surprisingly super fun gadget for Christmas. It's really simple to use and charge, and it really works! I'll never have to buy another lighter again.Promising review: "This is seriously the coolest device of my winter holiday. It makes lighting candles a breeze. Yes, there is a weird crackling noise, but that's a super minor annoyance. It's a super intuitive device. Plus the lighter with the USB (included), charge for a bit, then pop it open and light ALL THE THINGS; well, candles. I don't know how well it lights cigarettes or whatever. However, for my personal intended use, it's awesome!" —Jee WGet it from Amazon for $13.99. | AmazonPromising review: "I ordered this planner because it had everything I required of my weekly planner: Month at a glance; week at a glance; section at the end of each month for notes; mission board and even a straight edge ruler was included! The binding is very sturdy, like a hardcover book and not flimsy like many other planners being sold. There's also a section with pockets to hold my stickers. After many years of using Outlook, CRM, etc, sometimes it's just nice to go back to what has always worked well since the beginning of time! Why complicate things right? I also believe it's much better to write instead of type when it comes to goals and tasks. It helps our brains work better in the long run." —Pershing140Get it from Amazon for $14.99+ (available in two styles). | | AmazonPromising review: "These work amazingly well. I was surprised that you can charge and use them at the same time. I use them on planes to listen to the in-flight entertainment with my AirPods. I also use them to listen to music on my laptop with my AirPods. They work really well. Now, I don't have to carry my wired earbuds with me when I travel anymore. They really work as advertised. I have not had any issues with them since I started using them." —RPLGet it from Amazon for $40.49+ (available in three options). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Abby Kass / BuzzFeed, AmazonIt's the thinnest and lightest Kindle Amazon has released to date! And — as is made abundantly clear by the photo above — it's 100% waterproof. Promising review: "I love the fact that I can read on this Kindle in both daylight and dim light conditions. It is so light and compact, which makes it easy to hold, easy to travel with, and the battery lasts forever. I love it." —Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $129.99.And check out our full breakdown of the Kindle Paperwhite here. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Billie / Via instagram.com, BillieBillie is a fantastic subscription service that let's you choose how often you need your razor refills then delivers them right to your doorstep. I recently tried my first Billie razor and, OMG, my legs have never been smoother. They seriously have a handle style for everyone — including their new "Glow" razor that, you guessed it, glows in the dark! My coworker Rachel Dunkel is also a BIG fan of Billie razors and their other products. Here's what she had to say:"For the last five years or so, I haven't cared that much about shaving. I'd let my legs and pits grow into a (beautiful!) forest, but whenever I craved a nice, smooth shave and picked up a razor from the drugstore, I'd end up disappointed. Even with more expensive razor brands, I'd still be prickly and end up regretting ever shaving in the first place. I have never, ever had that problem with Billie. Ever since trying their razors and shave cream, I've actually *wanted* to keep up with shaving. You get a ridiculously smooth result on the first go, even if your hair is super grown out. But most importantly, it STAYS that way for way longer than with other brands. With Billie, it actually feels worth the time and money to shave, something that I could never say about any other razor."Check out our full review on the Billie razor subscription here.Get it from Billie for $9+ (available in six colors). | amazon.com, AmazonHonestly, no matter which version of the Dyson stick vacuum you purchase, I can promise you'll be satisfied with the results. I've used a variety of 'em and I can't say enough good things about the product. It doesn't hurt my back to use for an extended period of the time, the battery lasts long enough to clean my entire apartment, and it simply just WORKS. We have ours mounted in a narrow spot alongside our fridge — it's really easy to keep in plain sight without being an eyesore.Promising review: "I love this vacuum. The V10 doesn't disappoint. While it's weird to get used to holding this tiny piece of machinery, it really does an amazing job. It was incredible how much dog fur it picked up! I was pretty grossed out to be honest, to think I lived in this atmosphere for this long 'thinking' it was clean is nuts! I love all the attachments too, they are all top notch and well made. I feel like I can tackle my entire house with this bad boy. AND it's lightweight! I use it on the lowest setting and it still picks up a ton. I don't think I'll ever need the high or medium setting. But I did try the highest setting for a few seconds and literally felt like the vacuum was ATTACHED to the floor, that's how hard it sucked (in a good way)!" —Matthew MintunGet the V10 from Amazon for $349+ (available in three styles). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer / BuzzFeedMy fellow BuzzFeed editor Maitland Quitmeyer loves this thing. Here's what she had to say:"The acne scars on my cheeks from a series of breakouts are fading fast, and I get new acne very rarely — they're more like a pimple here and there occasionally when I have to fly somewhere (curse you, dry airplanes) or get stressed or.... who even knows why my skin freaks out sometimes. Never thought I'd ever put a no-makeup selfie on the internet, but that's how much I love this thing." Check out our full review of the FOREO LUNA Mini 2 here!Get it from Amazon for $139+ (available in six colors). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising Review: "LOVE THESE! They are a beautiful shade of gray, well-made and a perfect price! I ordered these to help protect against hair-breakage and I've already noticed a huge difference!!!" —shawnellnewberryGet them from Amazon for $9.98 (available in three sizes and 16 colors) | AmazonPromising review: "These are wonderful socks. Soft and warm and not itchy at all like socks with such a high percentage of wool can be. They fit perfectly, hugging your foot instead of slipping around like a sloppy mess. Love the muted colors as well. Thinking about getting more in other colors!" —Debra A. ScottGet a five-pair pack from Amazon for $11.99 (available in 11 styles). | AmazonPromising review: "I was kind of shocked at how good quality these straws are! They come in a neat little baggie that you can store them in, and the straw cleaner as well! I don't usually leave reviews on products (even if I really like them), but they donate 100% of the proceeds of your order to OCEANA if you leave a review, and that's a HUGE plus for me. So not only do I really like the product, I get to share the good news through this review AND my payment gets donated to OCEANA. I really really appreciate that. 10/10 product!" —Amazon CustomerGet a pack of 10 from Amazon for $8.95. | amazon.comMy sister bought this for me and I'm obsessed with it — which is why I know it's awesome! It's my favorite thing to start my pampering with, but I also use it in the morning before I apply any makeup. All you have to do is pop the separate roller piece into your freezer and you'll be ready to de-puff in no time.Promising review: "Extremely affordable and feels great on my face right when I wake up in the morning!! I can feel the difference after a couple of rolls along my puffy eyes and face. It soothes my puffiness with the cold but bearable feeling. And it does stay cool for a good amount of time. Best thing is its not a watery mess." —Tammy N.Get it from Amazon for $11.99 (available in eight colors). | AmazonI have this little foam roller and use it almost every night. I roll my spine over it and it releases all the tension in a series of very satisfying cracks. Get one — add it into your pre-bedtime ritual!Promising review: "My chiropractor recommended I buy the 36" version of this for some daily routine back stretching to do at home. This product has been amazing for stretching, and massaging sore muscles throughout my back and shoulders. I feel very supported by this roller and have had no issues with it thus far. I weigh 200 pounds and have yet to damage this roller after weeks of use. Overall very pleased with this product. And at such a great price, I honestly can't find a single negative remark to note about it." —Luke MarrsGet it from Amazon for $8.45+ (available in four sizes and seven styles). | AmazonYou can even pop these in the washing machine for a thorough cleaning.Promising review: "After my husband sliced his finger on our mandolin I decided to check out these gloves. We are both very impressed with how well they work. The company who sells these is also wonderful — they sent a follow-up email to ensure that we liked the gloves and would have replaced or refunded our money if we weren't happy. The only thing I was concerned about when I ordered the gloves was if I was buying the right size. My husband and I have different hand sizes, but the medium is working well for both of us. And knowing that they would send a different size free of charge was wonderful. Now we don't have to worry about slicing off our fingers!" —That Author Guy's WifeGet them from Amazon for $11.49 (available in sizes S—XL). | amazon.comPromising review: "Love how little space these take up. My closet is pretty small so getting these types of hangers was a must. Clothes don’t slip from the hangers which is nice because with the plastic ones, my tank tops and dresses would always fall off. You can even hang pants too. " —AmazonianCheck out our deep dive on the AmazonBasics Velvet Suit Hangers here!Get them from Amazon for $14.99+ (available in packs of 30, 50, or 100 and three colors) | Amazon, amazon.comI have one of these cool cups and have been really impressed with it. I recently used it early one morning when I was craving a cup of hot tea but had to run some errands. It pops open really easily, feels very durable, and keeps my drink hot.Promising review: "Love this cup. I was originally turned off to it due to the size of the top section, however it's not as big as it looks online and it's the perfect size. It will fit most purses but not likely women's pant pockets. After filling it with water I shook the cup and there was no leaking. Even after I finished my latte and collapsed the cup there was no residue leakage at all. The cup didn't get excessively hot either. The cup also had mL markers on the inside which is wonderful. I highly recommend this product!" —HRGet it from Amazon for $15 (available in 4 sizes and 16 colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I have incredibly fine hair that's super thick and frizzy. It's kind of a nightmare. My hair is prone to monster knots- I came back from summer camp once with a mat in my hair like a dog. Other hair brushes tend to rip my hair out because of the knotty-ness and fine strands. This brush is fantastic. The only thing I don't like about it is it took me 25 years to find it. I can actually brush my hair with minimal pain and hair loss. It works like a charm and I can brush my hair quicker and more thoroughly than with any other brush I've used." —Amazon CustomerGet a set of two from Amazon for $14.47+ (available in three styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comThis seemingly average little cleaning pen is filled with a high-performance formula that cleans jewelry like nothing I've ever experienced. It contains micro-fine cleansers, polishing agents, and a polymer that will make your gems so shiny they'll nearly blind you. I've used it on my diamond rings, but it also works wonders on my cubic zirconia earrings. Check out my full review of the Connoisseurs 1050 Diamond Dazzle Stick.Promising review: "The center stone of my ring (an oval white sapphire) has been cloudy since shortly after I got it. I have to use a lot of hand sanitizer at work, which gets under the stone. This product was easy to use. The little brush gets under the stone really well (much better than a toothbrush). My ring looks like new." —FintanCatGet it from Amazon for $8.78. | MadewellI've gotten one of these as a gift and have given one to my sister as well. It's my favorite bag to date! It has a small pocket inside you can pop your phone into (or anything else you'd be looking to grab in a hurry) and has so much space. I've even fit my laptop into it! The straps are sturdy and I love that this version also has a chic suede stripe down the middle. The best part? You can add your initials for an extra special touch.Get it from Madewell for $158 (available in three colors). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Food52Promising review: "I love this apron! I’m a petite 5’3” and get why some similar sized people may feel it’s too big but I love the way it fits. It’s a heavier weight which makes it feel like a lot on my small frame at first but I don’t mind the extra length and feel very protected. Pot holder pockets still work length-wise for me and I have not gotten a stain or ruined my actual clothing since I got this. Maybe I’m a messier cook than most but other thinner, smaller aprons didn’t provide the same protection. It’s a bonus that it fits my tall husband too." —Caroline F.Get it from Food52 for $45 (available in one size and five colors). | Amazon, amazon.comMy dog personally hates the car, so taking all 80 pounds of him to the groomer is often a struggle (to say the least). By using this attachment he can clean up without feeling anxious. The unique wand is curved to provide full coverage while washing your pet. It also has an 8-foot-long flexible hose for extended reach and be used indoors or outdoors.Promising review: "Owners of long-haired/thick-coated breeds: This is what you've been looking for. I've waited over 20 years for this and have used everything from custom heads to kitchen wash heads. The water flow from this even at low pressure (40 psi) is excellent, adjustment on handle are well-thought-out, and this WILL get right through a thick undercoat." —Animal DoctorGet it from Amazon for $33.01. | shophavly / Via instagram.com, HavlyI recently picked up one of these towels and it is unbelievably soft. It's thicker than most of my towels but seemingly takes up less space. The loop to hang it seems super sturdy which is an added bonus. Definitely pick up a set for each of your parents.Get it from Havly for $44 (available in five styles). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "After multiple containers for my brown sugar and continuously throwing my brown sugar away due to giant hard lumps, I began to wonder why our brown sugar never lumped as a child. That's when I remembered a weird brown bear in our sugar, After a quick Google search I found this! I soaked it in water for 30 minutes and then added to my lumpy brown sugar...two days later there is not a single lump in my sugar! Yay!" —SneezeloafGet it from Amazon for $5.61. | quip / Via instagram.com, quip / Via instagram.comDoes you boast about being a minimalist? Or maybe you just have ZERO counter space? Then the Quip might just be the toothbrush of their dreams. It has a three-month battery life, comes with a wall mount and travel case, and is super quiet during use. I own one myself (as do my mom, mother-in-law, and father-in-law) and love how it encourages me to brush thoroughly.Promising review: "I truly love this toothbrush, feels great when done. Like the fact that it tells you when to move to the next quadrant. People in general do not take the two minutes to brush their teeth, much less concentrate on each quadrant and change the brush every three months. Anyway, I love it and will recommend it." —Maria S.Check out our full review of the Quip here.Get it from Quip for $25+ (available in eight colors and a variety of subscription plans). | amazon.com, AmazonIt combines six kitchen appliances in one, including a pressure cooker, slow cooker, rice cooker, sauté, steamer, and warmer.Promising review: "Of all of the purchases that I've ever made to add to my kitchen's efficiency and fun, this is the one thing I could not do without. I ordered it after making a decision to cook with fresh ingredients in order to make my meals healthier. It took me awhile to gather data from online forums and various cookbooks and 'how to' resources before I actually opened the box and began my discovery journey. It's been a delicious one, indeed, not to mention how much time I am saving in the process." —DarleneGet it from Amazon for $59+ (available in 3, 6, and 8 quarts). | Amazon, amazon.comOne little machine that can whip up hard-boiled eggs, poached eggs, scrambled eggs, and omelettes? Sounds magical! And let me tell you — it is. Get one of these egg-cellent appliances ASAP. Read our deep dive into the Dash Rapid Egg Cooker.Promising review: "If you are on the fence about getting one of these, GET ONE. It really is as easy as it sounds to have a perfectly cooked egg, no guesswork. Just have an ice bath ready next to the cooker and let the eggs sit for a minute or two in there...peels come right off :) Makes healthy eating a breeze in the morning! Where has this been all my life!??!?" —rebeccaGet it from Amazon for $17.35+ (available in five colors). | Amazon, amazon.comI have one of these bad boys and can validate that it is SO easy to use. I pop my phone into it when I get in the shower and click the lil' button on the front to start the cleaning process. You can also charge your phone while it's inside the machine. Fellow germaphobes — you can thank me later.Promising review: "Bought this along with a set of agar plates to test it for ourselves. We swabbed my daughter's and husband's phones before and after use. It does work. We are very happy with the product." —GingerGet it from Amazon for $79.95+ (available in 10 colors). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 32 Products That Have Wild Before-And-After Photos *And* Are Under $25
Short Description Sub Headline: These before-and-afters are truly a sight to behold.
Content Body: Shopping | 32 Products That Have Wild Before-And-After Photos *And* Are Under $25 | These before-and-afters are truly a sight to behold. | Posted on January 31, 2020, 00:00 GMT | January 31, 2020, 00:00 GMT | Rachel DunkelBuzzFeed Staff | | amazon.comPromising review: "This has completely changed the way I use my cast iron pan. I can cook whatever I want and know the pan will be as good as new. For people that worry about the seasoning on the pan, this definitely won't hurt a thing. Once I'm done cleaning, I'll shake off any excess water and then heat it on the stove top for a minute until its completely dry. I'll then put a a very light coating of oil on it and heat it up again and the pan will be good to go for the next use. My pan has never cooked better." —JoshGet it from Amazon for $15.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "My son wrote all over his brand new Lego table with blue Sharpie marker. I tried everything to remove the stain. This product is EASY. Its consistency is like glue. I added one coat, let it soak in for an hour or two, scrubbed with a scrub pad, rinsed, added a second coat, scrubbed, and rinsed. It's all gone. It's magic." —VickiGet it from Amazon for $10.99. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I used this product four times now, and it’s unbelievable how white my teeth already are. You also don’t get sensitive teeth from this like other whiteners. Love it!" —CarrieGet it from Amazon for $9.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "Does exactly what it's supposed to do. Keeps the power strip and all the connected power cables out of sight, neat and organized. The only challenge I had was the need to unplug everything to put the power strip inside the box and then re-route the power cables into the box. Once done though, I no longer found myself stepping on or kicking the power cords on the floor. This keeps them nice and neat and out of the way." —Mitchell BellGet it from Amazon for $19.97. | amazon.comFor best results, mix the clay with apple cider vinegar according to the directions.Promising review: "This clay mask is unbelievable. I saw a bunch of reports recommending it and decided to try for myself. I have moderate acne and this mask has lessened my breakouts dramatically. This mask has also assisted in getting rid of hyperpigmentation. Will definitely buy again in the near term and would recommend this to everyone." —Letsgetdangerous_Get it from Amazon for $12.95. | amazon.comPromising review: "Great product! I bought these to put in my nightstand drawer to store small things, as the drawer is very deep. I've got Chapstick, hand lotions, a small flashlight, and other bedside items in them so they're not just rolling around the drawer. I just bought some more for my bathroom vanity. They fit together nicely but also lift right out of each other. The plastic is sturdy, and they came individually wrapped to keep them from scratching." —SparkyjGet a six-piece set from Amazon for $14.99. | amazon.comThis product works in just *40 minutes*, but it's safe to leave overnight for maximum effectiveness (or if you're just feeling lazy).Promising review: "Simply UNBELIEVABLE. Fume-free and no gloves needed, but dissolves ANYTHING cooked on! I had not cleaned my oven EVER. I simply sprayed it on, shut the door overnight, and wiped it off with paper towels. I don't have to dread cleaning the oven ever again! You can use it for everyday spot cleaning and only have to let it sit for a couple hours for minor things. I used it on my broiler pan that would not scrub clean with even steel wool — no need to scrub ever again now! My crockpot leaked over the bowl and burned on inside of the heating chamber. I just sprayed, covered, and wiped in morning. I mainly bought it because of the color and because I was able to buy it used and save some money, but even at full price I would recommend it. Because of how the three shades can point in different directions, you can illuminate three different parts of a room with just the one lamp. It's like getting three lamps in one!" —AshleyGet it from Amazon for $74.99+ (available in three finishes). | AmazonPromising review: "My 'laundry room' is in my garage, which has that regular old garage floor, and I wanted something to not only separate the area, but also protect any clothing that may fall onto the floor. I bought this to place in front of the washer/dryer and not only does it serve its purpose, it also makes the area look a lot nicer. The material is nice and sturdy, and looks like it can be easily hosed down to clean." —HotRodPRGet it from Novogratz on Amazon for $17.19+ (available in seven sizes and two colors). | | AmazonPromising review: "Overall, these are well designed, sturdy chairs that are very easy to assemble and are comfortable, too. I would recommend these, especially at the present price." —Hugh K.Get a set of four from Amazon for $79.99+ (available in eight colors). | AmazonPromising review: "This is a great shelf system! Title Headline: 40 Cheap Things You Can Enjoy At Home While You're Getting Your Money's Worth On Rent
Short Description Sub Headline: Here's to avoiding spending lots of money on social interactions you didn't want to participate in anyway.
Content Body: Shopping | | Under $50 | 40 Cheap Things You Can Enjoy At Home While You're Getting Your Money's Worth On Rent | Here's to avoiding spending lots of money on social interactions you didn't want to participate in anyway. | Posted on January 29, 2020, 03:00 GMT | January 29, 2020, 03:00 GMT | Elizabeth LillyBuzzFeed Staff | | | | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review (for the diffuser): "I loved this product! As you can see the light button has rubbed off a bit because I use it so much! It has all colors of the rainbow, it goes for 11 hours, is easy to clean, and it looks great. Other diffusers I just couldn’t say the same about. The only thing that I do have to warn is that you need to be careful about the oils you put in it or it can be ruined (from experience). This has lasted me sooo long and I am going to buy again! My sister bought first then I did she was bummed when hers no longer worked (from the bad oils)! Definitely recommend!!" —Happy Mom of 3Get them from Amazon: diffuser for $15.99+ (available in four colors) and eight essential oils for $14.95 | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "These masks are amazing!!! Having 'ice pick' scars left over from acne I was told that I'd have to pay for expensive laser therapy because the body can't produce enough collagen to heal deep scars. I've been using these masks for two months and I've seen SIGNIFICANT reduction in my scars. They are almost completely gone!" —ShaunGet them from Amazon for $10.99. | amazon.com, AmazonGet it from Amazon for $9.59+ (available in seven styles).Though if you're more into The Office, check out some versions with Prison Mike and Dwight wearing the CPR dummy mask. | AmazonGet three pens of varying brush sizes from Amazon for $6.99. | AmazonGet them from Amazon for $5.99+ (available in gold or black). | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "Our son has been into comic drawing lately and he would draw his own lines/boxes on paper he stapled together! I saw this book while Christmas shopping and thought it would be great for him. He loves it!" —Ebiel and Erica CamachoGet it from Amazon for $5.99. | Amazon, amazon.comBTW, lots of reviewers have found success mixing this powder mask with organic ACV.Promising review: "I use the clay mask along with apple cider vinegar and let it sit on my face for 20–30 mins. I have been using it every single day but if you have sensitive skin, I don't recommend that. Tbh I have not been eating healthy 24/7 but it still works. Some days I forgot to put in on but in total I have used this mask over 10x. Just be patient and give it time." —Delandia StevensonGet it from Amazon for $9.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I have two cats, tried a de-shedder brush but they hate it and hide the second I take it out, so I was looking for other options and saw these gloves — it turned out to be a life-changer! To my surprise, cats absolutely love it! They even purr and roll around to make sure I didn't miss a spot. The layer of fur is easy to peel off from the glove and the more you collect the easier it gets. Now I am able to bru­sh my cats every oth­er day, since they enjoy it so much, which means less fur on my clothes and everywh­ere else. Very satisfied with this product and would recommend it to cat owners." —YanaGet a pair from Amazon for $12.99 (available in two colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I use this whenever I feel tired, and always after I’ve cleansed my face. I use rubbing alcohol to clean it after use and then put it back in the freezer in its own ziplock. I notice it’s helped with the redness in my face and it also helped when I’ve had migraines. It starts behind my eye so I roll it over whichever side of my head is in pain and it seems to help." —maihiroGet it from Amazon for $11.99+ (available in eight color combos).

Content Body: Shopping | | Gift Ideas | 42 Of The Best Valentine's Day Gifts For Men | Love language: gift giving. | Posted on January 30, 2020, 10:00 GMT | January 30, 2020, 10:00 GMT | Alexandra NapoliBuzzFeed Staff | | Hill CitySince it's on the thinner side, it can be packed easily for any and every vacay you two take together.Promising review: "This jacket will remain a featured item in my wardrobe for a long time. Well-fitting and flexible to be worn for active use or while out and about. I've worked out in this jacket, worn it to work events, and slipped it on for a cool evening out with the family. It's lightweight, easily packable, looks cool, and keeps you dry in a downpour. You can't ask for more in a lightweight rain jacket." —Luke513Get it from Hill City for $148 (available in sizes S–XXL and three colors). | Hill CityPromising review: "They have been my go-to weekend pants, went for a casual bike ride, went to museums, to the playground with my son and I'm taking them running as well. I can't think of anything that performs better; I love that they feel windproof and just the right temperature to have while doing some light exercise; I love how they come tight on the ankles which makes them perfect for biking around since the pants won't get stuck or stained with the bike chain." —gossler88Get them from Hill City for $98 (available in sizes S–XXL and three colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comHere's what a past BuzzFeed writer has to say about it: “I’ve had my Timex easy reader watch for close to two years now and it is STILL ticking along with no issues. The expandable band makes it super easy to put on and take off. And the gold tone still looks stunning after so many wears — because I rock it multiple times a week. It is simple to set the date and time, and the night-light feature is useful whenever I need a little assistance seeing the watch’s face. If you are looking for an affordable watch that is still super stylish, this is the PERFECT choice.” —Treye Green  Get it from Amazon for $35.75+ (available in three finishes). | AmazonPromising review: "I ordered two of these to display our record collection, which was stacked under our buffet. I no longer wanted our vinyl stacked and I was sick and tired of others flipping through them on the floor and then leaving them in a state of chaos. I have to say, we absolutely love these and will likely be purchasing more in the near future! They have exceeded my expectations. I love the practical, minimalist design. And my friends can now easily flip through our collection and play records without using our floor." —Kaci B.Get it from Amazon for $25+ (available in six finishes and two sizes). | NisoloPromising review: "I got these for my husband for Christmas and he's worn them almost every day. He loves the character of the waxed canvas and how it looks over time. They've broken in and fit him like a glove. The soles are super durable and great when he's caught in unexpected rain." —Sarah C.Get them from Nisolo for $288 (available in sizes 8–13 and five colors). | Uncommon GoodsThis kit makes 1 gallon and includes 100% malt extract, world-class specialty grains, fresh hop pellets, and high-quality yeast. This malty ale has a light copper hue, subtle bitterness from its Perle and Mt. Hood hops, caramel sweetness, and a clean, dry finish. Promising review: "My brother has always been interested in beer. This kit will allow him to easily create his own first batch; he will be so proud that he made his own beer at home!" —AdamGet it from Uncommon Goods for $45. | AmazonPromising review: "I like meditation but usually do it lying down. However, I recently got a puppy and decided to try this meditation pillow in order to relieve the back and neck pain I always experience while sitting on the floor for any reason. It worked wonders! I have tried other pillows like this in the past with no success. This one is superior in design, construction, height, and support. I will now also use it for meditation as well as for interacting with my puppy while playing on the floor with him. An attractive, fantastic pillow!" —Barbara CutreraGet it from Amazon for $29.99+ (available in six colors and two sizes).And check out our picks for the best meditation cushions on BuzzFeed Reviews! | Men's WarehousePromising review: "Exactly what I needed to add to and complement my wardrobe! The color, fit, and style of this jacket catches the eye and turns heads whenever I wear it." —Robert LGet it from Men's Warehouse for $72 (originally $179; available in sizes S–XXL and three colors). | AmazonPromising review: "This isa very solid piece. It's well-constructed and easily allows for straight lines. It comes with a useful guide with illustrations and is in an impressive package altogether. Overall great value for the price." —C in KSGet it from Amazon for $13.90. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "If you have the snow raining on your shirt every day from your amazing manly beard then you need to buy this stuff. It really helped hydrate and get my beard to a place where there is no beard dandruff to speak of. Keep your beard happy. Your shirt will thank you." —Colt and MissyGet it from Amazon for $12.22. | TicketmasterWhether your love likes to jam out to music or cheer in the stands of their favorite sport team's stadium, this a gift card will have you covered.Get it from Ticketmaster for $5–$500 (available as a digital or physical card). | Kayla Suazo/BuzzFeedHe can receive bags biweekly or monthly, with a selection from over 50+ countries. All ingredients are sourced via sustainable farming practices and as soon as you place the order, the beans are roasted, meaning he'll always get a fresh batch. AKA, Atlas is the subscription he's been dreaming of.Promising review: "My first observation after opening the box was the smell. It smells FAN-FREAKIN'-TASTIC. It also comes with sweet postcards from the cities where the batches are from, so the entire experience feels so lovely and personal. As for the coffee itself, it's heavenly. I am used to store-bought coffee — which yes, is fine — but both of these tasted incredibly fresh and different from each other. The Peruvian coffee has this dark, almost chocolate taste to it, so I imagine it would be delicious with a morning sweet treat (maybe I should start eating pie every day?). The Colombian batch, on the other hand, was a little lighter roast-wise but still had delicious notes of rich sweetness. TL;DR: both of them were incredible both in taste and quality." —Kayla SuazoGet a subscription from Atlas for $9+/month.And check out our full review of the Atlas coffee subscription here. | YetiPromising review: "Perfect for my daily lunch. I work road construction and it fits all my goodies and keeps them cool. Love the magnetic closure so nothing sneaks out when it gets moved or tossed around." —KayKay4Get it from Yeti for $79.99 (available in three colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: “I ordered a size 9, as there was no size 8.5. It fit just like an 8.5, which was perfect! My husband says that these shoes are extremely comfortable. Normally when buying a new pair of shoes, the heel can be stiff or too thin. These shoes have padding where the heal is to give you that extra bit of comfort.” —BH&H  Get them from Amazon for $19.99+ (available in sizes 6-12.5 and 20 colors). | amazon.com, Hannah Loewentheil/BuzzFeedOne kit gets you garlic, kashmiri chili powder, crushed red pepper, cinnamon powder, smoked paprika, cumin seed, oregano, rosemary, cloves, turmeric, granulated onion, dark chili powder, ground yellow mustard, green cardamom powder, coriander seed, herbs de provence, fennel seed, and ground ginger.Promising review: "The variety and quality of each spice is amazing. I haven’t been able to try every one yet, but the red pepper was amazing, the smoked paprika really popped, and our oatmeal was brought to another level with the cinnamon. I'm looking forward to using all these spices and the branding is so cute." —Hamilton M.Get the kit from Amazon for $95. And check out our review on the Spicewalla essential spices kit! | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I've been wearing these as my black dress shoes for almost a year. These have seen business meetings, the dance floor, snow, rain, broken glass, and just about any condition short of mountain hiking. They've held up very well and still look new after a polishing. Scuffs buff out very easily and the shoe doesn't have any creases from where my toe bends. It's a very high quality shoe." —Amazon CustomerGet them from Amazon for $68+ (available in sizes 7–17 and four colors; wide sizes also available). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Abby Kass / BuzzFeed, AmazonIt's the thinnest and lightest Kindle Amazon has released to date! And — as is made abundantly clear by the photo above — it's 100% waterproof. Promising review: "I love the fact that I can read on this Kindle in both daylight and dim light conditions. It is so light and compact, which makes it easy to hold, easy to travel with, and the battery lasts forever. I love it." —Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $129.99+ (available in two colors).And check out our full breakdown of the Kindle Paperwhite here. | JCrewGet it from J.Crew for $148 (available in sizes XS–XXL and three colors). | AmazonPromising review: "Bought this for my boyfriend and he loves it! It's thin so it fits into pant pockets more suitably. Has multiple compartments for cash and IDs. Tight enough fit in the compartments where you won't loose any thing you put in it." —RachelGet it from Amazon for $34. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 24 Organization And Storage Products You Can Get On Amazon That People Actually Swear By
Short Description Sub Headline: Your home is about to be a palace of organization.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | Amazon | 24 Organization And Storage Products You Can Get On Amazon That People Actually Swear By | Your home is about to be a palace of organization. | Posted on January 04, 2020, 11:31 GMT | January 04, 2020, 11:31 GMT | Harper HendricksonBuzzFeed Staff | | | | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "Whether you’re a college student or a professional that needs something for the office, this shredder doesn’t disappoint. I really like the cross-cut feature because it utilizes more bin space. This means that it’ll be able to hold more shreds of paper. It’s powerful and reliable, and I haven’t had any problems with it since. I use it quite often and have only had to empty it once (out of the four months I’ve had it for). Its compact size makes it perfect for storing in tight spaces." —HandsONPrice: $36.99 | AmazonPromising review: "Best product I have bought in a long time. Keeps the kitchen cabinet so organized, you don't have to spend an hour searching for the right lid for a container." —DebbyPrice: $34.93 (set of 12) | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I absolutely love these baskets! They are a great storage solution for a smaller bathrooms or honestly any room. My toilet paper rolls fit well. It can do three across with a little room. Not quite long enough for four but that’s fine. It was nice it came with all the hardware to hang them all you needed was a drill or screwdriver." —MeganFromLVPrice: $35.21 | AmazonPlus, it has a snap-lock lid to keep odor to a minimum. Each bin holds up to eight pounds of dry pet food. It also includes a 1.5 cup food scoop.Promising review: "I love it. It is very useful storage for my small dog's food, treats, and other items. I would recommend this to my friends. It is so simple to assemble too." —Very PleasedPrice: $69.99 | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I have three cats, and now I wonder why I waited so long to invest in this sort of product. I originally was looking at other brands, but the ratings were not very good. I was worried I would have picky cats that would choose not to use the new scary box but they all have loved it! As another reviewer said, I also purchased the Merry Products Cat Washroom to house the unit. It hides it perfectly, and it looks nice in a living area rather then trying to find a place to hide a box. Additionally, I also purchased a forever tray to use instead of having to repeatedly buy disposable trays. I also bought micro crystals that are easier on the paws (two of my kitties were rescued and had previously been declawed). If you have cats or even one cat, this really is a great product, and a good investment in your time and home." —Jessica VaughnPrice: the self-cleaning litter box for $139.95 and the housing unit for $144.99 | AmazonPromising review: "The storage area is pretty big and the whole piece feels it was made with quality materials. I think it will last for a long time. I like the fact that the legs are short to minimize damage, which is what happened to my old ottoman. The lid opens effortlessly thanks to the lift cylinders. Overall we are very please with this piece, and it looks really nice in my living room." —DanielPrice: $159.90 | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "This product is a life changer! Perfect size for tv, cable, WiFi, Xbox, and sound tower wires. See my photos! So happy!" —BernicePrice: $25.95 (four colors) | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Short Description Sub Headline: Do you need these? Yes. Everyone does.
Content Body: Shopping | 26 Things I'm All Of A Sudden Realizing Basically Every Single Person Needs | Do you need these? Yes. Everyone does. | Posted on January 05, 2020, 11:00 GMT | January 05, 2020, 11:00 GMT | Mallory MowerBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I’ve tried so many brands of pimple spots, and these are hands-down the best on the market. I’m a performer at Walt Disney World, and a clear complexion is required. Last night, I put these on a few acne problems (a small cyst, a whitehead, and a pimple I shouldn’t have picked and has been a bump for about three weeks now). I just woke up and am writing this review in disbelief. THEY'RE FLAT! Gone! All of them! I could cry I’m so happy. The packaging is also ideal because it allows you to conveniently and easily peel the stickers off without stretching them out or folding them back on themselves. Do yourself and your complexion a huge favor! Have these on hand for a stubborn zit when you really need help. Make sure you apply them to completely clean and dry skin." —CaitlynGet a 40-pack from Amazon for $8.50. | amazon.comPromising review: "After seeing it say it only takes two minutes (mine was closer to four) I thought there was no way it would work. But I can literally hear how much easier the disposal spins. I can see the metal which used to be black. I'm in an apartment where it has probably never been cleaned. I didn't even know the second sink drain was white until this. It had a layer of brown gunk. Simply amazing, I'm shocked how well this stuff works." —J. PeaceGet a pack of four from Amazon for $5.94. | | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I bought this in charcoal and lost it on a trip, so I bought the exact color again because I missed it so much. Now I'm back to buy it in more colors. It is thick (because it's a watch cap) but I wear it year round in Dallas or Chicago. The fit is snug to the point that I can sling it back without it falling off and it fits over my afro or straight hair the same and doesn't lose is stretch after washing. This is my favorite hat." —CEGet it from Amazon for $14.99 (available in 36 colors). | amazon.comPromising review: "I seriously can't believe how well these little tablets work. I had the most disgusting HydroFlask coffee mug – I tried everything. Bottle brush, different kinds of soap, vinegar, EVERYTHING, and there was still a seemingly impenetrable layer of black sludge inside. It grossed me out so much that I bought ANOTHER HydroFlask to replace it. Now eventually they both got black inside, so I tried these little magic tablets. I let a tablet sit in each of my mugs for an hour or two, and the black sludge rinsed out COMPLETELY, without even scrubbing. They look brand new. What a magical product. No weird smell or taste afterward, either. I liked it so much I used it on another HydroFlask I use primarily to hold my Bloody Mary mix in the fridge. I couldn't put anything else in it because it would always taste like spicy tomato juice. Bottle Bright to the rescue! No residual smell or taste anymore. AMAZING AMAZING AMAZING." —Amazon CustomerGet a pack of 12 from Amazon for $8. | BlissPromising review: "This is hands down the best cleanser I have ever used. I have cystic acne and this is the only cleanser that I have used that has gotten rid of all of my cystic acne. I had to go a week without this a couple weeks ago and my cystic acne came back and within a couple days of using this again, it has all disappeared. This is amazing." —Michelle C.Get it from Bliss for $12. | amazon.comPromising review: "Oh man, this stuff is awesome! I sprayed and left it on overnight. I had no idea what to expect. I took a paper towel and started wiping out the oven. The grime just melted away. I am VERY pleased!" —KsGrl444Get it from Amazon for $5.99. | AmazonThis includes a ventilated case for storage.Promising review: "OK, this is DEFINITELY not a gimmick! Follow the instructions and this will save you time and sanity in the kitchen! Roll it with minimal pressure and it works like a champ. It also rinses very easily and dries quick. The case has holes on either end to ensure it dries completely in between uses when you toss it in a drawer. I will never hand/knife smash garlic and fight with those pesky skins sticking to everything ever again." —ThatKasperGet it from Amazon for $13.59. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 31 Gadgets You'll Probably Want To Try In 2020
Short Description Sub Headline: Inspector Gadget's got nothin' on you.
Content Body: Shopping | 31 Gadgets You'll Probably Want To Try In 2020 | Inspector Gadget's got nothin' on you. | Posted on January 06, 2020, 18:13 GMT | January 06, 2020, 18:13 GMT | Kat AngusBuzzFeed Staff, Canada | Heather BragaBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Heather Braga / BuzzFeed, Amazon / Via amazon.caI'm obsessed with candles, so it was a no-brainer for my husband to gift me this surprisingly super fun gadget for Christmas. It's really simple to use and charge, and it really works! I'll never have to buy another lighter again.Get it from Amazon Canada for $37.56. | Amazon / Via amazon.caWe've all been there — making our coffee or tea only to set it down and forget about until it's cooled down completely. Thanks to this mug warmer none of us ever have to suffer through another cold cup of caffeine again! Get it from Amazon Canada for $27.25. | | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Amazon / Via amazon.ca, BuzzFeedCheck out our full review of the John Frieda hot brush for more info!Get it from Amazon Canada for $38.79. | AmazonGet it from Amazon Canada for $50.61+ (available in two options). | Amazon / Via amazon.caIncludes a Fujifilm Instax Mini 9 Camera (with a selfie mirror!), 20 sheets of film, 10 sheets of rainbow film, 20 sticker frames, and a leather carrying case.Get it from Amazon Canada for $139.99+ (available in five colour combos; also available with just the camera). | Amazon / Via amazon.caI have one of these bad boys and can validate that it is SO easy to use. I pop my phone into it when I get in the shower and click the lil' button on the front to start the cleaning process. You can also charge your phone while it's inside the machine. Fellow germaphobes — you can thank me later.Get it from Amazon Canada for $105.45 (available in nine colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $29.99. | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $75.30. | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $68.99. | Amazon / Via amazon.caIt can be used as a pressure cooker, slow cooker, rice cooker, and egg cooker, with the ability to sauté, steam, and warm. Read all about why the Instant Pot is changing how we cook in my BuzzFeed coworker's review. Get it from Amazon Canada for $79.97+ (available in three sizes). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Abby Kass / BuzzFeed, Amazon / Via amazon.caIt's the thinnest and lightest Kindle Amazon has released to date! And — as is made abundantly clear by the photo above — it's 100% waterproof. Get it from Amazon Canada for $139.99+ (also available with 32GB of memory).And check out our full breakdown of the Kindle Paperwhite here. | Amazon / Via amazon.caThis is the number one thing on my wish list right now — it's so cool and I'm constantly staring at it in stores. I love that it has the ability to transform into a piece of art but also act as a room's main source of entertainment.Get it from Amazon Canada for $1297.99+ (available in four sizes). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer / BuzzFeedMy fellow BuzzFeed editor Maitland Quitmeyer loves this thing. Here's what she had to say:"The acne scars on my cheeks from a series of breakouts are fading fast, and I get new acne very rarely — they're more like a pimple here and there occasionally when I have to fly somewhere (curse you, dry airplanes) or get stressed or.... who even knows why my skin freaks out sometimes. Never thought I'd ever put a no-makeup selfie on the internet, but that's how much I love this thing." Check out our full review of the FOREO LUNA Mini 2 here!Get it from Amazon Canada for $179 (available in six colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caEvery gamer needs a fancy mouse! This one has light features that can be customized to WHATEVER colour they want, seven programmable mouse buttons, five default DPI levels, and four adjusting polling rate levels. Even if you have no idea what that means, the gamer in your home will simply be in awe over the features.Available from Amazon Canada for $20.29 (available in three styles). | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $29.91. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Heather Braga / BuzzFeed, Amazon / Via amazon.caFrom the moment I put the headset over my eyes I thought "Wow, I never have to leave the house again!!!" I'm personally more introverted, but I still enjoy spending time with family and friends. The Quest has been a great way for me to have a good time interacting with my loved ones without feeling overwhelmed by TOO much chatter. I brought it to Thanksgiving and we had a blast taking turns playing with it. More recently my sister and her boyfriend came over and we spent hours giggling watching one another play. Super fun!Get it from Amazon Canada for $199.99. | instagram.com / Via virzoom, instagram.com / Via virzoomGet it from Amazon Canada for $148.25. | Amazon / Via amazon.caMy dad and I tested out this watch and let me tell you — it's INTENSE. I workout regularly and this bad boy will definitely keep me in check going forward. It syncs up to an app on your phone that provides you with very detailed statistics on your cardio load, muscle load, and more. It has TONS of workouts you can track ranging from an outdoor walk and golfing to indoor cycling and long distance running. If you're looking to take your workouts to the next level, this will be quickly become part of your routine.Get it from Amazon Canada for $337.75+ (available in sizes S–L and five colours). | Amazon / Via amazon.caHonestly, no matter which version of the Dyson stick vacuum you purchase, I can promise you'll be satisfied with the results. I've used a variety of 'em and I can't say enough good things about the product. It doesn't hurt my back to use for an extended period of the time, the battery lasts long enough to clean my entire apartment, and it simply just WORKS. We have ours mounted in a narrow spot alongside our fridge — it's really easy to keep in plain sight without being an eyesore.Get the V10 from Amazon Canada for $599.97. | Amazon / Via amazon.caGet it from Amazon Canada for $144.49. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 35 Things Reviewers Say Are Actually So Comfortable
Short Description Sub Headline: Honestly, I'm at the point in my life where I don't even want to buy something if it's not comfortable.
Content Body: Shopping | | Clothing | 35 Things Reviewers Say Are Actually So Comfortable | Honestly, I'm at the point in my life where I don't even want to buy something if it's not comfortable. | Posted on January 06, 2020, 11:01 GMT | January 06, 2020, 11:01 GMT | Abby KassBuzzFeed Staff | | | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I LOVE this top. I’m 5’7 148 lbs (athletic build) 34DD, and I ordered a small. It’s oversized, so the small is perfect. I’d recommend sizing down one from your usual size. It's super comfortable, and since I ordered the white short sleeve, I can continue to wear it through spring. I’ll be ordering more colors!' —JoyGet it from Amazon for $18.99 (available in sizes S-2X and in 27 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This dress was everything! I’m a plus-size woman and generally wear a size 18. I bought a 2XL, and it fits perfectly. The material was very comfortable, even though it was on the cheaper end of the spectrum (which is expected because of the price). It's a beautiful dress, and I recommend it to all looking for an expensive classy dress" —Selena PooleGet it from Amazon for $26.99 (available in sizes S-3X and in 14 colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I love this skirt so much! I got a large (150lb, 5'4) and it fits me perfectly. I've had this black skirt for around nine months now and it has become a staple in my wardrobe! It has very VERY small pockets but pockets nonetheless, and it's very comfortable. The zipper is high quality, the material feels expensive, and I haven't noticed any fabric shrinkage or color fading! For me, it hits around mid-thigh." –livGet it from Amazon for $18.99 (available in sizes XS-2XL and 20 styles). | amazon.com, AmazonReviewers recommend ordering a half size down. Promising review: "These shoes are affordable, comfortable, and really cute! I had been looking for a loafer shoe, and these looked promising. They have a tiny heel that's just right, so not completely flat and not too high. The pointed toe makes these more modern and dressy. I took into consideration other reviews on size. I normally wear an 8 1/2 up to a 9, especially in dress shoes. I went with an 8 and they fit perfect, despite having a wider width foot. I plan on regularly wearing them to work. I'll update my review if they don't hold up, but they seem decently made." —VansGet them from Amazon for $34.99 (available in sizes 6-11 and in 35 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This is probably the most comfortable jacket I have ever owned! It’s soft and very warm! I survived 33 degrees New Mexico weather just fine in it!" —Ashley DranguetGet it from Amazon for $31.59 (available in sizes S-3X and in 15 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I love these leggings. I now have two pairs and will continue to buy from this brand. They fit perfectly and don't slide down or ride up as I work out. They also do well with wicking moisture and staying dry—no puddles of sweat to make me uncomfortable! I can't tell you how many times I've worn and washed them and they hold up perfectly. They're perfectly opaque too. No panty lines and definitely no patterns on my underwear showing through. I'm so impressed with 90 Degree by Reflex, especially for the price. They're my go-to workout leggings!" —IrvyGet them from Amazon for $22.99 (available in sizes XS-XL and in 27 styles).Read more about how great these leggings are here. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I love these jeans! So comfortable, so cute—just enough stretch so you can move around easily, without that saggy, baggy butt look after a few hours, lol. This is the first time I purchased this brand, so I didn't know how they would fit, but they are true to size. You can go by the size chart. I will definitely be purchasing more!" —tradergirl31Get them from Amazon for $16.50 (available in sizes 0-20 and in three styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I LOVE this wrap dress! The material is so soft and comfortable, and the dress is a perfect fit. It accentuates my curves and is super flattering. I always try to find dresses that would be work appropriate and also cute to wear if going out after work and on the weekends, and this fits the bill. It doesn't show too much cleavage and is the perfect length- a few inches above my knee." —TaylorGet it from Amazon for $24.99 (available in sizes S-XXL and in 22 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I really love this dress. It is very beautiful. It fit just right. I ordered an XL, and I am 203lbs, and I am busty, so the boob area was very comfortable. The dress itself was comfortable!! It did fall a little below my knees, which was a great length. It had a zipper on the side, but I didn’t use it because I didn’t even notice it had a zipper because the dress was stretchy. I will be buying again in other colors. I wore it for a wedding and received many compliments!!!!" —Joevonder JonesGet it from Amazon for $38.99 (available in sizes XS-3X and in 42 styles). | Nordstrom, Abby Kass / BuzzFeedPromising review: "I absolutely love these leggings. They're so comfortable, keep you tight, they are warm. Super stylish. I always get compliments on them." —Absolutely loveGet them from Nordstrom for $98 (available in sizes XS-XL, XS-XL petite, and 2X) or Spanx for $98+ (available in sizes XS-3X and in petite or regular). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "These are the most comfortable pants I’ve ever owned. I wear them to work, and people constantly ask where I got them from. The belt is a super cute touch. I bought several pairs in different colors, and they also have shorts that are just as cute! You won’t regret this buy!" —drdogmomGet it from Amazon for $24.99 (available in sizes XS-3X and in 35 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "This dress is very comfortable. It fit like a glove. I loved that I could dress it up or down. It could be a light spring dress or a winter dress. I love it" —LMSAGet it from Amazon for $36.99 (available in sizes XS-XXL and in 12 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comReviewers recommend ordering a half size down.Promising review: "These are cute and comfortable! I took the advice from other reviews and sized down. I am usually a 6.5 but got a 6, and they fit perfectly. I have wide feet, and these adjusted very well. I highly recommend to anyone looking for a simple but cute shoe." —ESGFGet it from Amazon for $35.99 (available in sizes 5.5-11 and in 57 colors and styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I could wear this every day. It's so soft and comfortable. I love these dresses, and I will be buying more but in different colors. It's great for date nights or for dressing up but also being comfortable. Title Headline: Here Are 11 Of The Best Diaries And Journals To Try In 2020
Short Description Sub Headline: New year, new notebook, new you.
Content Body: Shopping | Here Are 11 Of The Best Diaries And Journals To Try In 2020 | New year, new notebook, new you. | Posted on January 03, 2020, 12:00 GMT | January 03, 2020, 12:00 GMT | Amy GloverBuzzFeed Staff | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukSmall but practical, this lil' A5 diary is bursting with handy features from storage pockets to holiday planners. It comes with a whopping 288 stickers (yes, please), moveable dividers, a useful holiday planner that's perfect for organising big events in advance, and to-do lists (did we mention there's a separate address book, too?). You can easily see your weekly schedule at a glance with this diary, and the monthly planner section means you can set mid-term goals as well as documenting and organising your daily plans. Price: £11.49. | | | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukConnect to the accompanying app to upload everything from this notebook to the cloud, which you can then send directly to places like Slack, Dropbox, Google Docs, and more! Just write what you need to on its pages, save them to the cloud, wipe your words away, and start again. The app is available for both iOS and Android, making this next-level notebook the perfect futuristic tool for diarists and students alike. Price: £20.57. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukIf you're after a no-frills (but still pretty) journalling experience, this one-page-a-day diary is perfect. It does more or less what it says on the tin – you get given one page for each day of the year that you can fill with as much or as little writing as you'd like, and while there are some fun extras (like a gorge ribbon page marker and a handy yearly calendar), it's essentially a straightforward journal done well. An incredible buy for keen journallers or just someone who doesn't really go for all the bells and whistles, this diary is simple and beautiful! Price: £12. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukThe pages of this (pretty adorable) diary are dotted, giving you an easy guide to create your own grids, columns, and margins without restricting your space to doodle. Its genius pen-test page allows you to get your writing tools working without destroying a perfectly good sheet of writing paper (yesss), and there are key code pages and index pages too which will help you make sense of your notes. The diary comes with two colour-coded bookmarks, an expandable pocket, a pen loop, and its ethically-sourced vegan leather cover is bound durably enough to the notebook that it'll last the owner literally years. Ideal for doodlers, visual thinkers, or just anyone who wants to have more fun with their journalling, this diary can be used for low-key entries and Instagrammable artworks alike! It's available in teal, olive, charcoal, and pastel pink. Price: £18.97. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukWith plenty of space to map out each day of the week and a spare box to fill in your notes, this diary is a great way to keep on top of your schedule in style (and seeing as it's got a monthly goals section, it could even help you keep your new year's resolutions too!). The paper is thick enough to feel highly *luxurious* when you're writing on it, and there's a handy pocket at the back to help you store keepsakes like tickets or more practical stuff, like receipts. Price: £20.01. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukThis bad boy really has it all – blank tear-out lists, note pages, fill-in calendars, four useful pockets, and a pen loop. It gives you an overview of the week with plenty of room to fill in everything you need to do, and customers say there's space to write your reminders in too. The A6 size makes it incredibly portable, and it's so pretty it'll basically become decor when you put it on your desk! Available in two different designs, this incredibly well-reviewed diary is great for the busy person on the go. Price: £18.97. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukKeep track of your life and your garden with this beautifully-illustrated journal, which gives you space to track the things you've planted, gardening tips, and has loads of room for notes, too. Customers say it's given them everything they need to keep their plants on top form, and it's got a daily planner too, which you can use either for tracking growth or for writing down how your day went (or both!). Price: £14.08. | Amazon / Via amazon.co.ukThe design of this diary is stunning, and the recipes inside are pretty great too! With stickers, plenty of writing space, a selection of recipes ranging from desserts to mid-week meals, and some pages to help you plan out big events like birthdays and Christmas, this lil' guy seems to more or less do it all. Extras like conversions (great if you're baking) and contact pages make this gorgeous diary an absolute standout! Price: £11.08.

Title Headline: 12 Stylish Things That'll Have You Breaking Hearts On Valentine's Day
Short Description Sub Headline: You'd look cute in sweats, but just in case.
Content Body: Shopping | 12 Stylish Things That'll Have You Breaking Hearts On Valentine's Day | You'd look cute in sweats, but just in case. | Posted on January 31, 2020, 02:28 GMT | January 31, 2020, 02:28 GMT | Mariela SummerhaysBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Mariela Summerhays / BuzzFeed, The IconicThe sweetheart neckline, elasticised puffed sleeves, thigh-high centre slit and fabric-covered buttons — it's all just so dreamy. Made of pure linen with cotton lining, it's the perfect thing for your summer night date. Promising review: "This is my new favourite dress. I wear it to work in contrasting, bright slides — and at night, keep my face bare and sandals nude for the ultimate ethereal, romantic look. I get compliments on the blush colour and sweet sleeves all the time. It is linen — so crushes easily — but you get past that quickly enough for such a sweet dress."—Mariela SummerhaysOriginally $139 / Buy now for $69.50 from The Iconic. | Third FormYou've never owned a slip dress like this. Featuring adjustable tie-up straps, I've seen this dress worn slightly looser, like the above photos, making for a more relaxed silhouette — and tighter, creating a more figure-hugging shape and higher hemline. The timeless black colour, classic satin construction, keyhole detail to bust and ribbon back feature — 100% a dress to wear over and over again.Buy for $220 from Amazon Australia. | The IconicSo, not the only linen item on the list — and really, can you blame me when it's been so hot lately? These high-waisted, relaxed fit cropped pants feature sweet gathered detail to the cuffs and a pistachio hue that wouldn't look out of place on your date or work come Monday. Buy for $99.95 from The Iconic. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Natalia Krslovic / BuzzFeedI recently dressed my friend, Nat, in this dress for a style swap challenge video you can watch here. Of the form-fitting, midi-length dress with asymmetrical sleeve, she said:Promising review: "When I first saw this dress, I was simultaneously excited and scared. I love an asymmetrical sleeve, but I don't often go for anything this figure-hugging for fear of it not flattering my body.Turns out, I had nothing to worry about. This dress was sexy, comfortable and showed off all my curves — while still looking elegant and classy. I really felt super glam and I loved it. I was initially worried that some of my rolls were showing through, but once I'd gotten over my own insecurities, I was really vibing this look."-Natalia KrslovicOriginally $111.96 / Buy now for $83.97 from Amazon Australia. | @thirdform / Via instagram.com, AmazonThis excellent trouser from Third Form features a high-waist, wide leg, ankle-baring hemline — and perhaps my favourite detail, a tonal paisley pattern throughout. Lining from waist to seat ensures it will last you for years (no wearing down at the thighs!). Wear with its matching jacket closed, black stilettos and nothing else at all.Promising review: "Honestly, one of the best pair of pants I've ever owned. Figure-hugging in all the right spots but balanced with a loose-fit in the legs —which makes them suitable for both the office and date-night. Love the subtle pattern on the fabric too, and the side zip. But if I'm being real, it's all about the ass in these pants and I am liviinnggg for it."—Julia WillingBuy for $200 from Amazon Australia. | Mariela Summerhays / BuzzFeed, MyerPromising review: "I'm a big fan of statement earrings as part of an everyday outfit. I wear these with a double denim look and bare face, all the time. I love everything about this — the gold and pearl detail is just so decadent. Plus, considering the quality, it's so affordable — I buy something from Bling Bar whenever I need to gift my friends something."—Mariela SummerhaysBuy for $55 from Myer. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF In recent years, slip dresses have come back from their '90s hey day, and I for one, am here for it. Not all slip dresses are made equal though — cheap material, unflattering cuts — but this one here is the crème de la crème. Cut from pure silk in a form-flattering silhouette, its midi-length hem means it can be worn wherever without it looking like you've just run away from bridesmaid duties.Originally $250 / Buy now for $175 from The Iconic. | If, like me, you're challenged when it comes to styling your hair for special occasions, few things come as handy as a headband. These particular ones are fashioned from lush velvet, are embellished with pearl-like beads and have a knot design to centre. You'll look like a duchess — without the prince or intense public scrutiny.Buy a set of three for $17.99 from Amazon Australia. | Mariela Summerhays / BuzzFeed, SportsgirlI am literally wearing these now at my desk, as I type this. Unlike my usual heels, these are so comfortable. Their block midi-heels mean I can happily walk around everywhere and their classic black hue and minimalist design mean they have slotted easily into my existing wardrobe — date night or otherwise.Buy for $79.95 from Sportsgirl. | Ugh, it's just so pretty. An illusion neckline, lace overlay, asymmetrical hemline — this gorgeous dress wouldn't look out of place in Sophia Loren's wardrobe. Add a red lip and braid crown for a gorgeous ~romantic vibe~.Buy from $41.17 from Amazon Australia. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: ローソンさん天才…もっちり食感の“145円ケーキ”がたまらない美味しさでした
Short Description Sub Headline: ローソンの「香ばしチーズのモッチケーキ」がハンパない美味しさです。そのままで食べるとしっかりモッチりのバターケーキチーズ味、みたいな感じなのに温めると生地がフワッフワモチッモチになるんです！！ひとつのケーキで2回楽しめるの、最高じゃん…
