Title Headline: 21 Ten-Minute Cleaning Products You'll Probably Wish You'd Known About Sooner
Short Description Sub Headline: Resolve your cleaning conundrums, quickly.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 21 Ten-Minute Cleaning Products You'll Probably Wish You'd Known About Sooner | Resolve your cleaning conundrums, quickly. | Posted on January 22, 2020, 12:56 GMT | January 22, 2020, 12:56 GMT | Natalie BrownBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.comIt works on both old and new stains (including red wine!), and on any color-safe fabric that you can safely wet with water (read: not dyed silk or wool, probs, or anything that says "dry clean only"). Promising review: "I had terrible rust and oil stains all over the seats of my car. I tried other cleaners to get them out, but they actually made the stains darker. I took it to the dealership to see if they could get it out and they flat out told me no, so I gave up and lived with it for almost five years. Then I tried this after it was recommended by a friend. I sprayed it on and literally watched the stain run right off my seat. It was amazing! I thought I was going to have to pay hundreds of dollars to replace the seats in my car because nothing else would work. This stuff really is awesome!" —BrittanyGet a bottle on Amazon for $11.45. | | | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF amazon.com, Scrubbing Bubbles / youtube.comYou just press it beneath the rim (after a regular toilet cleaning, of course!) and let it get to work. You'll have to re-stamp every 12 days or so, depending on how often the toilet's flushed. Oh, and make sure to stamp it somewhere it won't become a, well, "target" and get sprayed off before its time. Promising review: "A lazy housekeepers best friend — these are amazing and I'm bummed I haven't tried them until now! Warning: possible TMI! We're big fans of the 'if it's yellow, let it mellow' potty practice in our home as it conserves a serious amount of water if you flush every 3-4 tinkles vs every time....anyways! These little gems are easy to use and with our limited flushing, one application tends to last around two weeks before it starts to lose its smell and effectiveness. But it has kept our bowls clean and the bathroom smelling fresh." —StephanieGet it in packs that last for up to 20 weeks from Amazon: the "fresh" scent for $10.32 or the "rainshower" scent for $8.34. | amazon.com, amazon.comIt allows you to firmly grab two blinds at a time, so you could easily make one window's blinds look basically brand new in under 10 minutes. Plus it comes with five microfiber sleeves, which means you can finish all the blinds in your home without stopping to clean it off over and over — you just pop all the covers in the wash when you're done. Promising review: "A super time saver. It legitimately used to take us hours to clean all the blinds. My wife now does all the faux-wood Venetian blinds in the house in about one hour. It's really nice that it comes with some spare cloths for it, and it's cheap enough to buy a whole additional set so we can make more than one kid do this chore at the same time." —R.D.Get one on Amazon for $7.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comYou simply twist its base to dispense the solution into the bristles, brush it over your gems, rinse with water, and voila! Your ring will sparkle like a thousand stars, and you can toss the Stik back in your purse, ready for the next time you notice a little dinginess. (It works with pretty much every gem and metal except pearls.) Promising review: "I was a bit skeptical about this product and the fact that it's under $10 but once I opened and used it... OMG! I have a rose de France amethyst wedding ring and the stone was so cloudy it looked terrible. I kept trying to clean it with a toothbrush and warm water/mild soap as I was instructed when it was purchased. It would get clean but I couldn't get behind the stone so it would never really look clean. I used this product and once it was rinsed and dry it looked just like the day I received it. I was so excited! Fell back in love with my ring again and can't stop looking at it. The bristles on the brush really get into the tiny holes behind the ring setting which allows for an actual scrub on the back of the stone to remove the buildup. This product is amazing." —KY ActonGet it on Amazon for $8.78. | amazon.comPromising review: "I used it on our tubs, toilets, sinks, and shower. It took one bottle of this stuff to achieve the same result as three bottles of other brands. I will buy this again hands down. I just sprayed, walk away for a few minutes, and wiped and rinsed." —Carrie D.Get a bottle on Amazon for $4.98. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | amazon.comPromising review: "Works extremely well. We haven't done any cleaning on our dishwasher in five years, and the sliding trays were tough to pull out and push in, there was detergent build up all over the inside, and there was a milky film on all our cups. I bought this, ran the dishwasher with two tablets while it was empty, and the difference was astounding. There was still some build up and I figured it would require another cycle, so I popped another two tablets in, ran the machine a second time, and now it looks and sounds brand new. No more film on the glasses, no more dirty dishes from clogged sprayers, no more odors, and no more build-up around the door seals." —MartouneGet a box of six tablets on Amazon for $3.15. | amazon.comNote that it's best if your garbage disposal's just generally smell and not actually clogged — if it's clogged, definitely call a plumber. Promising review: "Do you have a stinky garbage disposal? If so, get some of these. They are cheap, smell nice. and the foaming action really provides you with a visual they are cleaning the drain. After using these the garbage disposal seems smoother (fewer strange noises, like it's been lubricated). I'd recommend these over Plinks any day as I feel the Plinks only hide smells whereas these foaming packets actually clean the disposal."—SugacookieGet a pack of four on Amazon for $5.08. | amazon.comIt's basically a small piece of metal chain mail (yes, like the knights wore!) that's dishwasher safe and doesn't require soap to scrub off all the remnants of burgers, eggs, and veggies lingering on your favorite pan. Just don't use it on any non-stick pans, of course — metal scratches 'em!Promising review: "This has completely changed the way I use my cast iron pan. I can cook whatever I want and know the pan will be as good as new. For people that worry about the seasoning on the pan, this definitely won't hurt a thing. Once I'm done cleaning, I'll shake off any excess water and then heat it on the stove top for a minute until its completely dry. I'll then put a a very light coating of oil on it and heat it up again and the pan will be good to go for the next use. My pan has never cooked better." —JoshGet it on Amazon for $15.99. And if you do get it, I recommend reading this review — I know it's long, but they offer some excellent advice on how to make the most of it. | amazon.comI've been using these for years, so I know: all they need is a little water, and they truly do erase all kinds of dirt and grime like it was never there! Promising review: "I can't believe how clean I could get my non-porcelain sink with this product. I was so disgusted with trying all types of cleansers, with very mixed results. But just a wipe or two and the sink was sparkling! Next, I tackled the tub — once, no doubt, a lovely porcelain fixture but now with worn-down porcelain that wants to hold onto every smudge of dirt or stain. Again, the sponge worked! It really did clean up, if not so sparkly white. I even considered taking a bath again, which I hated to do before." —PeninaGet a pack of eight on Amazon for $10. | amazon.comBecause it doesn't rely on adhesive paper, you only have to buy it once and use it forever — cleaning the hair off the brush when it gets clogged, of course! Promising review: "We live in a household that contains two humans, two dogs, and two cats. It's a real Noah's Ark furnished with a black sectional couch. Our dogs absolutely hate the vacuum. So much so they will attack the cleaner head with their vicious bite even before we power it on. This makes the task of cleaning our couch extremely unpleasant and nearly impossible. Thanks to Chom Chom, we no longer have this problem! With a simple, quick, SOUNDLESS sweep, we're able to keep our couch pet-hair-free in blissful peace. This tool does an amazing job picking up pet hair but not so much with crumbs. We were so impressed, we gifted these as Christmas presents for all of our pet-loving friends." —MagpieGet one on Amazon for $24.95. | amazon.comPromising review: "These towels are awesome for so many things. They are large and very sturdy, so they work well for household cleaning. The real benefit for me, though, is having a wipe that works for things like the grill, the oven, the dashboard of my car, muddy shoes, chairs and umbrellas that go to soccer games and practices, and lawn furniture. I frequently wipe something down, rinse the towel, and wipe again. The wipes are heavy enough to go through three to four rinses and wipes and still hold up. The smell is mild and doesn't linger on my hands or what I've wiped down. Because the canister is heavier than most, and the lid fits well, it's easy to throw one of these in the trunk or cargo area without worrying about leaks. The canister's recyclable when the towels are gone — an added bonus." —COMomGet a tub on Amazon for $11.75. | amazon.comPromising review: "I have a 19-year-old master bathroom toilet that had accumulated some nasty stains over time which regular toilet brushes and cleaning products just would not remove. Pumice stone worked like a charm! Given the nature and severity of the stains, it required some elbow grease, but 10 minutes later I have a new-looking bowl, and I see no signs of scratching. Am very happy with this purchase...well worth the very low price!" —Happy RetireeGet one on Amazon for $7.99. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 16 Horror Movie Details And Easter Eggs That Are Scarily Awesome
Short Description Sub Headline: "Oh, cool!" —Me catching these details while watching the movies through my fingers.
Content Body: TV and Movies | 16 Horror Movie Details And Easter Eggs That Are Scarily Awesome | "Oh, cool!" —Me catching these details while watching the movies through my fingers. | Posted on January 25, 2020, 01:45 GMT | January 25, 2020, 01:45 GMT | Allie HayesBuzzFeed Staff | A24"In an early scene, while Dani and Christian are arguing in Dani’s apartment, there’s a painting in the background of a girl wearing a crown who is kissing a bear, which outright foreshadows both of their fates at the end of the film."—corinneldwyer | | Universal Pictures"When Tiffany goes to the evidence locker to get the remains of Chucky, they also have Jason Voorhees’s hockey mask, Freddy Krueger’s glove, Michael Myers’ mask, Leatherface’s chainsaw, and even the puppets from Puppet Master locked up."—t413c16c57 | Buena Vista Pictures Distribution"I actually had a theory the first time I saw this that you could tell that Malcolm was dead from the beginning of the movie because, if you pay attention, he's wearing the same shirt he was shot in the entire movie."—stacieb46da63d87 | DreamWorks Pictures"There’s a scene where Naomi Watts’s character is riding on a ferry boat, notices a horse that is also being transported, and tries to pet the horse. There is a closeup of the horse’s eye, and it's a reference to the closeup that appears on the creepy cassette tape that she, her son, and her ex all watched that doomed them all. It was such a cool moment of foreshadowing!"—kminfl | Paramount PicturesIn the remake, during Ellie's birthday party, Jud can be heard in the background saying, 'There was a big Saint Bernard who got rabies..." which is a direct reference to Cujo, another work of Stephen King's."—caitlinm18 | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | New Line Cinema, Embassy Communications"Nancy is watching a trailer for Evil Dead while trying to stay awake so, in Evil Dead 2, the director (Sam Raimi) returned the favor by hanging Freddy's razor glove on the wall of the toolshed when Ash uses the chainsaw."—suspiciouscake

Title Headline: Just 9 Things To Try In January
Short Description Sub Headline: Because we tried them for you in December.
Content Body: Shopping | Just 9 Things To Try In January | Because we tried them for you in December. | Posted on January 06, 2020, 12:20 GMT | January 06, 2020, 12:20 GMT | Maitland QuitmeyerBuzzFeed Staff | BuzzFeed / Anna Kopsky"I have been carrying my laptop in a backpack for the last five years, because I really haven't found a laptop bag that is cute, comfortable, AND within my price range... until this beaut. Not only is it extremely adorable, but it also has survived plenty of walks in the rain and still looks like it's in the same condition as the day I got it. Best of all, I can throw everything I need for the day into the bag and there always still seems to be more room for more items. Just this week, I tossed everything in the image above in my bag like I do every morning before work, before realizing I also needed to bring extra hairspray, deodorant, and my makeup bag. All of those things also fit in this bag, and it was so nice to not have to carry a bunch of bags around on my commute! I really recommend this laptop bag for a stylish option that is well within anyone's budget. Woo!" —Anna KopskyGet it from Amazon for $25.99+ (available in four colors). | "If you’re familiar with the pearly world of teeth whitening, then you already know it’s a sensitive process. And if you see your dentist and go the professional route, it can also be an expensive one. That's why I decided to try GlowUp when I noticed my teeth looking a little yellow. It's an LED whitening kit that is fully customized to your mouth. To start, you take a comprehensive quiz, answering questions about your brushing habits and how discolored your chompers currently are. Once you're done, you get a specific formula shipped to you.Glowup costs $60 for a one-time kit, or $30 if you sign up for a bimonthly subscription, which is around what you’ll spend for most at-home whitening kits. A treatment takes only 10 minutes (compared with overnight trays or strips you keep on for 30 minutes to an hour). My blend included hydrogen peroxide (the whitening ingredient commonly used by dentists), menthol (to provide a refreshing minty sensation), and cellulose gum (to fight off irritation and discomfort). For anyone who’s all about natural ingredients, Glowup also utilizes pomegranate seed extract, chamomile flower, and aloe leaf juice to remove bacteria and disinfect breath.I love a schedule: setting one and keeping one. So brushing my teeth at night and using the kit was a cinch. I’d apply my custom gel to the mouthguard, set a timer for 10 minutes, and plug the cord directly into my iPhone’s charging port. It truly was that easy. For such a mindless process, I saw a significant difference in the color of my teeth after a week of daily use. Seeing that I’ve never used a whitening light before, I was skeptical. But the results were obvious and I now have refill gels shipped to me for touchups." —Alexandra Napoli Get a kit from Glowup for $60, or $30 if you sign up for a subscription (with refills for $10). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Kaysey Davis/BuzzFeed"I love a good sheet mask, and the Garnier Moisture Bomb sheet mask is one of my absolute favourites. Unlike other masks that are made of microgel, cellulose, or foil, this mask is made out of cotton, which is not only super soft, but more environmentally friendly. The cotton has a bit of stretch to it, so it's easier to fit it around my face, nose, and lips than other masks. It's also very gentle on the skin and less irritating than other mask materials, so it's great for anyone with sensitive skin. I have oily/combination skin, so my cheeks and chin tend to be drier than the T-zone. I love using the Pomegranate sheet mask to boost the moisture levels in my skin, but all the different types of masks are equal when it comes to hydration. I can just sit back and relax while my skin soaks up all the liquid goodness. Even after I remove the mask, there is so much product left on my skin and in the package that I use it the excess serum on my neck. I can immediately see brighter, smoother, and more hydrated skin after just 15 minutes on my face. I use them a couple times a week before I go to bed, so I wake up with my skin at its best." —Kaysey DavisGet a six-pack from Amazon for $14.94 (also available in four other varieties). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 33 Amazon Products That Convinced Skeptical Shoppers To Hit "Add To Cart"
Short Description Sub Headline: You can't argue with those results.
Content Body: Shopping | | Amazon | 33 Amazon Products That Convinced Skeptical Shoppers To Hit "Add To Cart" | You can't argue with those results. | Posted on January 30, 2020, 15:00 GMT | January 30, 2020, 15:00 GMT | Melanie AmanBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.comThe brush has special vents that allow air to flow so hair dries faster. Plus, it's quicker than using a dryer and then a flat iron or curling iron, which equals less heat damage. Promising review: "Just wow! I was skeptical at first. I wish I would have bought this sooner! After showering I get all the moisture I can out of my hair. And leave it to kind of air dry while I’m getting ready, having coffee, or whatever I’m doing that morning. It takes me about seven minutes to dry my hair if that! I have very thick naturally curly hair. It’s is a fabulous tool to have in your arsenal! May be the only one I have to use. No flat iron needed as of yet! Would buy again in a heartbeat!" —D.KGet it from Amazon for $27+ (available in four colors). | | | amazon.comPromising review: "I was skeptical at first but fully committed now.+ only 1/4 of the bottle in and my skin looks better+ feels smooth+ no redness and less acne scars+ little to no breakout even during my cycle+ absorb fast+ moisturizingI used it in the morning and before sleeping at night 😍" —Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $7.70. | amazon.comPromising review: "Holy crap!! Are you skeptical when it comes to buying stuff online? ME TOO! That's why I figured all of these rave reviews were a crock of crap. I've seriously bought every kind of vacuum out there, including the Rumba, which is about as intelligent as a cotton swab. But I have four cats and a golden retriever, so I was getting desperate! I believe the saying is… a picture is worth a thousand words. Check mine out (above)! Of note — the 'before' picture was taken of my dog's bed AFTER it went through the washer and dryer. Look at all of that left-behind hair!!! And the 'after' picture was taken after only THREE MINUTES spent vacuuming her bed. I. Am. SOLD! BTW, I've NEVER taken the time to review a product before, just FYI." —Luka ChanGet it from Amazon for $30.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "A perfect dupe for Drunk Elephant's Babyfacial!!! This is a fraction of the $80 price tag of Babyfacial. This brand is a godsend!!! Science does not lie. I was skeptical at first because it's so inexpensive, but it's real and it works!!!! Title Headline: 14 Ocean Creatures That Show Just How Wild The Earth Actually Is
Short Description Sub Headline: Nature is beautiful and terrifying.
Content Body: 14 Ocean Creatures That Show Just How Wild The Earth Actually Is | Nature is beautiful and terrifying. | Posted on January 24, 2020, 13:03 GMT | January 24, 2020, 13:03 GMT | Ben ArmsonBuzzFeed Staff | | By Wildestanimal / Getty Images, Aldorado10 / Getty ImagesPhysalia physalis, more commonly known as the "Portuguese man o' war" is often mistaken as a jellyfish, but is in fact a siphonophore. A siphonophore is an animal that is made up of a colony of organisms working together, meaning that the man o' war is in fact a group of animals!The man o' war get its name from its uppermost polyp, which is a gas-filled bladder that floats above the water, resembling an old warship. The man o' war's tentacles can grow to 165 feet in length and deliver a venom that can kill small fish and other small creatures. Although it can't kill humans it will give you a nasty sting, if your like me and you do kind of want to know what that weirdly beautiful gas-bag feels like, maybe think twice. | Mookmook / Getty Images, BBCThe Giant Trevally which is located in the Indo-Pacific region, is an apex predator – meaning that it is basically the bad bitch of the sea. It can grow up to 170cm in length and feeds mainly on fish and crustaceans, but can also be found feeding on birds too. It is so skilled as a hunter that it can be seen leaping out of the water to grab birds as they fly close to the water to feed. Land or sea no animal is safe from this fish!

Title Headline: 36 Ways To Make Cleaning Your Whole House Easier
Short Description Sub Headline: The faster you clean, the faster you can reunite with your couch.
Content Body: Shopping | | Home | 36 Ways To Make Cleaning Your Whole House Easier | The faster you clean, the faster you can reunite with your couch. | Posted on January 24, 2020, 12:01 GMT | January 24, 2020, 12:01 GMT | Emma McAnawBuzzFeed Staff | amazon.comPromising review: "I fell in love with this product some 15 years ago and I am so very happy that it's still available in the same wonderful formula as ever. It has a fantastic citrus scent. This takes care of any stain so fast and efficiently, it's become a party trick. I have seriously poured red wine over a white comforter to demonstrate how great it is. It is a miracle in a bottle! We use it for all sorts of cleaning on materials around the house, and one bottle has lasted us years! This is definitely a product every home should have." —Melanie NolenGet it from Amazon for $6.67.Check out other "14 Stain Removal Hacks We Know Actually Work Because We Tried Them" to avoid future freak-outs! | | | amazon.com, amazon.comThis comes as a starter kit: one sweeper, seven dry sweeping cloths, and three wet mop cleaning solution cloths!Promising review: "This product saved me — I have arthritis in my back and knees, and normal mopping and ringing out were such a chore and pain to my joints. The Swiffer is so easy: no bending, no rinsing out, no wringing. I just put a wet pad on, run it over the floors, and they come out clean. When the pad gets dirty, you just change it. I recommend this great product to everyone if they want a truly clean floor with no hassle." —Frank PaolucciGet it from Amazon for $11.97. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | amazon.comPlus it feeds your wood protective carnauba wax and beeswax to give it some ~luster~ and extend its lifetime.Promising review: "OMG! This is the most AMAZING product! We inherited some antique furniture from the '30s that had been in storage forever. It was dry, dirty, and not much to look at. I used this product on it and the oak wood literally came alive, showing the beautiful grain and texture of the wood. I have since used it on my oak kitchen cabinets and they look AMAZING! I will never use anything else other than this product on my wood surfaces! No greasy feel, just a fantastic smell!" —Tiffany SadowskiGet it from Amazon for $8.48.To learn more, check out "This Wood Polish's Before-And-After Photos Will Make You A Believer". | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | amazon.comPromising review: "I've seen the commercials for years and thought it was another gimmick. Our dog has been bringing in mud and jumping on our bed right after. Washing with detergent alone didn't remove the stains very well. I washed it with some of this stuff and all of it came out. I couldn't see where the stains previously were. Needless to say, I started doing a bunch of loads of white clothes to get them all whiter!" —KristyGet it from Amazon for $12.89+ | amazon.comIts natural rubber bristles attract pet hair on multiple surfaces, like carpet, tile, hardwood, and linoleum AND has a built-in rubber squeegee (aka the thing you use on your windshield) for cleaning windows and spills. Promising review: "I bought this broom two years ago and it is still going strong! I have four large breed dogs and we have fur EVERYWHERE! This works so, so well! I came back and purchased one for my neighbor and sent one to my favorite pet rescue down south. I am always amazed at what this picks up even after I just ran the vacuum. I also use it to get dust and cobwebs off the floors and ceilings. It truly is a super tool." —RoseannGet it from Amazon for $13.33 | amazon.comDid I mention it's lemon-scented?Promising review: "I'm a little embarrassed to write this review; it's been six years since my last oven cleaning. After seeing the results, I couldn't help but spread the word. Sure, it took some beer, a little John Mayer, and a lot of elbow grease, but I got the job done, thanks to this handy little product. It did require two treatments; however, given the circumstances, this product accomplished quite a feat in just an hour. The attached pictures (above) speak for themselves." —William FredericksGet it from Amazon for $5.99. | Caroline Miller / Nifty / BuzzFeedGet a can of hairspray from Amazon for $3.59.To learn more, check out "14 Cleaning Hacks We Know Actually Work Because We Tried Them". | Amazon, amazon.comThey're great for windows or any glassware, too!Promising review: "I couldn't get my windows clean using cleaning solution, newsprint, and a lot of elbow grease. There were always streaks and dirt left behind. Enter these things. One quick cleaning, and I do mean quick, and my windows are now cleaner than any windows I've ever cleaned. It's simply amazing. We were all standing around in utter shock and delight before running around trying the cloths on other stuff: the TV, the picture glass, etc. I know it sounds corny, but I couldn't wait to get up this morning, because I woke up in the middle of the night excitedly thinking about trying it on the car today. They are truly, truly amazing." —Amazon CustomerGet a pack of eight from Amazon for $14.98. | amazon.comEach application lasts about 12 days! Refills have six gel stamp uses, and each box has two refills.Promising review: "Love these. They keep the toilet clean. So you squeeze this thick, nice smelling gel stuff onto the inside of your toilet bowl using the dispenser that comes with — easy. It lasts a few weeks according to how often your toilet is flushed. Each time you flush, water runs over the gel, cleaning the bowl and dispensing a fresh scent. I've watched as, ahem, dirty stuff stuck on the inside of the bowl gets washed away as the cleaner works its magic. I've used these for years and highly recommend." —Johnny's girlGet a pack of two from Amazon for $9.99. | One Good ThingPromising review (for the lavender essential oil): "I am absolutely in love with this! I use it for many different things around my home. I use it to keep my mattress, pillows and down comforter fresh. It helps me get a better night sleep, since the lavender is a calming solution." —kimmyGet them from Amazon: baking soda for $3.08 and lavender essential oil for $7.99.Check out more from One Good Thing for "How To Clean A Mattress". | amazon.comAnd it's lightweight so lifting it isn't a *chore*. Promising review: "Have long hair? Have you killed other vacuums with your (slightly worrying amount) of shedding? Then look no further. We bought a another Bissell vacuum a year ago, and it didn't take long for my long hair to just kill the little vacuum. Now, we have this vacuum and our apartment is actually clean because my hair is not too much for it. The bristles have grooves that prevent hair from caking on, and it's very easy to clean. The brushes are also adjustable, so you can really get into the carpet if you want. It's also pretty light for something so heavy duty. For the price, it's a great vacuum and would really work if your place isn't very big, as the cord isn't super long." —J. HallerGet it from Amazon for $92.70. | amazon.comPromising review: "This works extremely well. We haven't done any cleaning on our dishwasher in five years, and the sliding dish trays were tough to pull out or push in, there was detergent build-up all over the inside, and there was a milky film on all our cups. I bought Affresh, ran the dishwasher with two tablets while it was empty, and the difference was astounding. There was still some build-up and I figured it would require another cycle, so I popped another two tablets in, ran the machine a second time, and now it looks and sounds brand-new. No more film on the glasses, no more dirty dishes from clogged sprayers, no more odors, or build-up around the door seals. I'm going to be buying Affresh from now on, and hopefully it will extend the life of my dishwasher." —MartouneGet it from Amazon for $3.71. | amazon.comPromising review: "I used it on our tubs, toilets, sinks, and shower. It took one bottle of this stuff to achieve the same result as three bottles of other brands. I will buy this again hands down. I just sprayed, walked away for a few minutes, and wiped and rinsed." —Carrie D.Get it from Amazon $4.98. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: Just 14 Things Under $20 That'll Probably Make A Big, Big Difference
Short Description Sub Headline: Big difference for very little coin.
Content Body: Shopping | Just 14 Things Under $20 That'll Probably Make A Big, Big Difference | Big difference for very little coin. | Posted on January 31, 2020, 05:40 GMT | January 31, 2020, 05:40 GMT | Mariela SummerhaysBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Bunnings, Timbermate / Via youtube.comI am not a handy person, so I've kind of just accepted the scratches and dents my home and furniture are slowly accumulating *eyes my tiny humans and cat*. This brilliant little tool, which comes in every conceivable hue of wood, can be rubbed into the surface of your furniture or heated to fill larger dents. You can even mix more than one stick to get your desired colour! Now anyone can be a home renovator.Buy a single stick for $6.55 from Bunnings. | | | AmazonThese patches are made of hydrocolloid, a wound-healing material that protects against bacteria. Ultra-thin and complete with a matte finish, they can be worn on top of inflamed and acne-prone skin, and under foundation (!). A few hours later, your zits will have shrunk noticeably. No wonder people are buying these in bulk.Buy a pack of 18 patches for $5.20 from Amazon Australia. | AmazonLook, can't relate. But I've seen the benches y'all are sitting on for hours on end and they can't be great for your back. This water-resistant seat can be used to provide back support — or unfolded, as cushioning for both you and a mate. It's easily rolled up, comes in three different colours (blue, red, black) and even has a mesh pocket to keep your cold ones close at hand.Buy for $15.90 from Amazon Australia. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Lush / Via au.lush.com, @lushcosmetics / Via instagram.comI will continue to write about this lotion until someone physically restrains me. This combination of oatmeal, lavender oil and organic cocoa butter is almost solely responsible for the solid eight hours I get every night. It smells heavenly and feels like a warm hug on freshly-showered skin.Plus, Lush only purchases from suppliers that don't test on animals, so you can feel good about where you're putting your dollars.Buy a 95g jar for $17.95 from Lush. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | AmazonCast iron skillets are the preferred pans of many professional chefs, due to the even distribution of heat across the entire surface and unparalleled heat retention. This one features lips on either side for easy pouring and at 3.5" in diameter, is perfect for cooking a sweet dessert for one or two.If you're looking for inspiration on what you can make your date with your cast iron skillet, here are 21 recipes you can start with.Buy for $19.95 from Amazon Australia. | AmazonReviewers say that this stamp makes the perfect winged eye every time — infinitely easier than trying to get even lines freehand. Each set comes with two pens — one for your left eye, one for right — and is water-resistant and smudge-proof.Buy for $11.57 from Amazon Australia. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 12 Pictures From South America That Show Australia's Bushfire Smoke Has Reached Their Shores
Short Description Sub Headline: Experts predict smoke from the wildfires may have also reached the Antarctic.
Content Body: 12 Pictures From South America That Show Australia's Bushfire Smoke Has Reached Their Shores | Experts predict smoke from the wildfires may have also reached the Antarctic. | Posted on January 07, 2020, 23:53 GMT | January 07, 2020, 23:53 GMT | Julia WillingBuzzFeed Staff | Darrian Traynor / Getty Images: The Australia BushfiresThe UN World Meteorological Organisation has also stated that smoke may have reached the Antarctic by now. | Mᴀx Pᴏᴡᴇʀ@maxpawuerOK | Mᴀx Pᴏᴡᴇʀ | @maxpawuerOK | Chile dawned cloudy, but not because of the weather but because of the smoke from the fires in Australia. Smoke is a threat to the Ice Fields of the Argentine Patagonia. The smoke is coming to South America.The world's great media prefer silence #australiafire #AustraliaBurning | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Ruptly@Ruptly | Ruptly | @Ruptly | Smoke from #Australia's fires spotted in #Santiago, #Chile | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Estación bcp Meteorología@Estacion_bcp | Estación bcp Meteorología | @Estacion_bcp | Humo de incendios en #Australia 🇦🇺 llegan a America del sur. Asi se atardecia en Salto #Uruguay | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Stefanos Fotiou@stefanosfotiou | Stefanos Fotiou | @stefanosfotiou | This could be a new record on transboundary #AirPollutionThe #AustralianWildFires smoke reaching Argentina and Chile! https://t.co/sZwV5HHdYP | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Alejandra Galan@SepiaMNX | Alejandra Galan | @SepiaMNX | Australian bushfire smoke reached Chile! #australiafire and Australia's bushfire season is not over yet! #ClimateEmergency https://t.co/ARRQn6armT | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | James Lee@JKyL5 | James Lee | @JKyL5 | Australian bushfire smoke now crossing Argentina 🇦🇷. Title Headline: We've Gathered 14 Of This Week's Best Deals You'll Want To Throw Your Wallet At
Short Description Sub Headline: Fashion, tech and homewares, oh my!
Content Body: Shopping | We've Gathered 14 Of This Week's Best Deals You'll Want To Throw Your Wallet At | Fashion, tech and homewares, oh my! | Posted on January 20, 2020, 00:20 GMT | January 20, 2020, 00:20 GMT | Mariela SummerhaysBuzzFeed Staff | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF @silklaundry / Via instagram.com, THE ICONICOriginally $250/ Buy now for $175 from THE ICONIC.In recent years, slip dresses have come back from their '90s hey day, and I for one, am here for it. Not all slip dresses are made equal though — cheap material, unflattering cuts — but this one here is the crème de la crème. Cut from pure silk in a form-flattering silhouette, its midi-length hem means it can be worn wherever without it looking like you've just run away from bridesmaid duties. | LoverOriginally $450 / Buy now for $270 from Amazon Australia.So it has the hallmarks of every conservative family-friendly garment — subdued colours, thick shoulder straps, midi-length, A-line skirt. But, being from brilliant Aussie label Lover, the Eden Midi-Dress also features a lace-up, rope corset to the waist. Something for Nanna, something for you. | AmazonOriginally $529 / Buy now for $329 from Amazon Australia.Valid until January 29.Maybe you're an e-reader cynic, as I once was. But there comes a point when your back aches from carrying three different books in your shoulder bag and your bank account looks a bit sad from your impulse buys — at which point an e-reader starts to look like an attractive option. If that's where you are now, the Kindle Oasis has a glare-free screen, adaptive front lights (no need to stop reading as the sun goes down!), is waterproof, holds thousands of books and a single charge lasts weeks! | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Natalia Krslovic / BuzzFeedOriginally $111.96 / Buy now for $83.97 from Amazon Australia.I recently dressed my friend, Nat, in this dress for a style swap challenge video you can watch here. Of the form-fitting, midi-length dress with asymmetrical sleeve, she said:Promising review: "When I first saw this dress, I was simultaneously excited and scared. I love an asymmetrical sleeve, but I don't often go for anything this figure-hugging for fear of it not flattering my body.Turns out, I had nothing to worry about. This dress was sexy, comfortable and showed off all my curves — while still looking elegant and classy. I really felt super glam and I loved it. I was initially worried that some of my rolls were showing through, but once I'd gotten over my own insecurities, I was really vibing this look."-Natalia Krslovic | Harris Scarfe, TontineOriginally $209.99 / Buy now for $104.99 from Harris Scarfe.As you may have heard, Aussie retailer, Harris Scarfe, entered into voluntary administration last month and has begun the process of closing its doors. That being said, there are a bunch of great deals to pick up this week, including this King-sized, Aussie wool doona, that you can wash — which is great, because you're not quite sure that airing your doona out does very much at all. | Originally $39.07 / Buy now for $29.31 from Amazon Australia.Valid until February 8.Yes, I know you keep your appointments in your phone and it's been working well for you so far. But take it from someone who has just made the move back to journals, your productivity is going to go off. Research indicates that writing down your goals immediately gives you a greater chance of achieving them — and if not now, then when? This one comes with monthly calendar grids and space for daily to-do lists or hourly appointments.Not feeling this one? Browse up to 25% off Moleskine Notebooks here. | TIgerlilyOriginally $129 / Buy for $77.40 from Amazon Australia.If a stinking hot Aussie summer is the question, these lightweight, cotton pants here are the answer. Featuring the most extravagant bell-bottom legs with gathered, frilled hem, they're basically a built-in cooling system around your calves. If that didn't already convince you of their comfort — elastic waist and side pockets. THE DREAM. | Originally $59.99 / Buy now for $29 from THE ICONIC.I went to Rome when I was a teenager and I kid you not, the only souvenir I brought home with me were heels that looked exactly like these. Everything — from the red, patent finish, the croc-embossed detail, ankle strap and pointed toe — oozes Italian glamour. Beautiful thing about the chunky heel means you can wear it with jeans during the day, as easily as with a dress at night. | JB Hi-FiOriginally $329 / Buy now for $164 from JB Hi-Fi.So by now you've probably lost your obscenely expensive earbuds or worn down the cable on your infinitely-old corded earphones. Enter these over-ear wireless headphones. The best of both worlds, it gives powerful sound, is intuitive to use and takes up little room in your bag. Most importantly, it has the best in active noise cancellation, so you can shut the world out when necessary. | IKEAOriginally $249 / Buy now for $179 from IKEA.Right, so one of these babies entered my life for the first time recently and now I'm angry at myself for not getting one sooner. Chances are you, like me, sit for hours in one spot, shoulders up to your ears, everything but your fingers completely immobile. When standing at your desk, you can't help but shift your weight, move around to pick up things still at your waist's level etc etc. Move from sitting to standing with only the simple rotations of a crank handle.It might've cut my remedial massage bills in half, but let's be honest, I'm still going just as often, regardless. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: 46 Products That Might Make You Want To Exercise More This Year
Short Description Sub Headline: Don't sweat it — you're about to get super motivated.
Content Body: Shopping | 46 Products That Might Make You Want To Exercise More This Year | Don't sweat it — you're about to get super motivated. | Posted on January 21, 2020, 04:09 GMT | January 21, 2020, 04:09 GMT | Heather BragaBuzzFeed Staff | AmazonI've also been using this game as a way to supplement my trips to the gym. This may seem like a childish adventure from Nintendo, but JEEZ within moments I'm sweating my butt off. To play, you'll place a JoyCon into both the ring con and a leg strap so your movements are monitored. To move through each level you have to physically run in place and each time you "battle" an enemy you have to do 15 reps of an exercise of your choosing. For example, each time I complete a squat the enemy receives a "kick." It's so fun I don't realize I'm working out until the game reminds me to take a break and have some water. It even monitors your heart rate for you. It's more intense than you'd expect!Get it from Amazon for $79.99. | amazon.comPromising review: "Arrived today. Very easy to set up. I had it up on the wall in less than an hour. Looks great! I love that the medals can be hung below the bibs. I have 11 hung in total, which take up the entire rack. My only complaint is that I have 42 bibs hung and it is getting rather full-looking. Looks like I'll be ordering another bib display shortly... or run less races (and that's not happening). ;) Happy running, all!" —RocknRunnerGet it from Amazon for $34.99. | AmazonThis book truly transformed my workout mentality. It made me want to get up super early and run before the chaos of the day began. I started right after finishing her book and have continued ever since! If Khloe can do it, why can't we?Promising review: "I bought this book not knowing much about it, except it was written by a Kardashian and I have a weakness sometimes of binge-watching their show. This book not only makes me see Khloe completely different, but this book is one of the most inspiring and motivating things I've read! After reading a chapter I found myself wanting to immediately work out, and become a kinder and driven person. I just happen to be a new mom working hard to lose the baby weight and stay positive, and this was the perfect book to keep me going when the going got tough and motivated me to not give up and push myself harder! HIGHLY recommend this awesome book!!!!" —Amazon CustomerGet it from Amazon for $26.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Love this belt! It is super comfortable and sturdy. I bought the belt to hold my iPhone 8 Plus and keys while I run. The iPhone 8 Plus is a tight squeeze but fits even in its OtterBox case. I love the hook to snap my keys on so they stay in place and I don’t have to worry about them falling out. I did not even find the need to flip the belt as my phone and keys felt secure and I wanted easier access to my phone. It fits snugly on my hip and the belt did not bounce around on my run even with my heavy phone inside. All in all super happy with this purchase. Worth every penny!" —Elise V. RydingGet it from Amazon for $22.99+ (available in sizes 2XS–2XL and in nine colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comIn my opinion, the hardest part about exercising is finding a workout that you find fun and actually want to spend time doing. Enter: the Simply Fit Board. You can use it to balance during planks, as support for push-ups, or to strengthen your core. You're gonna love it!Promising review: "Love this board! I use every day and it is a great workout. It's transportable, durable, and highly effective! My abs look amazing! You can work cardio, core, upper body and lower body in a great variety of workouts on YouTube designed for the Simply Fit Board — can't give higher praise for this one!" —Heidi HoganGet it from Amazon for $14.80 (available in four colors). | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "Great! Fun way to mix it up for home workouts and travel. The dice are big and chunky and easy to read. Recommended!" —Kirsten B.Get it from Amazon for $13.41. | Hill CityPromising review: "This is a neat bag that doesn't look too high brow for the gym, looks rather government-issue. It does have some nice features, the zippers and the water repellency are neat adds. The build quality is still suspect but as long as the stitching for the handles have been done with some stress testing at the plant, it looks pretty strong." —McFlyGet it from Hill City for $148. | NintendoI admittedly am someone who thrives while working out at the gym, but there are many exercises I've been dying to try and don't because I don't want to embarrass myself. Boxing is one of them. Luckily, I can start practicing my skills (and break a decent sweat!) at home while playing this super-fun game on the Nintendo Switch. I use this game as a way to mix up my exercises / when I don't feel like venturing out to the gym. I have to say, it's a SERIOUS workout. I'm usually sore for days after and have burnt up to 300 calories in 30 minutes! If you get tired of the provided songs, mute your TV and turn on your favorite workout playlist — a great hack, if you ask me!Get it from Nintendo for $49.99. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I don't honestly know if there are enough words to express how much I love these gloves! They are seriously the most comfortable gloves in the world. They have awesome quality and construction, these will last a long time. I went with the 10 oz. ones and it was the perfect match. They fit snugly with wraps on, which is exactly how I like them. I use these regularly both on the bag and in sparring matches and love them for both! Can't beat them!!!" —RyanGet them from Amazon for $19.99+ (available in sizes 8 oz.–16 oz. and in eight styles). | mobotnation / Via instagram.com, NordstromPromising review: "This is the best water bottle ever! I’ve been looking for a good straw water bottle and this one is perfect. Others sound funny and don’t get a good suction. This one comes with a plastic and stainless straw. I also can’t believe how awesome the quality of the foam roller is and actually use it way more often than I thought I would. Also, love products made by woman!" —ajgreenGet it from Nordstrom for $49.99 (available in four styles). | Outdoor VoicesYou can choose from three different bra styles and four types of leggings to put together your perfect workout ~look~. While one pair of leggings usually costs $75, when you by Outdoor Voices' Rec Kit you'll get a full outfit for $95. Not bad, I tell ya ;)Get it from Outdoor Voices for $95 (both bras and leggings available in sizes XS–XL and in eight colors). | Good AmericanGet it from Good American for $59 (available in sizes 0–7 and in three styles). | AthletaPromising review: "I love this bra! I was hesitant about the straps on the back being functional, while they are very cute; but it fits well and holds up fine during yoga (although I won't be using this for any more intensive training). I have the matching leggings and I really like the pattern, and the Powervita fabric is so nice!" —kr2107Get it from Athleta for $39.99 (available in sizes 2XS–XL and two styles). | BuzzFeed, amazon.comNothing pisses me off more than when I'm working out and the wire from my headphones gets stuck on something and they get RIPPED out of my ears. I need to step out of the Stone Age and upgrade to a wireless pair like these.Promising review: "Fantastic headphones! They stay charged FOREVER! I had them fully charged and used them for an hour on average 6 times a week and did not need to charge them again for a month! The only complaints I have is when doing certain exercises they tend to slide off my head a little so I have to adjust them a few times." —Jessica JohnstonGet it from Amazon for $29.99+ (available in eight colors).This is also one of our BuzzFeed Reviews picks for the best wireless headphones! | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Mallory Mower / BuzzFeed, Heather Braga / BuzzFeedAh, the magic of technology. From boxing and speed skating to dodgeball and combat fighting, there are tons of simulation games for the Oculus Quest that'll help you work up a sweat at home.Get them from Oculus: Rift for $399.99, Quest for $399.99.And check out one BuzzFeed writer's full review of the Oculus Rift here. | AmazonPromising review: "I love mine! I am still fascinated with checking my info frequently and it works to motivate me on sluggish days. I wasn't sure I could get 10,000 steps a day in so I set it to 8,000 steps a day but I am managing to exceed the 10,000 on most days as I am averaging more than that. I have started running in addition to doing my 2x/ week weight workouts and still occasionally doing my at home DVD workouts. It also helps to make sure I am drinking enough water (although this requires that you log in how much you drink). I love the reminders! It buzzes me to let me know when I have hit my goal and to remind me to get my 250 steps in per hour. I also can log what i am eating and I was surprised to see I eat more calories than I thought. I am not currently trying to lose weight as I am breastfeeding my baby so I am not worried about that for the moment but I do want to keep working out to get back in shape. This is great for motivation, for tracking so I can see how I am doing and then when I go back in the log I can see how well I have done." —DeliaGet it from Amazon for $143.99+ (available in two sizes and seven colors). | PelotonI am SO interested in trying out one of these bad boys. I'm a sucker for the commercials and have even gone as far as downloading the Peloton app in an attempt to recreate the classes on a stationary bike at my gym — but it's just not the same as being in your own home. If you already own one of these bikes, can I come over and give it a go? Kthanks.Promising review: "Peloton, you have taken things to the next level... so happy I have a variety of classes, not only spinning. I’ve owned my bike for two years and my only complaint (at that time) was variety beyond the bike. I now have a new love for bootcamp, running, strength, stretching and yoga, and of course spinning. We dropped our family gym membership just a month ago and we have dedicated space in our house to have our tread, bike, and free weights. This was a game-changer! Thank you for offering what we all need." —AnonymousGet it from Peloton for $2,245+ (available in four packages). | amazon.com, amazon.comKacey Musgraves even posted about having/loving this exact water bottle! So, you can be both *happy* you're drinking lots of water and *sad* you always have to pee. Such is life!Promising review: "I'm in love with this bottle! Why? Because I only need to fill it ONCE and have my hydration requirements are met. The design is trendy, the motivational quotes help me stay on track AND it's pretty much portable. I'd recommend using the hand bar instead of the little rope thing because a full bottle IS HEAVY! Love it and would recommend it for my fellow water laggers :) Enjoy!" —AnisaGet it from Amazon for $13.95+ (available in 3 sizes and 35 styles). | amazon.com, amazon.comA few years ago I broke my foot and found I needed major support from my sneakers, not just for working out but for everyday use. I bought my first pair of Asics and never looked back. They are cushioned, comfortable, and exactly what you'd want in a sneaker — and over 3.7K Amazon customers agree!Promising review: "I love these shoes! I am hard to please due to plantar fasciitis, fallen arches, and lots of screws in my ankle. Great arch support and really beautifully designed shoe. The photo doesn't do them justice. They make me happy looking at them and wearing them. I only wear them to work out and they feel great! Great price too!!" —T. DiscosolaGet them from Amazon: women's sizes for $59.95+ (available in sizes 6–11 and in 10 styles) or men's sizes for $54.50+ (available in sizes 6–15 and in 16 styles) | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I absolutely LOVE these running shoes. They are extremely lightweight, feels like you are running on air yet with support. Super cute, look exactly as pictured and are true to size. I always wear a 6 and the 6 fit me perfectly. I would order these 100 times over, actually contemplating getting another pair in a different color just because these are so perfect. I’ve had them for over two months and they have not worn out at all. Wipes clean and doesn’t stain which is amazing!! I regularly run outside so I destroy my running shoes, these I’ve just taken a wet paper towel to and they are good as new! Sooo so happy with this purchase!" —KatGet them from Amazon for $45.99+ (available in women's sizes 5–11 and 25 styles). | Amazon, amazon.comHow CUTE are these? They are technically weights to add additional resistance to your workout, but they are also very stylish! You can wear them on your wrists or around your ankles during at-home yoga for an extra boost during your routine.Promising review: "These weights are incredible – absolutely stunning! Such great quality too. I got them for walking and yoga but I think I am going to wear them everywhere! They are very comfy and soft to the touch. And I LOVE the packaging. They come with a free bag to carry them in. I am definitely going to buy more colors." —JackieGet them from Amazon for $49 (available in four colors). | amazon.com, amazon.comI have one of these yoga mats and it has been a game-changer. Whether I'm taking it to an actual class or using it to follow a workout on YouTube at home, I know I'm not going to slip and hurt myself (can you tell I'm accident-prone?). Its many cute style options are for sure an added bonus!Promising review: "Love love love love this!! I'm 5'10" with LONG legs, so regular mats don't work for me. I step off them and they're not big enough. This one is amazing...nice and thick. Once I washed/prepped it, there's not slippage. You do have to wash/scrub it or it starts out pretty slick. But totally worth the money. I haven't used any other of my mats since. Thinking about getting another one to leave at my office." —CareyidahoGet it from Amazon for $22.48+ (available in 34 styles). | amazon.com, AmazonI was first introduced to this product via watching the Kardashians work out on Instagram (yes, really) and I've grown to love it! It's really simple to use — I like to do my crunches on it, as it gives me more back support. There are tons of other ways to break a sweat using this, so def consider adding it to your shopping cart.Promising review: "Omg...I love this. I just did 5k race with my son and his friends, it's called The Inflatable5k, meaning you run 3 miles while having inflatable obstacles to run, jump, or climb upon. I did it, but I have to say it was harder then I thought to balance on a balloon! I bought this wanting to improve, but I was not expecting all this FUN. I really love it! It's so easy on my joints — in fact when I use this in place of my step for aerobics DVDs, my knee pain is gone...for real! Unexpected bonus!!" —KatGet it from Amazon for $99.99+ (available in 11 styles). | Amazon, amazon.comThis is a prime example of something my gym has that I've always been too scared to try (for fear of quite literally falling on my face). The sliding technique used with this workout tool is great for building up your core — and actually looks kinda...fun? I'm gonna order a pair of these gliding discs to test out on my wood floors in the privacy of my own home. Who's with me?!Promising review: "This seems like a simple idea, but I would never have thought of it. I like the ability to exercise arms, back, chest, and core in so many variations. You can cater movement based on how you position yourself and move the gliders; the nuance of movement is near limitless. I tried it on my hardwood floor, but prefer the easier gliding on carpet. I compare it to my ab roller and find it to be an interesting alternative. I can keep my hands with palms downward open flat or place my fists on it for slightly different stressing of the hand and forearm muscles." —CharlieGet a set of two from Amazon for $10.97. | amazon.com, AmazonEssentially a tire with handles, this item is going to roll right into your workout routine. It's great for strengthening your abs, shoulder, arms, and back — which is pretty unbelievable based on how compact it is. Sign me UP.Promising review: "The little ab wheel is deceptively simple and sturdy. It looks like a kid's toy, but with proper daily use, it will give you a serious workout. It will strengthen not only your core (abs and lower back) but your arms, shoulders, legs, and entire body as well. In addition, it will give you an aerobic workout, because your heart and lungs will want to join in the fun!" —WhizzetsGet it from Amazon for $13.50+ (available in two colors). | Amazon, amazon.comDon't believe me? Order one of these and give it a try. This seemingly harmless workout tool makes for a serious strength-training sesh.Promising review: "This is actually a great kettlebell for the price. It's also much smaller than other coated kettlebells I have, so great space-wise. The handle is a perfect size for two hand grabbing, not all of my kettlebells are. I was worried the handle might not be smooth, but it is powder coated and has a great feel when I swing it. I'm going to order more before they disappear." —The Great BuzzwamiGet it from Amazon for $13.99+ (available in 5–50 pounds). | amazon.com, amazon.comExercise balls are a must-have for any home workout! You can use them to improve your core, for overall balance, alongside a Pilates video, and much more. Not to mention they're pretty fun to just bounce on.Promising review: "I can't even begin to say enough good things about this stability ball! My back has gotten so much stronger since I started using it as an office chair for one or two hours per day! I work from home and my back had gotten incredibly weak, to the point that I could only walk 1/4 mile before the pain would get EXTREMELY bad and unbearable. After two weeks of using the ball, I can now walk 1 mile before pain begins — that is a HUGE improvement and has made an even bigger impact on my happiness and quality of life. I might add that it is REALLY fun to bounce on it! I having been having a ball with it (pardon the pun)." —ValerieGet it from Amazon for $18.90+ (available in 3 sizes and 10 colors). | caliabycarrie / Via instagram.com, CALIAI have a pair of leggings from Calia by Carrie Underwood and they are one of my favorites to work out in. The material is unbelievably soft and do a really great job at wicking away sweat during even the most intense workouts. I've worn them to spin classes, to run, and while exercising at home. They're definitely a splurge-worthy pair you'll be happy you invested in — I mean, they have POCKETS!Get them from CALIA by Carrie Underwood for $70 (available in sizes XS–XL). | amazon.com, AmazonDon't act like you don't know exactly what I'm referring to! Anyways, this body workout bar can transform any doorway into a personal gym. Promising review: "I live by this iron gym. If you ever need a way to build confidence before embarrassing yourself at the gym with wrong form and two measly pull-ups, grind it out in your home and watch the improvement with this product. It’s affordable and very stable. I weigh about 205 lbs and it holds my weight perfectly! I started out doing maybe two pull-ups and I practiced and I’m now doing 20 a clip. I’ve done it and you can too!" —MarcusGet it from Amazon for $36.49. | Amazon, amazon.comUh, hello, there's a skull and crossbones on the handles of this jump rope! So freakin' cool! It is ideal for those interested in cardio training and is very lightweight — great for storing in your junk drawer and busting out when you're ready to sweat. Plus, it has 4.9K five-star reviews on Amazon, so you know it's legit.Promising review: "Very good-quality materials are used, starting from the steel rope, which is encased in some sort of heavy-duty, slightly clear plastic to the smooth bearings. The finish of the rope is very slick and seems like it'll hold up a long time. If you grab the handle and spin it, the bearing will go 10 revolutions easily, speaking to the quality of the bearings. I've only had it a couple of weeks and it is holding up great. For $10, probably one of the best ropes you can get. And from what I read about the owners of the company and their warranty, seems like these folks will be more than happy to get a new rope over to you ASAP if your current one breaks for whatever reason." —RomanGet it from Amazon for $10. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "With a new baby I found myself doing a lot of upper body exercises while holding my little one. While this is a great upper-body and potentially full-body workout, I found the baby to be a little too squirmy to be effective so I decided to pick up this medicine ball. It was a great choice. It's grippy, compact, and effective. It also doesn't have a tendency to spit up on me while doing chest presses, which is a big plus. Best part — this ball doesn't complain if I accidentally drop it. Honestly — this is a great basic medicine ball. The rubber skin provides great grip. No 'heavy spots,' with the weight evenly distributed across the ball. There are plenty of quick exercises you can do at home to do a full-body workout with the benefit of building both slow-twitch and fast-twitch muscle. Ball seems plenty durable and should last a good long time. Great purchase. Thinking of buying another in a different weight." —Todd W.Get it from Amazon for $28.50+ (available in 10 weights). | Amazon, amazon.comYou can work out SO many different parts of your body using these stretchy little guys — and you don't even have to leave your bedroom.Promising review: "I have had these for a few weeks now and I must say I'm thoroughly impressed with the packaging and quality of these bands. You get everything you see in the product pictures and it is exactly as advertised. There is an instructional pamphlet that details several different exercises possible with these bands with images of the different setups. The foam bars are sturdy and I had no trouble getting a good workout from using the bands with the bars. There isn't really anything I can fault this product on. It is truly a terrific exercise product that will get you results if you put in the effort of using it. A plus is that it is so mobile and compact in the storage bag that I leave it by the television set so that I can get in a little exercise while I am watching" —W. KwokGet it from Amazon for $20.98. | PatagoniaPromising review: "This is my all time favorite jacket. Goes with me everywhere I go, it’s packable enough to not even second guess myself if I should bring it or not. I use it mainly for bike rides around town and any trips I might need a shell to go over some insulation. Works awesome for how minimal this jacket is." —MartiGet it from Patagonia for $99 (available in men's sizes XS–XXL and in seven styles and in women's sizes XS–XL and in eight styles).Or check out a similar jacket on Amazon for $39.25+ (available in women's sizes XS–3XL and in 14 styles). | AmazonPromising review: "I really like how bright they are when I'm out on my early morning runs. I've purchased other lights in the past and they just don't compare. I haven't had to change them yet and I run three to four mornings a week for the last month and a half." —SpeedyGet them from Amazon for $11.99 (available in two colors). | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF

Title Headline: Estas experiencias retratan la situación que se vive en los terribles incendios de Australia
Short Description Sub Headline: "Todo estaba en llamas. Tres casas ya no estaban y el fuego estaba a punto de llegar a nuestro único lugar de refugio".
Content Body: Estas experiencias retratan la situación que se vive en los terribles incendios de Australia | "Todo estaba en llamas. Tres casas ya no estaban y el fuego estaba a punto de llegar a nuestro único lugar de refugio". | publicado January 09, 2020, 16:57 GMT | January 09, 2020, 16:57 GMT | Clare AstonBuzzFeed Staff | Ruth Ellis / BuzzFeedMi ciudad natal se había vuelto oscura por el humo de los incendios en la zona. Mis redes sociales repentinamente estaban llenas de historias y publicaciones de viejos amigos y miembros de la comunidad que se preparaban para arriesgar sus vidas por defender sus hogares. Al momento de escribir esto, algunos todavía lo siguen haciendo. | Siobhan Threlfall / BuzzFeed“Me desperté la mañana del 31 de diciembre alrededor de las 2:30 porque mi madre gritaba mi nombre. El cielo detrás de la casa de mis padres era solo un gran resplandor de color rojo, junto con el rugido del fuego haciendo eco en el valle. Mi mamá y nuestros dos perros evacuaron la ciudad. Mi papá, el jefe de bomberos voluntario de Nerrugundah; mi hermano, Caden; mi hermana, Skye, y yo nos quedamos para proteger la ciudad. Miembros ya estaban llegando al hangar de bomberos para cuando Caden y papá llegaron ahí. Inmediatamente, entraron al camión para (ir a) investigar el incendio, mientras Skye y yo llamábamos a todos en el valle.Papá predijo que el fuego no nos impactaría realmente durante otras dos horas. Mientras esperábamos, pusimos sistemas de aspersores, preparamos nuestras bombas de agua y retiramos los tanques de gas de la casa... todo mientras la radio emitía llamados de auxilio. Hubo llamadas de personas que se encontraban en peligro, llamadas de la tripulación que necesitaba ayuda urgente, así como llamadas que solicitaban ambulancias que ahora se necesitaban por todas partes en la Costa Sur. Mi hermano nos contactó por radio. Él y otra bombera voluntaria, Ashley, habían ido a ver cómo estaban los miembros de la comunidad, pero, por la cantidad de árboles caídos y el fuego que se dirigía directamente hacia ellos, no pudieron llegar con dos de nuestros miembros de la brigada. Se iban a quedar atrapados en su casa en el paso del fuego. No sabía si iba a volver a verlos". | | | Ver esta nota en Facebook | AtenciónEsta imagen es gráficaToca para mostrarToca para mostrar

Title Headline: All You Need Is Love...But Also Maybe These 31 Products
Short Description Sub Headline: The Beatles were actually singing about all of these products.
Content Body: Shopping | All You Need Is Love...But Also Maybe These 31 Products | The Beatles were actually singing about all of these products. | Posted on January 25, 2020, 03:01 GMT | January 25, 2020, 03:01 GMT | Samantha WiederBuzzFeed Staff | Amazon, amazon.comPromising review: "Cannot stress enough how amazing these came out!!! I gave them as a Secret Santa gift to my two friends and they said they're the best gift they’ve ever received. I was a little concerned about the quality of the picture, since it was an iPhone-quality photo off of Facebook, but they came out 10 times better than I had even hoped. 5 stars for sure!!!!" —Amandax054Get the, from Amazon for $24 (available in 10 colors, and sizes S and L). | Amazon, amazon.comSome notable recipes include treacle tart, Molly's meat pies, and Kreacher's French onion soup. Pictured right: pumpkin pasties.Promising review: "I LOVE IT, I'm no master chef, but this cookbook might change that. I might even become a master wizard chef! Anyways the recipes are phenomenal, especially the pies! It's pretty basic sometimes, it's more European-type cuisine, so if you don't like haggis, liver, lamb, or other English/Scottish dishes, etc., then these recipes aren't for you. The book references are cute, and I vaguely remember some of them. My younger siblings go crazy when I make anything from this book because they love Harry Potter." —TigerlilyGet it from Amazon for free/Kindle Unlimited, or $10.95/hardcover. | amazon.comPromising review: "Wow! I've had it for an afternoon and I'm in love. I can't afford to keep going for human massages. *This* I can afford. I think I'm going to buy another one tomorrow so my wife and I don't fight over whose turn it is. Update a few days later: Okay, this many be getting out of hand! I purchased a second one for my wife last week (very smart thing to do). Today, she just asked me to buy two more, one for her daughter and her sister. I just placed the order. I'm using mine three of four 20 minute sessions a day. It continues to work great. Seriously, this is a wonderful product. Spread the word!" —Lynn Robert CarterGet it from Amazon for $49.95. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I got tired of breaking the bank over mascara. My sister suggested Essence Lash Princess False Lash Effect and I IMMEDIATELY fell in love. It provides dramatic length and great volume. I can honestly say I can’t stop looking at my eyelashes in the mirror every single day because of how awesome they look. Also, it is very long wearing. I go from an 8 hour work day right to the gym and sweat like crazy...and this stuff doesn’t budge! I love it!!" —Carrie E. MillerGet it from Amazon for $4.99. | AmazonPromising review: "I got these as a gift for a family member who is a wine aficionado, partly for a laugh but also for their great concept. When she opened them, I did get a huge laugh, but once she understood the concept she was amazed. I've received confirmation from her that they work wonders and truly provide an airtight seal. Now all the corks can go in the trash after they come out and a wine condom goes on!!" —ThomasGet a pack of six from Amazon for $16.97. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I really love this menu board. It's cute, easy-to-see, and gets the job done at the same time. It has made menu planning, keeping a grocery list, and keeping track of upcoming appointments so much easier. A friend who saw mine has already ordered one for herself. It comes with three markers — blue, pink, and green, and you do have to 'prime' the markers first. Once you do that, they work so well and are nice and bright. The menu board is a nice, big size and has a strong magnetic hold." —S. WinkeljohnGet it from Amazon for $19.99. | AmazonPromising review: "These were a suggested item for my bullet journal, and they were not at all expensive, so I went ahead and got them. I'm so glad I did. The colors are beautiful, and don't bleed through when writing normally, BUT you cannot hold the pen down in one spot for any amount of time, or they will bleed pretty badly. A great deal for the price." —DanielleGet a pack of 10 from Amazon for $5.49. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Very impressed with this belt. This one has a clasp, which makes it super easy and keeps the full design! Great quality and came nicely packaged. Have worn multiple times now and get lots of compliments. The buckle isn’t too big but it’s big enough to make a statement! Definitely recommend purchasing!" —Shannon PayneGet it from Amazon for $14.99+ (available in nine colors, and sizes XS—XL). | amazon.comPromising review: "I love these! I was sick of having to scrape face mask gunk out from under my nails so these are a great alternative — plus I can use each for a different product if i'm using two at a time, and not risk cross-contamination. They are a little wide though, so they might not fit in all jars and some you might have to scoop the product out first onto another surface for that reason, or if like me, you use a volcanic clay mask, the product bends the silicone a bit if you try to scoop it from the jar since the clay is thick and the silicone is flimsy. BUT, the good news is they won't break from bending AND they are really easy to clean and wipe off!! Adore these and am definitely never going back to brushes that have fibers." —Amazon CustomerGet a pack of two from Amazon for $3.98. | amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "I'll start off by saying all matte top coats are porous, so by their nature they won't wear as long as glossy polish. Having said that, the OPI matte top coat lasts just as long and re-applies much better than most other matte tops I've tried. Works great on top of gel manicures! If you're hooked on LED gels like me, this polish works great to matte down the ultra-wet appearance of LED-cured gel polishes. If you want the look of completely nude nails for any reason, (fashion, dress code, acting, etc.), but you don't want to sacrifice that protective shield of your super-strong gel manicures, try applying OPI Matte Top Coat over your clear OPI LED-cured manicure. No one will ever know your nails aren't nude, and they won't chip on every doorknob or keyboard." —M. SpaldingGet it from Amazon for $10.50. | AmazonCheck out our write-up of the delicious Mike's Hot Honey!Promising review: "I was a skeptic, but now I AM a believer. This mixed up honey is absolutely fabulous. I ordered three bottles more after my initial order. Why? Because it is really good on everything. And I mean EVERYTHING. Soft pretzels, toast, biscuits, waffles, cereal, yogurt, ice cream, and definitely pizza. Gives everything in your kitchen a small kick of sweet heat flavor without burning your mouth. I have told many of my friends about this magical elixir and they all agree — this is the BEST specialty honey any of us have ever had. Don’t hesitate to buy it. It is absolutely wonderful stuff. I most HIGHLY recommended!" —Jeff R. ClowGet it from Amazon for $6.99. | AmazonPromising review: "Throw out the others, this is the one. I have a drawer full of wine pour spouts of varying designs. Some don't fit all bottles, some leak while pouring, and some are so tall that storing upright in a refrigerator is difficult and none seal completely. This spout/stopper seals completely and lets you lay the bottle on its side. The aerator allows air to move back into the bottle while pouring to avoid the 'glug glug' effect of other pour spouts. The strainer may filter large cork pieces, but is not fine enough for sediment. The portion of the corker that fits inside the bottle has fit every bottle I've tried it in, from standard size bottles to the larger 1.5 liter bottles. It appears to be made from a flexible material that doesn't add any unwanted taste to the wine. " —Jack DallasGet it from Amazon for $5.33. | AmazonPromising review: "I purchased this product to clean those little spaces in my car filled with random crumbs from my husband and dog hair, and it works amazing. Picked up everything and didn’t leave a residue. The lemon scent was faint and didn’t overpower the vehicle while I was cleaning it. But this definitely got in all the little nooks and crannies." —KimberlyGet it from Amazon for $7.99. | amazon.com, amazon.com, amazon.comPromising review: "Another satisfied customer here. I developed some ugly coffee stains on my two front teeth earlier this summer. I could not get them off with regular brushing and they were making me very self-conscious. I found this product and, after less than a week, the stains are completely gone. Great product!" —laurapghGet it from Amazon for $9.99. | AmazonPromising review: "Love this little spoon! It fits perfectly on the edge of my coffee mug. Now, I no longer have to go searching for a spoon to stir my morning coffee! Since it sits on the edge of the cup my fingers don't get sticky from a wet handle. Plus, it's absolutely adorable and makes me think of my own kitty while I'm away at work. This spoon has become an essential part of my morning routine." —Brianna S.Get it from Amazon for $1.59. | amazon.com, amazon.comCheck out a BuzzFeeder's review on this incredible journal!Promising review: "I've been writing in this little journal for three years now and already bought a second one just to make sure I can continue this wonderful habit into a new volume. The quality of this journal is excellent: The creators obviously put some thought into how much use it would be getting. I'm especially pleased with the paper. I tend to press really hard when I'm writing, but the ink doesn't show through on the other side at all. Highly recommended! Get a few, as you'll probably want to give some away." —EdTech-LibrarianGet it from Amazon for $10.17. | Tap to play or pause GIFTap to play or pause GIF Maitland Quitmeyer / BuzzFeedRead a BuzzFeeder's experience with this fabulous winged eyeliner stamp (#3).Promising review: "I just want to make my morning routine as easy as possible. I love winged liner, but I don’t have the steady hand for it without mistakes. This makes the perfect and consistent wing every time. Love it!." —Julie BGet it from Amazon for $13.97. | amazon.com, AmazonPromising review: "I love this cute little makeup spatula! It's so convenient and useful. If you're a makeup/product junkie that doesn't like wasting, (like I am), this is the perfect problem solver for those empty bottles with product still caked on the inner walls. It's long too, so it works in just about any bottle or jar. I only bought one and I use it for everything. It's washable, so it will last you a long time. Great gift for a makeup artist, if they don't already have one!" —Samantha VillaGet it from Amazon for $5.99.

Title Headline: BTS Hung Out With Ariana Grande And Five Other K-Pop Headlines You Need To Read This Week
Short Description Sub Headline: New friends, nominations, and tours galore!
Content Body: Music | BTS Hung Out With Ariana Grande And Five Other K-Pop Headlines You Need To Read This Week | New friends, nominations, and tours galore! | Posted on January 24, 2020, 18:21 GMT | January 24, 2020, 18:21 GMT | Sarah HanBuzzFeed Staff | Emlyn TravisBuzzFeed Staff | | 방탄소년단@BTS_twt | 방탄소년단 | @BTS_twt | 우식씨 SAG 상 축하해 | Reply | Retweet | Favorite | Amoeba Culture / Via youtube.com, JYP EntertainmentChen and Dynamic Duo first collaborated in 2017 on the song "Nosedive."Step Out of Clé has two English tracks, "Double Knot" (for which they released a performance video!) and "Levanter," which were previously released in Korean off of their album Clé: Levanter. They're also about to kick off the US leg of their District 9: Unlock tour next week, which you can get tickets for here! | Yuehua Entertainment, Source Music / Via youtube.com, BlockBerry CreativeGfriend released the track list (featuring two tracks written by BTS' mastermind and CEO of Big Hit Entertainment, Hitman Bang — ICYMI, Big Hit acquired Gfriend's label last year) and a trailer titled "A Tale of the Glass Bead:Previous Story" for their upcoming album, Labyrinth. Ahead of the release of their first mini-album, Reminisce (which you can preorder on MyMusicTaste), on Feb. 3, Everglow announced their first US tour, the Everlasting Tour in USA! The five-date tour includes stops at Dallas, Atlanta, Chicago, Jersey City, and Los Angeles. Tickets have yet to go on sale, but we'll let you know as soon as they do. Loona unveiled the track list for their upcoming mini-album, #. They also opened their own TikTok channel!And the gifts continue, because (G)I-dle unveiled their 2020 I-land World Tour this week too! Stay tuned for deets!P.S. Dreamcatcher's main vocalist, Siyeon, will release a solo single on Jan. 29, ahead of a full group comeback (that's currently in the works).
